adr_address: 73 Amoy St, Singapore 069892
name: Alati Divine Greek Cuisine

reviews.text:
Very decent Greek food!
Greek yogurt is very creamy but fresh with cucumber dressing.
The Greek salad is the most impressive one tonight with very strong olive taste and very generous olive oil dressing.
Grilled octopus is chewy but not too difficult to chew.
We also tried the slow cooked lamb. Decent but not as good as grilled octopus.

Everything was really well thought out and refined without being too uptight.
The food was very tasty, with high quality ingredients and the right cooking. We had a couple of dips, Greek salad and then the octopus and grilled fish, it was very abundant and we were full - they nicely offered Mastiha as a digestive.

The service was attentive, professional, warm.

The place was nicely decorated and it wasn't too cold or too warm.

Definitely recommend it!

Have been here 3 times so far & the food never disappoints. We always go for the dips coz they are so good & most often you'll order more bread but then you'll get too full once the food comes lol. We had their cheese balls with watermelon & grilled fish as well (didn't get to take pics of them). This is a place to come in a big group so you can order more dishes to try, coz everything is so appetizing!

The best Greek restaurants we’ve ever been in Singapore. The ingredients are so fresh and every dish is very delicious.
The desert is also the highlight.

Will come back to try more dishes.
Recommended by a friend. The seafood was fresh and tasted good. The skewers on the other hand was so so. The fries were not crispy.

adr_address: 22 Scotts Rd, Singapore 228221
name: Alma by Juan Amador

reviews.text: Visited for lunch on a weekday. We had the fish and duck each. Mains weren't spectacular but everything else was great. We loved the Egg dish with mantou and butter. Dessert was interesting as well but the flavours came together well. The complimentary petit fours was buttery and crispy on the outside and we enjoyed it. Service was prompt and excellent! Overall a really memorable experience.

Great food and service. Flavours were on point, and loved the presentation. Loved the personal touch of tableside garnishing.

Set lunch I feel is well priced, with decent selection.

We loved the bread, Uni pasta, Duck Breast and barramundi. The Egg had to be our favourite dish of the day.

Nice environment and friendly staff.
And the food is great!

It’s my honour to have an opportunity to try the New Menu. I like the most is my main, the Glacier 51 Toothfish with special mixed with 4 different oils! It’s amazing and taste really good 👍🏻

It’s a wonderful night and dinner with my beloved. 🥂

Recommend 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟
Wonderful lunch - worthy of its Michelin rating. Flawless service, delicately balanced and well curated menu. Delicious wine recommendations to accompany the food.

tried the 8-course menu. overall i think it was a hit and miss. did not really understand some of the dishes and some combinations of ingredients felt lacking harmony. i do like the arctic char, mantou and wagyu. the rest were just okay. no complaints on the service and the sommelier (jessie) was on point. atmosphere felt relax and spacious. hope the dishes can improve and im sure it can be better.

adr_address: 10 Collyer Quay, Level 43, Singapore 049315
name: Altro Zafferano

reviews.text: Altro Zafferano is a fine Italian restaurant situated on the 43rd floor of the Ocean Financial Center. The establishment offers exceptional service and a commendable selection of Italian cuisine. During our visit, we experienced a minor issue with the soup being overly salty, but the matter was promptly addressed by the staff. The wine service was exemplary and complemented the Italian dishes effectively.

Overall a decent option for Italian flair, though a little clinical in its setting. It’s nice that they have a private room for groups but it can get really loud if you’re sitting near by since the glass doesn’t seem to be double glazed. The food were all pretty classic and went down well. Best part was dessert

Exceptional top notch service from the staffs especially from Paneer, Guru and Kelly. Felt like a sky full of stars with never ending surprises from the experience menu. Food was heavenly flown down, with flavours out of this world, paired wonderfully by the amazing chefs. Definitely worth a comeback, in need of an encore from this restaurant for future date nights.

One of the best italian restaurants you can find in Central!! The food is nice and presentation is great too!! Definitely need to commend them for their excellent service.  Love how they make us feel so welcomed and the attentiveness given to our needs! Not to mention the stunning scenery!! Thank you for the hospitality!! Definitely be back again!! Money well spent!!!!

They serve some of the most delectable Italian dishes we've ever had, each dish was prepared with exquisite flavours. We highly recommend trying the White Truffle Tagliolini while it is still in season. The ambiance of the restaurant is brilliant, perfect place for a romantic dinner, or just a night out with friends/family. We wholeheartedly recommend this restaurant to anyone who appreciates fine Italian cuisine and exceptional service.

Our server, Cheryl/Cherry, went above and beyond to make our dining experience truly exceptional, we want to express our sincere gratitude for making our dining experience memorable. Your professionalism, friendliness, and knowledge about the menu were outstanding!

adr_address: 1 St Andrew’s Road, 06-02 National Gallery, Singapore 178957
formatted_address: 1 St Andrew’s Road, 06-02 National Gallery, Singapore 178957
name: Art di Daniele Sperindio

reviews.text:
I'm absolutely thrilled to share my recent dining experience at Daniele's Restaurant. This place is, without question, one of my all-time favourites. Every course served here is nothing short of a joy, making each visit a memorable gastronomic journey.

From the moment you walk in, you are welcomed by a fantastic team that goes above and beyond to ensure you have a wonderful dining experience. Their service is commendable, a seamless blend of attentiveness and professionalism that leaves you feeling well taken care of.

The food at Daniele's is a culinary masterpiece. Each dish is carefully crafted to perfection, offering a tantalizing blend of flavors that leave you eagerly anticipating the next course. The passion and dedication the kitchen put into their creations are evident in every bite, making each meal an absolute pleasure.

I cannot recommend Daniele's Restaurant highly enough. Whether you're a food enthusiast or simply looking for a delightful dining experience, this is a place you must try. The exceptional service, delicious food, and overall ambiance make this restaurant absolutely worth visiting.

Thank you, Daniele's for an unforgettable experience. I can't wait to return and indulge in your exquisite cuisine once again.

Overall, it was a good experience at Art! It’s a good place for occasions, but at this price point, one would also expect better service.

The good: Nice views, well spaced seating for privacy, and tasty food! The variety of sweets at the end was a nice finishing touch - I could only wish I had more space for them!

The bad: Service could be improved. When we first came, there were many waiters standing around and talking by themselves and we had some difficulties getting their attention. Throughout the meal when we needed refills for water, we also found it slightly difficult to get the attention of the wait staff. This was rather ironic as it looked like there were more wait staff than tables but many of the staff were standing around talking by themselves rather than attending to guests. The wait staff were also inexperienced with the menu - we felt that he was pushy in trying to get us to go for the tasting menu (which was more expensive than the course meal) but when asked about the dishes, he was unable to explain some of them.

Absolutely everything was perfect. Exactly what anyone would want in a Michelin star experience. Our waiter took us through a journey of beautiful food. I've never had a waiter that knowledgeable and that dedicated to his craft.

Absolutely a five star restaurant!  The food was innovative and delicious from the starter through dessert with a very good wine list and excellent wine pairings.
I cannot speak enough about the service. It makes the hospitality industry proud. It was friendly, helpful and they make you feel really special.
The atmosphere with its floor to ceiling windows of unobstructed views of the city, the MBS area were absolutely gorgeous.  We had a sunny clear day on our visit on Friday the 22nd but I have to believe that on a rainy day it would feel incredible to be watching mother nature.
I could not recommend this restaurant more on the rooftop of the National Gallery.   If you have not had the chance to enjoy this experience, it is a must for both visitor and Local Singaporean.
Congratulations to the Service Staff, Bar Staff and the Chefs!!!  THANK YOU.

Great outside terrace with sweeping views of MBS and its surroundings.

We have visited just the outside terrace, so I cannot say anything about the fine dining restaurant inside. Outside however the main selling point is obviously the magnificent view. We ordered a bottle of champagne from the well curated wine list and enjoyed the sunset vibes.

Bar snacks were quite decent, but given the fact that this is coming out of a kitchen that currently holds one Michelin star I would have expected a bit more. Overall however, a cool place to enjoy the evening!

adr_address: 138 Market St, #40-01 CapitaGreen, Singapore 048946
name: Artemis Grill & Sky Bar

reviews.text: Attentive service, great good and ambience. Codfish is fresh and firm and together with the sauce, it tastes delightful.  The rest of the dishes are nice too. The cake that we ordered in advance also tasted fantastic.

Saw alot of good reviews for Artemis, decide to bring my gf there to celebrate her birthday! Made reservation 1 mth in advance, only to realise that I have reserved for the sky bar few days before the day, couldn’t find any indoor slot online anymore. Managed to secure an indoor dining by calling in 🙏 as my gf really looking forward to it! thanks artemis!

We reached there on time and being seated at this really nice view of mbs! We had complimentary sourdough bread which was quite nice!

We ordered Fremantle Octopus as starter, for main we had Black Cod and Iberico Pork Loin and crispy fried artichoke.

the star of dish is… the fremantle octopus! love the texture of how well the octopus was cooked and love the tomato and eggplant relish! best combination ever!

then comes the Black Cod, the fish was cooked to its perfection, the puree and sauce has its unique taste and matched perfectly with the cod fish

the iberico pork loin was quite tender, gf commented its abit tough, just find the bean we find it was abit salty

crispy fried artichoke, was over salty. nothing special and was a let down.

As it was my gf’s bday, they have complimentary cake for her!

The only thing we find the staffs probably need to go for some basic training on taking photos for the customers. 😄

I had a company dinner at Artemis, it was a great mood and kind of staff, especially scenery. Food was also tasted.
Price ? Um.... 150~180 per person.

I have been here several times for business dinners. This was the first time i brought my family here. All of them praised the food. My mum who has small appetite, finishes the entire plate of black cod. She said very tasty. My wife and son love the iberico pork and the wagu beef. Not forgetting the delicious scallop and hamachi.  The dessert was also very good. Ended up ordering another one. The price is reasonable and strong recommend anyone to give it a try.

Firstly, the pre-booked window seat offered a beautiful night view, and the elevated perspective from the higher floors was also impressive. Secondly, the food was delicious, with the Black Cod highly recommended.
Lastly, the restaurant staff were friendly and professional.
It’s a wonderful birthday experience with my wife!

adr_address: 51 Bussorah St, Singapore 199467
name: Ayasofya Turkish Restaurant

reviews.text:
Came here for the first time for Iftar and had a pleasant experience. Good food, served by friendly service staffs.

Shout out to staff, Bilal, for being so accommodating and efficient in delivering the service.

Loved the food here!! Mediterranean food ALWAYS slaps hard! We ordered a platter that came with different dips, a pide, grilled haloumi cheese and one mixed grill. The food was really filling! We also ordered their ice tea and it was on the sweeter side but still nice. Would recommend people to eat here!!

Meats were well seasoned and mostly tender. I usually eat my steaks medium rare, and the grilled beef here is "well done". But i found the beef and other meats to be tender and reasonably moist.

Overall an enjoyable meal.

Place is easy to find. Touristy spot. Prices are a little high for their serving size.  But it tasted so good. All types of meat are tender and flavourful. Rice tasted so good. Oily. But good, really. Extra rice cost 6$++

The pizza like spinach bread we ordered was so so. It's a little bland but cheesy. The mango yougurt drink also did not have much exciting taste on it. Turkish tea tasted like lipton. Nothing exemplary. Also, the serving was so small.

Service that time lacked a little attentiveness, but it was ok for us. You need to look and wait for someone and catch his/her attention.

Place has al fresco and indoor dining.

Overall, it was good to try.  But must splurge with its prices. Paid about 130 sgd.

Nice view of the mosque from the restaurant
The meat platter for 4 is what we ordered, great variety of prep for chicken and lamb.. comes with a buttery rice. Loved it.
For sides we had a spring roll that had spinach and cheese, it’s highly recommended..

No they don’t serve alcohol but you won’t be missing out!

adr_address: 38A Martin Rd, Singapore 239072

editorial_summary.overview: Bright, breezy restaurant with blonde wood furniture, an upbeat vibe & menu of upmarket Greek fare.

name: BAKALAKI Greek Taverna

reviews.text:
I loved everything about this place -food, service, quality and ambience.

My colleagues and I walked in during dinner time and fortunately they were able to get us a table. The service was quick and friendly.

My recommendation would be to get the meat platter and the octopus. Everything was excellently seasoned, well cooked and delicious, even the olive oil on the table!!!  We ordered the baklava for dessert but loukoumades were on the house which came as a really nice surprise and I preferred it to the baklava. Price is definitely on the higher end but everything was so worth it.

Had a very nice Greek meal but the popular beers and wine were sold out. The Octopus was succulent with nice smokey taste. The fish roe were a tad bit too salty but that was expected. The lamb was also very good. Pricing was excellent. Wish there was a bar counter to wait at for our table. Very good service and crowd management by the restaurant.

Great authentic Greek food served here. Seafood patter was tasty and filling. Good spread of seafood. Fish was fresh and the octopus was very well done.
Dessert and coffee was also uniquely Greek. I’ll be back to try more dishes

We thoroughly enjoyed the toasted bread with olive oil, sea bream with potato salad, lamb chops with roasted potatoes, baklava and mosaiko. We found the portions to be just nice and the food to be of good quality. We like the music, restaurant decor and clean washrooms. Service by MK and another tall non-Chinese gentleman (forgot to get his name) was attentive and cheerful. Happy to celebrate my birthday here. Will be back!

Huge Greek restaurant with good selection of Greek wine. It’s a pretty popular restaurant so do make reservations beforehand. Food is really good here. Dips can be served in smaller sampling sizes and it goes nicely with the bread and pita bread. The fried cheese with honey and sesame seeds was my favourite. For mains, I didn’t managed to get a pic of the lamb chops but it was good, just ever so slightly more cooked than the same dish we had at Blu Kouzina previously. However, the potatoes that came with the lamb were fantastic. Grilled octopus was tender and the fish was really good and it came with a side of potatoes. In fact, we actually ordered fish twice. Didn’t have the opportunity to order dessert but I reckon it will be quite good.

adr_address: 18 Gemmill Ln, Singapore 069255
name: Bar-A-Thym Restaurant by Francois Mermilliod

reviews.text: Really great restaurant serving excellent French food. Friendly service from all the staff, including Chef Francois! All the food was very good, the stand out dishes were the Iberico pork jowl and the wagyu beef cheeks cooked in red wine. I highly recommend this restaurant and will be back again.

Great restaurant at a fair price. I was there for my wife's birthday and took the 5 courses "omakase". The food was really REALLY good, from the duck rillette to the lobster, the amazing lamb, the great pasta and dessert. Special mention to the amazing bread, It had the true taste of a good French bakery (even in France, not so easy to find such a bread nowadays).

The service was perfect. All the staff was very nice as well as Francois himself. My wife was very happy by the food and the surprise for her birthday dessert! We will definitely come back regularly! Thx guys

Celebrated my husband birthday here and it went well. All the  foods  we ordered were delicious. Staff are very friendly especially Santos, who provides impeccable service.

Thank you so much to the whole team for wonderful food and service. We will definitely go back.

A true taste of France, combining authentic flavors, attentive service, and a charming ambiance. It’s a culinary gem for those seeking a refined and memorable dining experience.
Service was impeccable, Jerriek, a great restaurant manager who is really friendly.
I look forward to returning to indulge in more of their delectable offerings.

Came here for valentine's day dinner and 1st time trying out this restaurant. The 1st entree bread with duck rilettes was really good and we were expecting more great to follow. Trout tatare dish was refreshing. The scallop and foie gras that followed were quite good as well you will expect. We ordered the Angus beef Wellington and the lamb rack and beef Wellington was the winner here nicely rusted with perfectly cooked beef. The white choco dessert was really too sweet though and we couldn't finish which is a shame. Service was good and the dishes came without too much waiting in between. Will drop by to try out their usual menu another day.

adr_address: 165 Tg Pagar Rd, #01-00, Singapore 088539

editorial_summary.overview: Dry-aged beef, charcuterie & a large wine list in an upscale French steakhouse with Sunday brunch.

name: Bar-Roque Grill

reviews.text:
Evelyn was an amazing server, she would check on us at regular intervals and if we needed anything. It’s a joy to be served by her.

Beef Wellington here is second to none. Beef is tender, soft to eat, and moist. Puff pastry is light and buttery. Most amazing beef wellington I had period.

Starters were good but nothing to rave home about. Caesar Salad was topped with a generous amount of cheese. Sauce felt heavy and thick.
Japanese style steak tartare, tastes of soy, mirin marinate. Taste reminiscent of your first tuna poke bowl.

Generally it’s an amazing and enjoyable place to dine at. The wine selection is wide. :)

Dishes were good, beef platter nicely done - medium rare especially the ribeye with a good charred. Ambience was a letdown, where we were seated in the booth the air was filled with smoke smell.....thereafter the need to air our clothes before laundry.

Really thankful that we went Bar-roque Grill to celebrate my sister's birthday. It is our first time trying Bone marrow and beef wellington, and it is nothing short of amazing. It is possible to order just the bone marrow without steak.

Bone marrow comes with toasted sour dough bread, which is just perfect when eaten together with it.

Beef Wellington is cooked with medium rare doneness. Was afraid of it becoming too raw if not cooked perfectly. It was amazing.

Really appreciate the birthday surprise, which ended the meal wonderfully. Thank you! Will definitely be back again!

This was an excellent experience. We tried the bone marrow for the first time and it was tasty and flavourful. For mains we had the beef Wellington and it was perfectly prepared and incredibly tender. Will definitely be back.

Got served by the legendary Evelyn as mentioned by many others in the reviews. She is friendly, provides a very personalised service and even went above and beyond to have a small birthday dessert for me. Thank you Evelyn!

The Wagyu Flank Steak is cooked to my liking. The char and doneness is the way I like it. The price is very reasonable and hence it is value for money.

I will be back again!

adr_address: 435 Orchard Rd, #04-01 Wisma Atria, Singapore 238877
name: Baristart Coffee Singapore (Wisma Atria)

reviews.text:
i found this wonderful place nestle in a section of OCBC bank in Wisma Atria. it’s quiet, comfortable and enclosed by beautiful, colourful books.

was there for lunch, despite it being a weekday and smack during lunch time, the place was peaceful - i was with friends and we could have a pleasant conversation throughout.

the 3 of us ordered our own mean however i can only represent my Wagyu burger - it was brilliant, the bread was soft and the patty was juicy. my friend asked for extra spicy pasta and according to her it was zingy. i would be trying that next time.

from the menu, there were a few interesting choices which i will definitely go back for.

It was a lot of people during Saturday tea break time. Luckily, there was a small table just nice for 5 of us. I ordered the shaved ice as I already had a cup of coffee during lunch. No what I was expecting. Anyway, the new item strawberry yogurt is quite nice with tangy taste. Their cream puff is so satisfying. I love the runny cream but not to the extend of kinda watery.

Baristart is known for having one of the 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 cream puffs and we came here for our tea break a while back to try their January seasonal special: 𝗠𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗮 𝗖𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗺 𝗣𝘂𝗳𝗳 (𝟭 𝗳𝗼𝗿 $𝟳, 𝟯 𝗳𝗼𝗿 $𝟭𝟵.𝟱𝟬). The moment we took our first bite, we instantly regretted not getting a box of 3. The cream puff looked like a fist sized crater, lightly dusted with matcha powder. When we cut into the puff, it revealed the most vibrant green matcha cream that just 𝗼𝗼𝘇𝗲𝗱 out. The matcha cream had a 𝘀𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁 𝗲𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗲𝘀𝘀 which balanced out the sweetness from the cream, we just couldn't get enough of it.

We also got their 𝗛𝗼𝘁 𝗖𝗵𝗼𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗚𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗲 ($𝟴.𝟱𝟬) made with their 𝗛𝗼𝗸𝗸𝗮𝗶𝗱𝗼 𝗕𝗶𝗲𝗶 𝗝𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗲𝘆 𝗠𝗶𝗹𝗸, which had deep and rich chocolate flavour, and was very creamy and delicious.

The vibes at Baristart Coffee are perfect for any cafe day. Although the prices may be high, their cream puffs are surely of a high standard too - and they are a must get for anyone coming down for a try. We’d definitely be back for round two!

Follow us on IG @toofoodtomiss for more foodie content!

Loved their signature cream puff. On the pricier side, but worth a try! Their iced matcha wasn’t sweet and was quite powdery, so I wasn’t a fan, but I’m sure other people prefer this type of matcha latte!

Had a hot latte and Obihiro Butadon as recommended by service staff. The coffee was smooth with light caramel undertones. Loved it. The Butadon on the other hand was ordinary and a bit chewy. Not worth $19.80. The cafe wasn't crowded by the time I arrived, around 1.30pm. Plenty of seats available. Service wise, there was a lot of room for improvement.

adr_address: 65 Chulia St, #05-02 OCBC Centre, Singapore 049513
name: Beng Thin Hoon Kee Restaurant

reviews.text:
The restaurant on the 5th floor of OCBC Centre is a hidden gem! Enter through the main entrance, then take the lift at the rear of the building. Be aware that the restaurant entrance isn't covered, so bring an umbrella if it's raining.

The food is delicious! I highly recommend the dishes in the photo. The service was also fantastic, making it a great place for a gathering lunch or dinner. It's definitely worth the money!

Our extended family of 14 had a great dinner together seated at one table. Staff were considerate to give us a cosy corner which was comfortable for the elder members without cold drafts. Food was of good quality, good portions and delicious without being salty or oily: Garoupa fish was fresh, oyster omelette was crispy with plump oysters, flavorful hokkien noodles with good sized prawns, crispy and tasty ngoh hiang, smooth Or Nee

I had an excellent yam nest and oyster omelette. Im usually not a fan of oyster omelettes but this one was particularly unique, with a thin crunchy omelette and a mild taste for the oysters. Roasted chicken is decent.

Didn't like the shark fin fried rice

This is one of my favourite restaurants for Hokkien fare. I highly recommend their prawn rolls, mee sua and roast chicken. Prices and portions were reasonable.Their service was prompt and it’s evident that their service staff were experienced and passionate about their job.

It's a place where you will find traditional holkien dishes.

Highly recommend the duck salad and hokkien mee.

Service from staff is also efficient and they provided plates, knife and lighter for us when we told told them to help bring out a birthday cake(brought over my ourselves).

adr_address: 115 Amoy St, #01-01, Singapore 069935

editorial_summary.overview: Choice fusion dishes & cocktails served in a comfy locale with leafy decor & happy-hour specials.

name: Birds of a Feather

reviews.text:
The experience at Birds of a Feather is simply outstanding! The food, service and atmosphere are nothing short of excellent.

For those who like spicy, find the chicken in the chill is a must order! The barramundi dish left a very good impression in my dining experience.

Overall, highly recommend for you to come down and try! I will definitely come back again to try the other dishes.

You have to give this restaurant a try. This is my 3rd visit. I have always enjoyed their food. Presentation is top notch, like a piece of art. Though it's fusion food, the flavours of East and West are cohesive. In my opinion, the people who created the dishes have a profound knowledge of flavours and texture. Who would have thought of grilled octopus and feta cheese? Amazing flavours!

used to frequent this cool chic place regularly for their interestint cocktail selection and fusion cuisines

however, the standard of the food and service seems to drop.

slight improvise to the taste and plating.  still prefers the older version especially the buratina sauce and yuxiang eggplant portion strung.

Was a lunch birthday celebration, we ordered the lunch set for 2 at $138+++. Added $20 for prawn, total damage $158+++. Starter 8.5/10, Binjai 6.5/10(Kind of too sweet), prawn 8/10, pork belly kale w rice 9.5/10(Must try! Very sinful coz super oily but tasty). Dessert 5/10. Overall rating 8/10. Worth trying.

Express lunch ($33.90++)
1. Yu xiang eggplant - Good combination though not a lot of eggplant.
2. Mapo tofu - Good, super strong mala flavour.

Find the chicken in the chillies ($19) - Good, strong mala flavour with chicken morsels and cashew nuts but hard to find them.

adr_address: Marina Bay Sands Hotel, Lobby Tower 2, #01-05/05A, 2 Bayfront Ave, Singapore 018972
formatted_address: Marina Bay Sands Hotel, Lobby Tower 2, #01-05/05A, 2 Bayfront Ave, Singapore 018972
name: Blossom Restaurant

reviews.text:
We made a very last-minute booking and was given a 7.45pn slot.  At 7.15pm, they were kind enough to call to say that the table was available and that we could proceed earlier if we were nearby.

Kudos to Jasmine and Emilia for the amazing service.  Emilia was very friendly and put everyone at ease and treated us as if we were regular customers despite it being our first visit!   As we ordered, Jasmine was so kind to tell us that what we ordered was sufficient and advised us against over ordering which was greatly appreciated.  Service was so good that we always had fresh plates for every dish and everything was portioned out nicely for us.

Foodwise, it was fresh, served hot and tasted good!  There were no delays between dishes and everything was well paced.  Peking duck and the chicken were excellent and are highly recommended as a must have if you ever visit Blossom.  The steamed fish was very fresh and extremely well executed.

We will definitely be back again soon!

Service was very attentive, was attended by Reiko & Ah Ying. Refilling of tea was very prompt, and always checked in on the customer’s dining experience. Food was tasty, and they gave really good recommendations on the food. Ambience was perfect , natural lighting, they moved us to a place with comfortable shade. Prices were reasonable the fact that
They are located in Marina bay sands!

Went for lunch without booking. Managed to get a table for 4.
Judy was very friendly and approachable.
But my best vote goes to 1 young lady named Yan Yan. She is very meticulous, attentive and very fast in getting our plates replaced. Glad to have her serving our table.

Friendly and attentive service from Emilia throughout and professional phototaking by Reiko.  We left with an enjoyable and satisfactory experience both from the serving team and the food.  Like the turnip/carrot cake - simple dish well processed and flavourful.

Service at his restaurant is over the top!  Staff is attentive and customer oriented and there are so many servers.  Food is decent but not outstanding.  The truffle tofu is probably the one dish that stood out for us.  The round table size is abit large for our party of 5 and since restaurant in the lobby of the building, it’s not conducive for dinner chats.

vicinity: Marina Bay Sands Hotel, Lobby Tower 2, #01-05/05A, 2 Bayfront Avenue

adr_address: 52 Boat Quay, #05-01/ #06-01, Singapore 049841
name: Braci

reviews.text: Our experience at Braci was probably one of our most memorable meals and the food served was truly deserving of its Michelin star. Would highly recommend getting the seven course menu as there were so many more elements in our dinner incorporated that made it all the more special. Flavours were all very well balanced and overall we left feeling very satisfied.

While my visit to Braci left me slightly disappointed with the service, the redeeming factor was undeniably the delicious food. The flavors were exquisite, showcasing culinary expertise. Despite minor hiccups, the overall dining experience was a satisfying culinary journey that I would recommend for its delectable offerings.

Cosy and intimate restaurant. The 7 course is quite heavy so best to just nibble on their bread. Some memorable dish was the wrapped pasta with shaved abalone core. Also the 100 years old vinegar. The chocolate dessert could be improved. Service was efficient but patchy. Suffered an incident when the wine glass was tipped over by the staff and my whole shirt was drenched. In such a case, perhaps the service recovery could have been better.
me and my husband had a lovely 7 course dinner at Braci :) the food is Italian and genuin with some international touches. Very well served and composted. Highly recommended this place.

Visited in Sep 2023

Braci was on my list of restaurants to visit for over 4 years and I must say that it was worth the wait. It is no surprise that Braci has retained its Michelin 1 star for 6 consecutive years. The menu was a progressive one which is definitely inspired by Chef Mattie’s Italian roots. There are 2 choices for people (5 course and 7 course). I would suggest people to go for the 7 course as the additional dishes in the 7 course meal are worth it. One of my favourite parts of the experience was trying out the 100 yr old balsamic vinegar.

If you’re not taking the wine pairing, I would strongly recommend folks to try out a few of their cocktails, esp. their Negroni (one of the most unique ones I’ve had)

Service was good. The restaurant is able to cater to some food allergies (like my shellfish allergy).

A definite recommendation for fine dining lovers.

adr_address: 10 Bayfront Ave, L1 - 81, Singapore 018956
name: Bread Street Kitchen by Gordon Ramsay

reviews.text:
My very first experience at Bread Street by Gordon Ramsay was truly enjoyable. The food was amazing and beautifully presented. The customer service was excellent, and the atmosphere was truly great.

Tried the Beef Wellington, one of Gordon Ramsay's signature dishes, along with Caesar Salad, two glasses of wine (red and white), pork chops, chicken wings, and Chocolate Fondant with salted caramel for dessert. A delightful culinary experience from start to finish!

The visit to Gordon Ramsay's bread street kitchen was our first experience and was an amazing one. The first bread dish to be presented as an appetiser. It was served warm with a variety of artisanal butters and oils and had the ideal amount of crunch and tenderness on the inside. With each bite, my family and I were left wanting more.

Our ordered fish and chips elevated to a gastronomic masterpiece. We set eyes on the flawlessly battered, golden-brown fillets. Perfectly seasoned, the coating is both delicate and crispy, encasing each delicious and flaky piece of fish. Not to be overlooked are the side dishes, which include mushy peas and tartar sauce that have enough flavour to be a dinner on its own.

The service? Perfect. The staff guarantees that your eating experience will be nothing short of exceptional because they are genuinely kind and professional. You are treated like a VIP from beginning to end, regardless of your level of experience with food or informal dining. The service staff continuously refills our water and replaces our dining plates and cutlery once we have finished a plate of food.

I have been a long-time follower of Gordon Ramsay, so visiting his restaurant was a fascinating experience for me. I was particularly keen on trying his signature dishes: Beef Wellington, Fish and Chips, and scallops with a perfect crust - all of which I have seen on Hell's Kitchen.

We dined there twice. On our first visit, we tried the Fish and Chips along with the scallops, and both dishes were executed flawlessly. The Fish and Chips featured black Atlantic cod, incredibly tender and flavorful, with a delicate and crispy coating. Served with potatoes and fresh green pea puree, it was a delightful dish. The scallops, boasting a perfect crust, were well-cooked inside, tender, and thoroughly enjoyable. I highly recommend this dish.

During our second visit, we indulged in the main highlight, the Beef Wellington, requesting it to be cooked to a medium - it was cooked to perfection. The meat was exceptionally flavorful, tender, and juicy, complementing the puff pastry and truffle beautifully. Served with creamy mashed potatoes and sweet carrots, this dish was a true culinary delight.

Despite these successes, the chicken butter curry we tried was a letdown, lacking the authentic Indian flavors we anticipated.

However, the service at the restaurant left much to be desired. It was slow, and dirty plates lingered on the table for too long. But if one can overlook these shortcomings, the quality of the food makes up for it.

While the prices may be slightly higher than average, the quality of the ingredients justifies the cost.

The food were elegantly presented and tasted as good as they looked! The star of the show was obviously the Beef Wellington. Note that the portion is pretty huge so it was great for sharing. Though the price was on the high side, the overall experience and ambience were better than our expectations. Great place for special occasions.

This was perhaps the most memorable moment for my sister and me during our weekend trip to Singapore to attend a concert. We decided to go for the Beef Wellington experience, complete with three courses, but we had to finish it in less than 45 minutes or else we would be late for the water show that we had reserved a viewing area for (although now they cancel the ticket system). Unfortunately, we missed the reserved tickets anyway because the dessert was so delicious it required more than two bites. We wished we had more time to savor everything slowly. In terms of price and location, I believe the three-course meal was reasonable and definitely filling. I would recommend making a reservation and opting to sit inside, as we couldn't wait and ended up at an outdoor table in the mall, which wasn't as pleasant as the atmosphere inside. However, this did allow us to skip the long queue. The small appetizer could have been larger to make the dish more satisfying, as it was quite mild for just a few bites. As for the Beef Wellington, one slice was more than enough. The bread crust was satisfying, and the thin layer of mushroom complemented the beef perfectly. The carrots were too sweet for our taste, so we didn't eat any. I would return for the dessert, as it was a delightful mix of sweet, bitter, caramelized, and burnt flavors, complemented by a touch of ice cream to end the meal on a high note. The Msupervisor/manager  (Mr.) was very understanding and helped expedite our meal so we could make it to the show on time. However, I found the frontline staff to be not as friendly and attentive. We were only served one-third of a glass of water, and they didn't come back to refill it until the next course. This was my second visit; the first was two years ago when we sat at the bar. Although this time was rushed, it was definitely a better experience with the Beef Wellington.

adr_address: 29 Scotts Rd, Singapore 228224
name: Buona Terra

reviews.text:
I have some mixed feelings about what to rate this place, here is a break down.

Positives

- The wines are well priced! Great value on champagne
- Good diverse menu and execution on the flavours, the welcome snacks were the highlight for me!

Negatives

- I know it sometimes can’t be helped but screaming babies and fine dining just doesn’t match!
- As the tables filled up it was obvious the restaurant was understaffed. Wine glasses were often not topped up and the pacing of food was inconsistent. Sometimes waiting 15mins sometimes dishes were served while previous course plates still on the table
- mouldy air vents!

A lot of potential here but sadly did not hit.

A contemporary Italian restaurant located within the heart of Orchard. Made a reservation for our anniversary dinner on a weekday night and the restaurant was pleasantly quiet.

We had the 5-course set dinner with the choice to top up for pastas and mains. I had the white truffle pasta and steak  while the hubby had the squid ink pasta and pigeon.

It was interesting how they presented the white truffle in a wooden box and shaved the truffle right on my pasta.

The staff were friendly and offered to take photos for us for the special occasion. Overall a pleasant dining experience.

A very highly recommended restaurant. You'll experience great service, great food, great wine and you're sure to have a full belly with immense satisfaction. I'd say Buona Terra has done really well in making the fine dining experience a pleasant one as you get to experience different flavours combined together that exceeds your expectations.

Second experience here. Was given a private dining room as we had a party of 8. The dishes were very different; think the party size allowed for the chef to produce a different range of food like the salt baked turbot. Overall, delicious and balanced with an Italian family style vibe.

Visited in Sep 2023

A fantastic dining experience. The dry-aged duck main course was absolutely fantastic and so was the fish/turbot main course dish. The beef carpaccio course was also brilliant. The restaurant doesn’t have a non-alcoholic pairing and that’s probably a small area where they can improve their ‘value proposition’.

Service was top notch.

A definite recommendation for a classy dinner experience

adr_address: 81 Club St, Singapore 069449
name: CENZO

reviews.text:
Great service but food was kinda mid.

Might have ordered the wrong antipasti but both…. are not good. I don’t even remember what are they but I did not like it.

I love seafood but the crab pasta here was really fishy… :’) Not sure if it’s meant to be like so, but it’s a no go for me.

The prawn risotto though, order that if you are here!! It’s creamy but not surfeiting at all, flavour was good & the prawns are big and fresh.

The Wagyu flat iron was of perfect doneness but am not a fan of the red pepper sauce - feels oily and doesn’t go well with the steak.

My friend said this is the best italian restaurant in sg so we went together

We ordered
-tigelle
: New taste for me and it was iconic. I’ve never think that i can eat pork fat in this way! And the sauce was hit. But the bread was but too thick so for the balance i recommend to use some thin bread.
-scallops
: Top 2 dishes with tartar. I love the collab with cauliflower purée. The savory flavor wad good and the green oil was good combination. Also i love how they cook scallops its crispy outside and super tender inside!
-veal tongue
:the side was bit too overcooked but middle part was tender enough. The sauce was so addicting. The point of this dish is cooked vegetables bottom off the dish! So nice combination with veal tongue.
-pastrami
:it was decent. But i recommend to use soft thin bread and the open sandwich format. Cause for the balance.
-tuna tartar
:tartar was inside of the mini bell pepper and super iconic! The combination with tartar and pepper was insane. This dish was top 2 with scallops.
-sangria
:good for cleansing food

And the service was good they slow down the speed for us! Big appreciate for this one. I love cenzo cuz they have iconic special dish we’ve never tried before! I will definitely bring my friends to introduce cenzo. Thanks for the dishes cheers

As a repeat customer of Cenzo, I have always been impressed with the delicious food, especially their prawn risotto which was particularly delicious, bursting with flavor and cooked to perfection.

However, I was rather disappointed with the service this time as the servers seemed to be rushing us throughout the meal, constantly hovering behind our table and once even wanted to clear our plates before we finish the meal (note the restaurant was not fully occupied at that moment so we weren’t sure why service was so rush). Bill was also dished to us immediately after we finished the meal. This made us felt rushed and detracted from the overall enjoyment of the dining experience.

Hope this aspect of the service can be improved to ensure that all guests can fully savour their meals without feeling hurried. Food was good nevertheless :)

I’ve dine here on two occasion, with friends and with family.

I’m most impressed by the food and service. They were attentive to hear that we were celebrating a birthday and decided to surprise us with a birthday treat  (tiramisu - no pics :

Amazing food and impeccable service! Their flavours were towards the heavier side which I love it. The staff was extremely attentive and and they were also patient in giving recommendations for us too!

Although the price was a bit steep (~$90+ per pax for the items shown + drinks), I felt that the overall dining experience was worth it. 🤩

adr_address: 17a Dempsey Rd, Singapore 249676

editorial_summary.overview: Refined Peranakan cuisine & an ample wine list offered in a lofty, rustic-chic setting.

name: Candlenut

reviews.text:
Fabulous Peranakan dining experience at this 1* Michelin restaurant, Candlenut. The place is located at Como Dempsey.

Quality food here with unique taste. We especially love the Crab Curry, Ngoh Hiang and the Pork Jowl.

Service level here is top notch. Servers will ensure that your cups are always topped up with water; they are also very attentive and will check in with you on your overall experience and also the food quality etc.

Location and atmosphere wise, it is well situated in Dempsey and the overall vibe that the place exudes is that of a relaxing one with modern Peranakan decorations.

Highly recommend this place for Peranakan food, the service oriented staff here and the value for money 1* Michelin experience.
Good food, good service. Price is on the higher end but the food is good. Set menu may be just enough, so if your appetite is large, recommend you order a couple of more dishes.

Delicious Peranakan dishes packed with flavour. We liked everything we tried, especially the Crab curry and the Sambal prawns! The courses aren’t huge, but enough to share and enjoy as a group, we loved that! From starters to dessert, every dish had its unique taste.
The service was attentive and earnest, but not pretentious, which is refreshing to see in a Michelin star experience.
The place is nice, tables are spaced out, gibbing each group privacy and a quiet feel, but it doesn’t have a cozy feel.
All in all the experience was really positive and at a reasonable price range. Highly recommended!

It was a cool evening and we enjoyed dining outdoors - this is a busy but quiet restaurant and tables are spaced out well so there’s privacy. We tried a few items from the menu and  agreed that the next time we would try the omakase menu. Portions were small but in the end everyone felt satisfied and full. Service was excellent.

The only Michelin starred restaurant I want to visit again in Singapore.

Always order a la carte but for the first time, ordered the tasting course. Absolutely enjoyed all!
Wonderful food, good service and affordable price.

There were unknown food charges on my bill. Noticed it at home the next day. I completely trusted the service but should’ve checked more carefully when I paid.
They contacted me later and the charge is returned. Very sincere.

Highly recommend and will visit again.

adr_address: 32 Boat Quay, Singapore 049821
name: Charlie's Restaurant & Bar (Boat Quay)

reviews.text: Nice view and ambiance. A nice place to watch football or some matches and have a drink, specially at night, wonderful view of the river. Service was good. Food was good. The quesadilla was very tasty. Crowded on the weekend and public holidays, especially on NYE because you would be able to see the fireworks by the river. Rcm to reserve in advanced.

It's a sports bar on the Quay.  You can't really expect much.  The edamame were oily, which is weird.  The shrimp were low quality and the sangria was below average...had a fizzy texture instead of a dry red wine base.
Nice view of the river and food is quite tasty! Worth the money if you are into the view.

This is awesome place. Their happy hour deals were worthwhile and the food was surprisingly not too bad. Garlic prawns were very good, salad was tasty and fresh, and the Charlie's Burger was delicious though a tad salty.
The waiters are very friendly and helpful. The river view is superb at night. Although the steak choices are not that much, the pizza, sides, and draught beer didn't disappoint me.

adr_address: 25 Mackenzie Rd, Singapore 228681
name: Chef Kang's Private Kitchen

reviews.text:
All the private rooms to serve the guests, very good place for business dinner with important partners
The dishes we ordered are all very delicious, the chef comes to our room to explain each dish how they cook and why they come out the idea.

I had a very disappointing experience at Chef Kang's private dining on 31 March 2024, which was confirmed well in advance, and I even received a reminder email. Unfortunately, upon arrival for a birthday celebration, the restaurant was not open.

This was incredibly frustrating, especially considering Chef Kang's reputation as a Michelin-starred establishment.

The disorganization ruined the celebratory atmosphere of the day. Well done on this aspect, Chef Kang.

We ate here twice with one of their Michelin VIPs and were completely blown away by the excellent dinner. We were showered with VIP treatment. The food was oozing with Chef's talent, craftmanship and passion. 5 Stars.
However, I was back on my own on 2 other occasions and both meals were disappointing. Was also turned-off by the Chef's arrogant attitude. Looks like they don't treat their customers equal. 2 Stars.

5 Stars for this restaurant.. Although they are a Michelin 1 Star restaurant for consecutive years.

Managed to get a table after booking for very long. They are so popular and is always full house. You can't walk in too.

The dishes are Cantonese style and the wok hei is fantastic!

The restaurant only has 3 private dining rooms.  That is why it is very difficult to book a table.

The staff are very prompt and friendly.

Chef kang is very friendly too and joined us for drinks and photos.

Price is on the high side but it's worth the quality of the dishes.

Chef Kang is a Micheline Star Chinese Restaurant.

His Superior Sharks Fin soup is fantastic.

Every dish carefully and passionately prepared.

adr_address: 9 Craig Rd, Singapore 089669
name: Coucou Authentic Swiss Restaurant and Bar

reviews.text:
Good food, unique and wholesome flavours. The sauce goes very well with the dishes.

Not crowded, but we booked a table nevertheless since we went in a big group.

Serving time took a while, likely due to our group of 10. Reordering some side dishes was prompt though.

Overall an enjoyable meal.

Came here for the cheese fondue. It was served with bread and we had to order additional potatoes to eat with the fondue. It would be great to have more different types of food to dip the fondue with. The rosti was good and the pesto pasta was super fresh. However, I ordered the steak to be medium rare and it was way more rare than expected that I couldn’t chew on the meat and had to spit it out. No complaints about the service, the atmosphere was cozy and comfortable.

We were recommended to come here by Swiss friends living in Singapore. The ambience is nice with many cuckoo clocks and strong smell of cheese. We had the rosti Zermatt which is highly recommended. For dessert we had the lemon pie which was quite sharp. Very popular place so do make a reservation.

The service staffs are helpful and explain each dish when served. Order the cervelas salads well blend with sausage and gruyere cheese. The mushrooms sauce for the filet mignon is light and doesn’t overwhelm the pork favour. The mignon was prepared well, keeping the tenderness. We tried the veal sausage rosti with onion sauce. The rosti is one of the better one in town. Preferred to eat it crisps without the sauce. We had the meringue and the tartelette for dessert. Nothing unique on the two. The aroma of the cheese fondue from next table was irresistible. Need to try it next time.

We relished the fondue Moitie Moitie (Original Swiss Recipe $35++), which comes with a selection of side dishes like potatoes and boiled veggies. Try the pasta with wild boar ragout, a seasonal meat stew, for another intriguing entrée.

It's warm and inviting, with lovely interior decor for getting together with loved ones.

Enjoyed the meal with wines and beers! cheers!!🥂🥃🍻

adr_address: 290 Orchard Rd, #05 - 22, Singapore 238859
name: Crystal Jade Golden Palace

reviews.text:
First the negative: why does a quality restaurant like Crystal Jade have to nickel and dime on little changes like $1.5 pp for water, $.40 for towel and even $4 for table pickles?? You can be better than this.

The positive: the food experience, everything we had was delicious and tasted just perfect. The BBQ roasted platter was amazing, the roasted pork was crispy and so full of flavor. The staff was very polite and professional as expected.

We had a wonderful experience in Crystal Jade Golden Palace. The food and service was excellent. We appreciate that the Peking Duck was served in a traditional way. The restaurant also offered us complimentary Longevity buns for our birthday celebration. The only thing we may have to comment on is that the Peking Duck pancake is a bit too thick. Other than that, everything else was great. We will be back!

Very good service, food and menu options very well explained and able to customize for diners with food allergies.
The guy taking orders was very nice and friendly.  Good job.

Some of the food tended to be a bit salty.

Dessert was good, but pricey.

My husband located this restaurant on Google maps, it was about 10 minutes walking distance from our hotel. It is situated on the 5th floor of a shopping mall and closes at 10pm. Last order is at 9.30pm.

We shared a starter of crispy crab and prawn rolls. They came separately wrapped with red and green sauce.

I had a lamb rack (one lamb cutlet to be precise) on a bed of potato and vegetables. My husband had braised sliced duck for one person with steamed rice. The food was nice and the service was quick. The plates were not hot, so the food became cold very quickly.

The wine is expensive, but always is in Singapore. More cost effective to buy a bottle.

The chrysanthemum and jasmine tea was nice.
Wanted to have a simple chinese meal for 2. Just ordered 1 fish, 1 veg and 1 meat. It was excellent, marble goby was nice and the roasted pork skin was crunchy. Simple but really excellent meal.

adr_address: 30B Boat Quay, Singapore 049819
name: Dark Horse Japanese Restaurant & Bar

reviews.text: Attending my birthday celebration at Dark Horse was an unforgettable experience. From the moment we stepped in, the attention to detail was impeccable. The serene ambiance created the perfect atmosphere for celebrating with friends. The staff went above and beyond, ensuring every aspect of the evening was perfect. The sake ceremony added a special touch, making the celebration truly memorable. As for the food, it was exquisite. Each dish, from the delicate oysters to the flavorful skewers, was expertly crafted and left us craving for more. The combination of traditional flavors and innovative twists made for a culinary journey that delighted our taste buds. Overall, it was a birthday celebration that exceeded all expectations, leaving me with cherished memories that I'll treasure for years to come.

Absolutely amazing place. Have been several times and will continue coming back. The food was super delicious, great quality Japanese staples, very flavorful and juice. The vibe is comfortable and the staff is kind. Everything from food to alcohol is priced amazingly, definitely recommend checking it out.
Love the view and vibes here. Creative japanese food made with love paired with a cool wine list! Owner sometimes makes cocktails too!
A hidden spot for a secret rendezvous serving authentic Japanese food and premium drinks at reasonable  prices

We had a lovely dinner. We had the Okonomiyaki (mixed seafood), tuna sashimi bowl, and some skewers. Everything was delicious and the view was amazing (have your drinks on the patio!). Wonderfully welcoming and attentive staff.

adr_address: 1 Empress Pl, #01-03 Asian Civilisations Museum, Singapore 179555
formatted_address: 1 Empress Pl, #01-03 Asian Civilisations Museum, Singapore 179555
name: Empress

reviews.text: Had an intimate wedding in the family at Empress. Food was good. I love the soup in coconut. Special thanks to Maggie who was very attentive to details like giving us stools to our bags, very swift in serving and clearing our plates too. Thank you for changing the one of the soup to suit a last minute dietary requirement. We feel so lucky to have her assisting our table. For those who are considering holding a wedding here, you are in safe hands.

A good restaurant at the Asian Civilization Museum. One of the key features of the restaurant is the terrific view of Singapore River side. Had the set lunch and it was a sumptuous dim sum and Cantonese style dishes. Great layback ambience. Very good attentive service

Was a bit nervous coming back after 2 years as I’ve read reviews on how the quality has dropped, but my worry was unnecessary.

Food is still as good as before, perhaps with the exception of the halibut that we felt was not as fresh. Managed to impress my superb cook sis in law and her entire family so that’s an absolute win.

Favourite dishes include the black pepper beef, Hokkaido scallop (asparagus was HEAVEN), impossible mapo tofu, and roasted duck. Not to forget the Ginger Bread Creme Brûlée!

Thank you once again for making our Christmas dinner memorable!

They are situated on the ground floor of the Asian Civilisation Museum and right by the Singapore River. The location and ambience are both perfect and food is really good too. They also serve vegetarian dishes here. Service could be more attentive though.

Quite disappointed with the flavour or the food. Quality is good, like the prawns were juicy and fresh, but the flavour was meh. Salmon skin was incredibly crunchy though. Sure we were there for an event but expected a lot more flavour wise. Surprisingly enjoyed the black sesame ice cream.

adr_address: 16 Jiak Chuan Rd, Singapore 089267

editorial_summary.overview: Intimate restaurant plating elegant Spanish dishes with an inventive, contemporary twist.

name: Esquina

reviews.text:
Came here a few years ago and recently decided to try it again. The food is good, no doubt about that. Presentation is nice and portions are decent. Was looking forward to the paella the most but I'm not sure if I was expecting too much or standards dropped a little. It's still tasty! But the texture was a little too mushy that day.

Oh seems like there was some execution failure on the lava cake as well. But flavors were okay, so it's fine.

Also don't try to enter the restaurant even a minute before 6pm. The waiter will sternly tell you they open at 6pm. It was a rather odd experience and maybe it put a dampener on the mood a little tbh. It's just 1 minute.. maybe don't unlock the door.

As a tourist, the image of a city is down to the details creating by people who are passionate. Esquina is definitely the true representation. Highly recommend to book table by the bar. You will witness an orchestra of good team work. Gentle tap on shoulder, joyful smile to each other… you can feel the food is prepared by love. Foods are excellent especially hearing the number of hours put into preparation. PS. Chef and sou-chefs are all eye candies who made my mum so happy. As she kept saying, “fresh…. Very fresh”. Thanks guys.

Food in general is on the saltier side. The uni paella is more like glutinous rice and the use of uni was not appropriately use in my opinion. Pork jowl was good. Oyster was fresh but the sauces which is premixed is a bit too salty. Staffs are very serious looking and doesn’t really engage into conversations even thou it’s a bar top set up.

Overall, the food left more to be desired. They were also served at a lukewarm temperature. 😕

We had the octopus (good), tuna ceviche (OK, could be fresher), uni paella (OK), and the lamb leg (good, but small).

The second floor dining room is quite cosy though.

An establishment that has weathered the test of time, consistent and runs like a well oiled machine. A compact but well covered menu with daily specials. High quality food and tasty. Have to put a credit card deposit when booking online though. Wine options are quite pricey, even the entry level ones.

adr_address: 40 Hongkong St, Singapore 059679

editorial_summary.overview: Elevated Spanish dishes & cocktails are prepared in an open kitchen at this trendy eatery.

name: FOC Restaurant

reviews.text:
Superb dining experience here!
The food was so good we barely took 1/2 the photos we ate but here are some! The best was the salted caramel butter toast with anchovy… it was creamy & rich yet an explosion of flavour with the brine of the anchovy. The toast was a nice crunch. Octopus with pork jowl was nicely seared & pork jowl was so tender. Both paellas are good but the one with the seafood broth has an amazing aroma - totally reccomend that if you’re a seafood lover.

Great service by the team as well & interesting presentation of cocktails!

FOC restaurant exceeded all expectations during our birthday celebration lunch. The Spanish cuisine was outstanding, with each dish bursting with great flavors.

The service was impeccable, with attentive staff ensuring a memorable experience.

The vibrant and lively atmosphere added to the overall enjoyment. Highly recommended for a special occasion!

Pleasantly surprised with how well this meal went.
Very happy with the starters, with our favourite being the parmesan cheese churros (with black truffle sauce). This is a must order. Another favourite is the patatas bravas. It's elegant in presentation and with each bite, the thin layers of potato really gives a remarkable texture. Not the biggest fan of the broken eggs, tasted regular.
They have pretty good mains too. The paella was delicious! Creamy and very flavourful. The ribs were nice and tasty as well, but needing a bit more of meatiness. The slices were a bit too small, thus, lacking some juiciness. That steak though is yummy as. The accompanying pepper adds another layer of flavour.
They have pretty good cocktails as well. And the service was wonderful. Can't wait to go back!

Flavourful, unique paella. The Argentinian Prawns is a delightful surprise. We can’t get enough of the sauce. Hope it came with more sourdough. Love the tasty and toasty Padron Peppers.

Great and fast service. Water always get refilled. Servers are attentive.

Great place for a hangout or a date night that serves up a amazing Spanish dishes.
Personally, I highly recommend the Patatas and the scallop and suckling pig paella. Amazing dishes. The cocktails were nice to view and drink.
The dessert we had are a little too sweet for our taste buds but might be great for some.
Definitely a place to revisit again!

adr_address: 13 Stamford Rd, #02-28 Capitol Singapore, Singapore 178905
name: Famous Treasure Chinese Restaurant

html_attributions: One of A Kind “OOAK 我们不一样”

reviews.text: Nice atmosphere restaurant. Service is good as well~they will consistently change your plates and refill drinks for us. Can give it a try for Peking Duck as they are having 50% promo right now. Originally, it was $98/piece, but now it is half price. It's a bit slow when serving dishes, but it is still acceptable overall.
Staffs were friendly and outlet is very clean and bright. Me & my mates had a great CNY dinner gathering with special menu. Thank you guys! Food was AWESOME!

A Hidden gem around this area. First time visited Famous Treasure and the food was excellent and the service was on spots. The waiter knees that we were busy eating Chili crab so they served our veggies and Hokkien mee after we almost finish our crab. This is the first time ever I had this thoughtful service. Definitely will be back again to explore more dishes!

Didn’t know where to go for dinner at Capitol piazza, we saw this restaurant facing the escalator in front of us, we took the escalator up and went to give this restaurant a try.

From the outside, we thought it was not crowded, until we went in and realise that it was actually quite full of diners in there.

Ordered a fish head curry and roasted pork belly.

The fish head curry was hitting the spot, right on point! Tasty and the curry spice is superb!

However, the roasted pork belly, we find it falling short compared to some other Chinese restaurants out there. Hence only 4 stars were given.

Visited for Lunar new year reunion lunch. Unethical restaurant. They are not honest because what was sold as "live prawns" were not live at all.

Drunken prawns were served as prawns in heavy herbal soup. (We saw no live prawns!) Prawns heads were cut, back of the prawns were also cut open. Texture was terrible and tasted nothing like live prawns. Some of the prawns were black and shell were fully stuck on the flesh. Roast pork smells of heavy porky smell, did not taste fresh.

When we asked, they covered up and shrugged us off. Disappointing meal, definitely not worth the trip to have a meal here.

adr_address: 20 Craig Rd, #01-03, Singapore 089692
name: Firangi Superstar

reviews.text:
Exquisite experience from start to finish. The moment I walked in, We were greeted by a warm and inviting atmosphere. The decor added a touch of elegance to the space. The staff were not only professional but incredibly friendly, providing top-notch service throughout the meal. From the appetisers to the desserts, every bite was a delight to the senses. The attention to detail in each dish was evident, and it truly elevated the dining experience.
What truly set this restaurant apart, though, was the personalised touch they added to our visit. They went above and beyond by printing out a picture of my friend celebrating her birthday and presenting it to us as a keepsake. And to top it all off, they surprised us with a delicious birthday cake, free of charge.
Overall, our experience at Firangi was nothing short of exceptional. I can't wait to return and create more memories at this fantastic restaurant.

I went today for my partner’s birthday and the place was stunning! It felt like we were dining in an art gallery, the atmosphere was incredible! We ate the set lunch and the whole food journey was like probably one of the best i’ve ever had. Especially with our server Rajinder who made the whole experience all the more enjoyable by going out of his way by explaining to us some of the dishes we were having which we really appreciate! Definitely going to recommend this to my friends and family! And also thank you for the complimentary birthday cake and polaroid!!!

It was my first time here yesterday and I really enjoyed the cuisine. Food was served hot, staff were attentive and took time to introduce the food to us.

They have a wide selection of chutneys - personally prefer the mint one. They have a vegetarian option for all the 3 mains (in their set lunch menu). The naan was super good and the lamb (main) was soft and tasty.

Cosy atmosphere with good selection of music.

We have been to many nice (and award winning) restaurants but have both agreed that Firangi Superstar is one the best, if not best restaurant we have been to the past year.

Food was exceptional and we were really glad to have tried dishes we have never came across before at other Indian restaurants. From the amuse bouche to the desserts, everything was exceptional and we almost could not find fault in any of the dishes. Only minor comment is that the brussel sprouts can be a tad less sweet (it was delicious nonetheless).

Service by the crew was impeccable. Special thanks to Siva, the restaurant manager, for the incredible and genuine high level of service that made our night. The restaurant is very lucky to have him and I look forward to meeting him again the next time we visit.

We will definitely be back.

This review is for the weekend brunch experience. We visited in February.
Service is good and they took very good care of us.
The food portions were very generous for the brunch set and we left stuffed. Flavour profiles in the starter box were interesting!

adr_address: 64 Tras St, Singapore 079003
name: Fleur De Sel Le Restaurant

reviews.text:
Very casual atmosphere. Being decoration which give a sense of warm ambiance.

Food were great. Wonderful with each course. Chef was definitely friendly. One of the most friendliest chef I’ve seen and talked.

Worth the time and money to check them out.

gorgeous restaurant, wonderful service and very delish food. went for the degustation menu and it didn’t disappoint :) also loving the quirky cat and dog statues! very stuffed after the whole course, didn’t managed to finish the sweets but it was a great experience overall! :)
Came for degustation lunch set. Overall food is delicious. Portion is kinda small but the dessert le baba was huge enough to make me full. Will be back for dinner.

Was there for a post Christmas lunch and we had the lunch set which came with Trout. Presentation was really nice, colours were amazing, as was the restaurant decor and service was attentive.
Unfortunately we had a bone in the trout which personally for me, in a place like this, marred the experience. While the servers v briefly apologized i don’t believe it was genuinely addressed to my own expectations. Maybe a misalignment of expectations i guess - may give the establishment a second visit in future but just perhaps not yet.

We came on Saturday and ordered the tasting menu. The food is great with excellent service! The degustation set lunch is $98 per person and it’s quite affordable especially the number of dishes and quality. Highly recommended place

adr_address: 8A Marina Blvd, #02 - 02, Singapore 018984
name: Forbidden Duck

reviews.text:
[Mar 2024] We might have found the best duck in town here at Forbidden Duck! The signature duck is tender, bursting with robust flavours. It’s perfect on its own, but you can also elevate it with the varied condiments that came with the dish.

The pan fried carrot cake that we got (available only for lunch) is also highly recommended.

Service is prompt and top-notch.

[Update in Mar 2024: Visited restaurant with fam again for dinner. The ambience at night is definitely better, food were as tasty, but the duck this time was not as tender and juicy.

For birthday celebrants, they offer 50% discount for whole duck (min spend $80 for other items).]

Had a fantastic dinner at Forbidden Duck, a cantonese restaurant by famous ‘Demon Chef’ Alvin Leung.

We made a dinner reservation for 5 pax on a Friday night and the place was not too packed.

We tried their signature slow roasted duck, cereal prawns, sweet and sour pork, pan fried marble goby, homemade beancurd and marble beef. The roast duck was excellent, so juicy and tender. The fish and prawns were really fresh and well executed. All dishes were on point except the beef that could have been more tender, we found it rather tough.

Do note that their signature yuzu egg tarts need to be reserved in advance ($8 for a plate of two).

Total bill came to about $400 for 5 pax.

Belated review:
Booked dinner for 6, 21st October 2023 for my wife’s birthday with my 3 boys and daughter in law, other two daughter in laws were not able to attend due to work and one got sick at the last minute.
Can’t get any fresher!

Food was very good, have to give special thanks to Cathy for assisting me in selecting the dishes, her recommendations were very good. My family enjoyed the meal, it was wonderful.

Again, special thanks to Cathy and team.

Spend $80 on ala carte dishes (drinks & desserts not counted) to get 50% off on the duck (from $88 to $44)! This is the on going birthday perks, claimable during birthday month and you need to show your identification to the staff. Do make reservation and to reserve the duck!

Duck is amazing! Juicy and the skin is very crispy. Flavours also well marinated and don’t have that very strong duck odour. The bun is calamansi infused, can really taste the citrus.

Iberico Pork Char Siew & Roasted Pork Belly was yummmmmy. Char siew is soft, tender and charred. Roasted Pork had a good ratio of fat to meat coupled with crispy skin layer.

Panfried Turnip Cake in XO sauce delicious can order.
Hot & Sour Duck Soup can skip… toooo oily.
Braised E-Fu Noodles was average but the portion size is huge.

Yuzu Giant Egg Tart was hmm okay only and don’t get why the rave. The egg filling was so so. Just get one piece to share enough.

Overall very good deal during birthday month! The duck is the most memorable dish.

The famed yuzu egg tart was interesting but somehow both flavours dont go well together for me.. maybe becauze the yuzu flavour overpowered the egg custard.

Hot n sour duck soup was nice - loved the thin slices of duck. Very small bowl for $12...but one person definitely cannot finish the whole bowl. Can be jelak.

Duo roast pork charsiew was very nice. Crispy skin, soft meat. Cant go wrong.

Carrot cake okok. Nothing special.

Eefu mee not very nice. Slightly soggy and mushy.

The duuuck... it was tender. Interesting way to pair with their calamansi bun. Duck skin was not crispy though, not sure if it was supposed to be crispy too. But at least meat was soft!

Overall, nice quiet place for a weekend chinese meal. I wont come here for dimsum though, super expensive.. 3 pcs hargao $9. But I guess for the location, it may be reasonable?

Also, location can be hard to find if you come from street level. Look for a corner with 1 lonely lift ;)

adr_address: 42 Boat Quay, Singapore 049831
name: Forum Seafood Village Restaurant

reviews.text: Delicious chilli crab! Great service. And a fun experience, they rang a bell as they brought out than! The flying noodles were very impressive, much taller than I expected!

Stunning view in this place, the food just made me go mmmmmmm.
Super happy with this restaurant.
I will definitely be coming back soon!
Very impressive experience with delicious chili crab and friendly staffs. would visit again! When you hear the bell should clap your hands.

I recently dined at Tian Tian Fisherman’s Pier, also known as Forum Restaurant, and unfortunately, my experience was far from satisfactory. The restaurant, which had a nice area, fell short in several key areas.

Firstly, the food quality was underwhelming. The dishes lacked the freshness and flavor one would expect from a reputable establishment. The presentation was lackluster, and food is extremely overpriced. detracting significantly from the overall dining experience.

I had high hopes for a pleasant dining experience at Tian Tian Fisherman’s Pier, but the reality was a stark contrast. Both the food quality and the level of service were subpar, and it's unfortunate that the restaurant did not live up to its reputation. I hope this feedback is taken as constructive criticism, as there is certainly much room for improvement. $200 for this LOL.

Good beer deals! $5++ for corona and a range of beer.
Tried the ee fu noodles. good stuff!
Shoutout to uncle Alan who was great and accommodating staff :)

adr_address: 1 St Andrews Road 05-03 National Gallery, Singapore 178957
formatted_address: 1 St Andrews Road 05-03 National Gallery, Singapore 178957
name: GEMMA Restaurant

reviews.text:
The service is impeccable and the atmosphere is perfect for dates.

The food is mostly a hit but once in a while (very rare but it happens), can be a miss. Might not seem like much to some others, but I especially love their bread with the seasoned butter. Steaks and pasta here are almost always good but some of the sides can do more work. Do try the octopus if you can, it’s sooooo good!

Have visited several times, including our anniversary in Feb, and will continue to support this business.

Loved the items by Chef Daniele. The Rocciola Amberjack was brilliantly done with a good balance of flavour and fragrance. Loved his pasta too. Another great dish with an explosion of flavours with every bite.

Food was awesome and fitting to the fanfare. Price point for the set lunch was well worth the money. Only downside was the service. I had intended it for a birthday celebration and left a note via email to their staff with their acknowledgement. The staff was not attentive when the meal was over. I had to ask for the birthday complimentary dessert and they seemed at a loss. Moments later they served. Was probably a mix up. But the surprise for my partner wasn't there already. Other than the service mix up, all was good. Just a tip, staff should brush up on articulation of the food descriptions. It seemed they were mumbling all the time. If not I'd have given a 5 for service.

We have family dinner here, I am so satisfied with food and service. Alvin is great guy to recommend us for food, they also have great list of wine. Worth money to experience this such excellent service.

Had a lunch there for the first visit and their dishes were mind blowing! Appropriate pricing and portion, it’s delicious. Friendly service throughout, there are quite a few wine selections too. Love the ambience and I will definitely back here again.

vicinity: 1 St Andrews Road 05-03 National Gallery, Singapore

adr_address: 16 Stanley St, Singapore 068735
name: Gaig Singapore

reviews.text:
Somehow a search on Espanol food led me to Gaig Restaurant, a quaint family restaurant that marries old traditions with modern interpretations. And I’m impressed after a visit here!

The food here evokes that feeling of warmth and nostalgia, while having that touch of sophistication. Being an individual who is into unique food adventures that evoke a wealth of subtle emotions, a meal here definitely satisfies me.

The ambience here feels very cosy and intimate with soft lights and the shelves and tables lovingly decorated with quaint bouquets of dried flowers. At the same time, it is classy, with hints of upmarket decor, making it more perfect for dates.

Service is very friendly and professional. And they make good recommendations on wines. I really enjoy my time here!

I always love to try as many signature dishes as possible without overstuffing myself, so tasting menu is obviously my choice.

The best tomato soup comes in the form of Salmorejo Soup, which is tomato based cold soup and jamón ice-cream. The soup is slightly creamier in consistency and packs with the nuanced zest and sweetness of tomatoes. The rich taste is further elevated with the meaty savoury sweetness of jamón ice-cream.

As a seafood lover, I’m so looking forward to Seafood Fideuà short noodles paella-style with Carabinero prawn. Nicely grilled, the prawn has firmness, briny sweetness accentuated by the lace of smokiness. The short noodles is of al dente texture, perfect.

Catalan Crème Brûlée is the best Crème Brûlée I ever have. No doubts about it. The chef managed to transform this old school dessert to an elevated and sophisticated version while retaining that bliss of simplicity evoked by this dessert. The custard is presented in foam form, rendering light and airy, which contrasts so well in texture with the toffee ice-cream. The lemon syrup is like a touch of gold added to the dessert, lifting up the taste and introducing complexity to it. A must-try here.

Thoughts: Impressive Traditional Catalan Fare that also surprises

A Spanish restaurant in Singapore located in this high competition zone where there are so many of choices for the different cuisines... The dishes are yummy but in quite small portion for each order, relatively higher price compared to most of the local Spanish restaurants we can get in Singapore
Service is good, the staff is very helpful, which is a plus.
Seems more suitable for the couple who is looking for the quiet place, not for family who may need bigger portion to get full..
They offer 1for1 corkage waiver, quite typical for the local practice, a plus, too

Purveyor of high-end Catalan cuisine. The offered tasting menu purports to be an overview of the restaurant's offerings, but has some notable misses. Service is attentive, though slightly pushy, while ambience is excellent on a quiet midweek night. In all, given the variable quality of the tasting menu, I would probably recommend going for ala carte versions of dishes you are actually interested in eating.

Liked:
