- Galician octopus and pork belly. Honestly the best thing we had, and is unfortunately not included in the tasting menu. I think it should be - it's an excellent and easily-portioned showcase.

- Of the tasting menu:
- Amuse bouche was suitably amusing: a shot of unseasoned yet highly fragrant mushroom stock.
- Salmorejo soup with jamon ice cream was an interesting starter, though I couldn't really taste the jamon in the ice cream.
- Of the tapas courses, the croquette and bomba were standouts, especially the surprisingly spicy and piquant sauce underlying the latter.
- Stuffed Cannelloni. The presentation (a single sad-looking cannelloni spooned over haphazardly with a thick sauce) is unappetizing, but it tastes pretty good.
- Catalan creme brulee was excellent and a satisfying end to the dinner, as were the petit fours served after as a nice gesture commemorate our special occasion.

Ambivalent:
- Of the tapas courses, the toast-based tapas (the jamon and the anchovies) had toast that was a bit too crispy - when you bite into it, the toast breaks up and gets all over the table. In the case of the jamon, because of the way the jamon is shingled, it's all too easy to end up eating a whole piece of ham with your bite of toast, so that you're left with excess toast and no ham at the end. Basically the mechanics of those dishes doesn't quite work.
- Seafood Fideuà from the tasting menu. Carabinero prawn wasn't the freshest, and the short-cut noodles themselves had a sort of rubbery overfried texture while not being as flavorful as they looked.
- Crispy suckling pig with strawberries from the tasting menu. The suckling pig is good, if normal, but the presence of fresh strawberries strikes me as odd. Thought it would be good as a compote or something.

Disliked:
- Apple and Fennel salad, separately ordered. Honestly very meh; the one-note vegetal quality of the fennel overpowers the dish, burying the taste of the apple. A dish that doesn't really come together.

Had dinner at Gaig on Friday night. When we entered the restaurant,  I initially felt it had a little stiff atmosphere but those worries wore off as the evening went on.
The service staff had excellent knowledge on the menu and recommended good dishes for us to try.
They were very friendly and even shared occasional banter with us whilst changing our plates or serving our food.  Special shout out to the male wait staff who wore specs, sorry we didn't get your name but you really changed the vibe of the night for us. 😊😊👍👍

Chef Marti, the Head Chef went around the tables checking in on the guests. We enjoyed chatting with him as well.

We had the anchovy on toast, jamon iberico, padròn peppers, mushroom croquettes, bomba de la Barceloneta, the Gaig's cannelloni, Galican octopus and pork belly (not pictured because I forgot! Haha!), the suckling pig dish and the Catalan creme bruleè.
Everything was lovely and I enjoyed the food very much!
Personally I prefer the more casual Spanish tapas styled food. But this experience was very enjoyable aswell for a special occasion.

Definitely will come back again to try the other items on the menu! 👍👍

Definitely one of the better Spanish food restaurants here. It's my second best Spanish food restaurants here this far. The ambience is rather upmarket.

We had the Galician grilled octopus, red prawn gambas, crispy tomato bread for starters. For mains, we had the crispy suckling with strawberries and the braised pork cheek rice (photo not included). Food is flavourful yet not salty.

adr_address: 107 North Bridge Rd, #04-07, Singapore 179105
name: Godmama - Peranakan Restaurant Singapore

reviews.text:
A lovely upper storey restaurant in Funan for those needing to satisfy their Peranakan food cravings. The Ayam Buah Keluak did not disappoint, the chicken meat was generous and we loved scooping out the flesh from the nuts to mix into the flavourful gravy and rice.

We also had the classic Chap Chye and a Kopi Buah Raja (coffee with durian purée and caramel syrup), which gave us the sweetness needed to complete the meal. Service and ambience were decent, and as the restaurant is usually packed, reservations are recommended and to arrive on time as the tables will be needed back after a certain duration for other diners.

Very thankful to the great service from godmama. We were having course nearby, so we made reservations and pre booking of food for 1pm on a Sunday. Sundays are usually very packed but they kept our seats for us and serve our food promptly when we arrived at 115pm.

They called in a few times to check in w us, to ensure the best service for us! Love it!

We loved everything we ordered - Otah, buah keluak, chap chye, sayur lodeh, Babi ponteh, sambal udang, ngoh hiang and butterfly pea rice. Amazingly done! Favourites are Babi ponteh (really soft tender pork belly slices), Sayur lodeh (very nice coconut milk infused).

As for desserts, we prefer the durian creme brrulee over the pulut Hitam panna cotta.

Will be back for good Peranakan food!

Food in general was pretty good. Loved the lamb shank rendang, and nasi ulum. The rest were ok. The popiah ...can give it a miss. Skin was dry and the popiah came falling apart. Not a very nice sight.

Drinks were good.

Staff need a bit more knowledge on what they are serving.

The best food I have ever had in a while!
Well Balanced, full of a complexity of the natural ingredients harmonious in the dish.
Sensational experience while staying in town.

I recently had the pleasure of indulging in some truly amazing Peranakan cuisine at Godmama, and it was an unforgettable experience. The dishes were a vibrant tapestry of flavors and the meticulous attention to details in the preparation of each dish was evident, from the aromatic spices that were perfectly balanced to the tender, succulent meats and the fresh, crisp vegetables. Absolutely loved the Nasi Ulam, Bush Keluak and Gingerflower and Lychee Sorbet. The restaurant's ambiance was great too! The staff were exceptionally friendly, which enriched the dining experience even further. This meal left a lasting impression on me. I cannot recommend it highly enough to anyone looking to explore the exquisite flavors of Peranakan cuisine. Five stars without a doubt and will definitely be back!

adr_address: 390 Havelock Rd, Level 1 King's Centre, Singapore 169662
formatted_address: 390 Havelock Rd, Level 1 King's Centre, Singapore 169662
name: Grand Shanghai Restaurant

reviews.text: Love their suckling pig and had been a regular here. Their service staff are really attentive and friendly. Manager are also flexible and knowledgeable to recommend their signature dishes to us, never felt being push to over order. Live singing is entertaining for the new comers but not for the regular. Highly recommended

Attended BYD-Singapore 10th Anniversary dinner here. Nice ambience with nice food. the double-boiled soup is very nice, the pan-fried fish taste good, and the fried noodles is stuffed with prawns. Other than the duck, they don’t provide any sauce for you, and I believe they would like you to taste the original taste of each dish. Overall, I love the food here.

Today we were treated to one of the most opulent, extravagant and memorable lunches we ever had. We were hosted by Chef Fong who is close friends with the executive chef that made a special lunch just for him and our family. Every dish was articulated with precision, creativity and a perfect harmony of flavour and texture. Some of the highlights included their signature apple and lychee smoked duck, dragon well tea shrimp, bird cage presentation of three dim sum, drunken chicken with longan, xiao long bao... even their complimentary peanuts and XO sauce were absolute perfection. You savour in a lap of luxury in their elegant dining room. This was an experience as close to perfection as you can possibly achieve. Staff were incredibly friendly, courteous and attentive. This is a meal that we will not soon forget! Our compliments to the chef and the entire staff for the great memories!

Enjoyed a lovely dinner with the family celebrating my dad's birthday here.
David and his team were amazing ! The weekly Sunday stage performance brought reality into movies where you see the ladies singing with a LIVE band playing while dinner is being served. My parents particularly enjoyed the chicken wanton soup, snow cabbage, and smoked duck ! The longevity buns served on the peach tree concept were gorgeous !
There's nothing to fuss about having dinner here.
Impeccable!

Attended the UFM1003’s 22nd Birthday Celebration at this restaurant recently.

Truly impressed by the dishes they served!  So delicious & each portion served was just nice!

Their service staff are mostly elderly who are experienced, efficient & polite.  Very much better than some places that hire temp…

Their herbal soup is super nice! & the dessert is a “killer”!

Will definitely be back again :-)

adr_address: 36 Purvis St, #01-03, Singapore 188613

editorial_summary.overview: Elevated French dishes & an extensive wine list offered in modern, sophisticated surrounds.

name: Gunther's

reviews.text: Good service and quality food. Serving size is not big enough probably because of the brunch deal. The pasta was really well cooked and it’s my favourite. Service by the staffs were exceptional as they took care of us properly. Definitely recommend this place for a romantic meal with partner for a memorable day.

Lovely experience with Gunther's.
Tried the discovery menu with a glass of wine each, one of our starters were taking abit longer than usual and we were offered a complimentary dish of caviar pasta starter each.

mini baguette is fantastic!
french approved.

on the pricier note, but worth it.

Nice ambience, service is good. Food is good  but not surprising. Recommended the pork jowl, well cook, very soft, moist and tasty. Angel hair pasta texture is very good except the truffle oil fragrance overpower the pasta.
Roasted gambas also recommended. We are eating course meal, I am not super impressed overall, maybe the ala carte menu might be better.
Delicious food and excellent service. We had the angel hair pasta and Alaskan king crab legs and they were cooked to perfection. Highly recommend!

Love the angel hair pasta with caviar! I literally licked the plate!!! So good. The Apple “tart” is really good, so crispy and top a little ice cream on each bite sent me to heaven. It’s worth the price, the whole experience is exquisite and I was there for lunch. I have to go for a dinner next chance I am back in Singapore.

adr_address: 7 Raffles Blvd, Singapore 039595
name: Hai Tien Lo

reviews.text:
4-4.5 stars with the set dinner.
Fine dining with great service. Food wise some hits some misses.
Ingredients are fresh but perhaps should not have wasted the fresh lobsters by deep frying it. Fish was quite meh. Dessert was innovative with pop corn. But could have put in more effort to come up with a more interesting dessert.
Personally I like the first dish. Duck was very fragrant n the salted egg dish was good. Soup is full of ingredients n tasty too.

Had a business dinner with multiple courses and lohei. The food served is generally good with since unique dishes that’s yummy and healthy. Ingredients are fresh and portions served are pretty reasonable, just can’t justify the quality / taste of food to match the premium price charged here, hence I can’t give the perfect stars here. Service is excellent with the staff being proactive and professional. Atmosphere is top class and a perfect place and setting for business meals.

Visited this restaurant for our birthday celebration.
As we had dined here before, the food, as usual, has never fail to impress.
We enjoyed the dishes we ordered though the presentation could be better.
The service provided by Kelvin and Lee Mee were great. Many thanks to both.

They have a huge variety of food and the portions seem bigger than other places. However the food quality is quite average, seems to be catered to older crowd as most of the customers I saw were older age group.

Their service is very average as well. Similar restaurants in malls, which is quite bad considering this is in a hotel

Would rate this a 3 star but bring it to 2 to normalize

Their dim sums were mostly a miss except the siew mai, they were quite good.

Deep fried seafood with vermicelli - was normal, could get it anywhere else

Puff with chilli crab meat - chilli crab spice is a little overpowering

Steam scallops dumplings with spinach - dumpling skin was stuck to the paper, taste wise is normal

Siew mai - interesting twist with quail egg and you do not taste the dry yolk that usually comes with quail egg. Can try this even for people who don’t like quail egg.

Char siew bun - can give this a miss, the pork is quite average and bun is mushy

Duck were fresh and very soft and tender. However their wraps are a little too thick and have too much moisture that caused the duck skin to not be crispy anymore.

Suckling pig skin’s crispiness is on point but is a little too porky

The double boiled chicken soup has an interesting taste since it’s cooked with coconut water but the seafood they use here don’t taste fresh and their abalone is quite chewy. Not worth the price at all.

Food quality was generally excellent: presentation; taste; and colours. Only gripe was that one stall of mushroom tasted sourish (quality control).

Service speed and attentiveness were excellent.

First lo-hei for the year of the dragon 🐉

adr_address: 8A Marina Blvd, #01-03 Ground Plaza, Singapore 018984
name: Harry's Marina Bay Link Mall

reviews.text:
Chill ambiance. Variety of wine and beer options. Same goes with finger food. The blue cocktail is really nice and I love it. The food is so so. Chicken wings, pizza is okay. The Spicy prawn pasta is good.

The staff are friendly and nice. They will respond to you swiftly when you called them. Expecting peak hours the service might be slow. We have been waiting for around 30 mins for a drink to be served but I can understand because all tables are full.

Overall it's still a nice place to chill with your colleagues after office hours if you're working nearby.

It's better to reserve a table to avoid disappointment as It's always crowded. So many  white collar are hanging around as the restaurant is just at MBFC

Seems like a really popular place to hang out for the after work crowd in the area. Even on a Monday night, it was pretty full. Pretty chill place to catch up with friends with a wide menu of drinks and pub grub. Prices commensurate with the quality of food in the CBD area.

Food is delicious
Service also good
Although peak hours still service was prompt
Every dish in the menu is very tasty
Staff is good n prompt in their service n response
Available both vegetarians and non vegetarian

Chicken tikka masala is sweetish… that is not acceptable
Over all good

Fantastic food with superb ambience. The food were delicious and tasty. The staffs were friendly, helpful, courteous and attentive. A big thumbs up to the staffs there for making us feel so welcoming and enjoyed our meals. Highly recommended!
Great chill-out place to enjoy a meal and drinks. Beautiful surroundings to soak in the scenery.

adr_address: 77 Amoy St, Singapore 069896
name: Hashida Singapore

reviews.text: The Omakase Lunch prepared by Kazu-san [our chef] (I hope I got his name correctly) using Hashida-san recipes was marvelous. We felt the total experience unique. The seafood is fresh and his method of preparation and the application of the sauce enhanced the freshness and taste of the seafood. The chefs were also engaging and continue to engage us in conversation which was something unique among the Omakase restaurants we went to. All the all, it was a great experience.

Hashida Singapore @hashida.sg introduces the innovative Abura Kappo @hashida.abura restaurant-in-restaurant concept helmed by chef Kenjiro “Hatch” Hashida. Abura Kappo Vol. 1 presents a menu priced at $200++ per diner, featuring a series of 13 bites that reveal a fusion of global inspirations interpreted through a creative Japanese lens.

The 13-course menu commences with the Monaka, presenting crisp wafers enclosing creamy egg custard. Following is the Lamb x Squid, featuring raw lamb and squid accentuated by Hashida’s gin salt. Cheese oozes from the textural marvel of Camembert. Setting the stage for the Japanese bluefin Tuna Consommé, served chilled in a wineglass. The Managatsuo offers a golden crunch, transitioning to sweet, soft silver pomfret. Ebi Toast showcases angel shrimp paste atop spongy, house-made tamagoyaki. A twist on Tebagyoza follows, featuring crisp deboned chicken wing stuffed with glutinous rice and egg. Wagyu Beef Tempura, adorned with a drizzle of tart balsamic and pomegranate sauce, marks the next course. A refreshing interlude ensues with the Duck Salad, where tender duck breast meets the vibrance of pickled turnip and persimmon. Soft Soba Taco features a house-made soft buckwheat tortilla, while Oden Tempura follows, recalling a Japanese classic with radish and tomato stewed in dashi, deep-fried to perfection. The Donabe offers an entertaining finale, DIY maki begins with Nanatsuboshi short grain rice and fresh seafood, served with three toppings and roasted seaweed: Spicy Tuna with golden tempura crumbs, Prawn Tempura with tempura sauce, and an assortment of julienned radish, shiitake mushroom, spinach, and burdock root resembling Korean Kimbap. Dessert is a two-part curiosity: shavings of shiitake mushroom-infused chocolate paired with house-made vanilla ice cream, alongside a slice of dried persimmon accompanied by rich, earthy house-made matcha ice cream

Location: Abura Kappo, 77 Amoy Street, Singapore 069896
It was very delicious. I was able to have a good time thanks to your careful consideration. I was so happy that they even gave me decorations. I especially like the scent of sake.

We had an exceptional experience that far exceeded our expectations. The quality and freshness of the ingredients were top-notch, and the service and interaction with the chef were outstanding. The level of care, attention to detail, and hospitality extended to us made it feel like a 7-star service. Our iced Ocha was constantly refreshed, and the waiter ensured that any food stains on the table were promptly wiped away, leaving us with an impeccable dining experience.

The staff's ability to fluently explain the dishes and their ingredients in both Japanese and English was impressive. Their genuine teamwork, commitment, and passion were palpable throughout the entire experience. The food itself was undoubtedly top-tier, with the uni spring rolls being a standout. The combination of the warm spring roll with the cold, flavorful uni was truly mind-blowing.

We were celebrating a birthday, and the staff went above and beyond by singing the birthday song and taking a Polaroid picture of us. The chef even took the time to write a personalized birthday card in both Japanese and English. It was evident that the chef not only possesses exceptional culinary skills but also exudes a warm and personable demeanor.

We also appreciated the special birthday dessert plate, which added a thoughtful touch to our celebration. We are truly grateful to the entire team for making our experience unforgettable and look forward to returning in the future. Thank you for the excellent service, and we hope to see you again soon.

This was one of the best food experiences in my life. The chefs here are extremely talented, transporting me back to Japan. They fly in fresh fish from Japan & you can really taste the difference. They have a great selection of sake too. Very intimate dining experience with only room for 8 guests, where you get front row to watching the chefs create each dish. The staff are very attentive too. Thank you for taking me on an incredible food journey.

address_components.short_name: voco Orchard Singapore, an IHG Hotel

editorial_summary.overview: Intimate, special-occasion destination showcasing artful, Modern European cuisine & choice wines.

formatted_address: 581 Orchard Rd, Level 3 voco Orchard Singapore, an IHG Hotel, Singapore 238883
name: Iggy's

reviews.text: We had a wine dinner at Iggy’s. The service staff was spot on, considering the many wines to be paired with the food. The food was excellent and the chef obviously calibrated his dishes to match the wines. How considerate of the chef. Thank you Iggy’s team for making our dining experience a truly memorable one. 💕

Food here is consistently top notch, considered, well balanced and delightful! Incredible quality of ingredients to create classic contemporary dishes. Regulars and will continue to be. As it was my birthday, I even got an extra surprise course of birthday noodles which was very hearty.

Lovely experience.  Good service and attentive staff. Well deserved Michelin star with the food. Has fantastic courses paired with champagne. Air- conditioning is way too cold and freezes everyone. Any warm dish turns cold too quickly. Dessert was also a star and did not let down the entire course of dinner. Felt the staff could have been more confident in introducing each course.

Came here to celebrate our anniversary, a surprise dinner planned by my husband for us. The restaurant is intimate with only a few tables available, so you get undivided attention from the staff. It is also an open kitchen concept which I love so you can see the chefs hard at working preparing their masterpieces for us. I enjoyed pretty much every single dish, the abalone wellington was definitely unique and one of a kind. Overall had a really good experience here.

One - starred Michelin restaurant located within Voco Hotel (previously known as Hilton Orchard), serving Modern-Contemporary cuisine,established by Restaurateur-Sommelier Ignatius Chan in 2004. There is heavy influence of japanese ingredients used in the menu and served in the European way. Opt for the menu with two main courses for a wholesome dining experience. Food presentation is beautiful and tastefully presented, and what's good to look at is also good to eat.

vicinity: 581 Orchard Road, Level 3 voco Orchard Singapore, an IHG Hotel

adr_address: 2 Stamford Rd, Level 70, Singapore 178882

editorial_summary.overview: Modern, 40-seat European-British restaurant with sweeping city views offering seasonal ingredients.

name: JAAN By Kirk Westaway

reviews.text: Prepare to budget at least $SGD1,000 for the set menu for two (more if you include wine). Despite the restaurant boasting 2 Michelin stars, our high expectations weren't fully met. The flavors seemed overly complex, diminishing the originality of Great British Contemporary cuisine. For instance, the fish and chip starter lacked a distinct fish taste, and the blue lobster was enjoyable, but the pasta had an unexpected tom yum flavor. The guinea fowl resembled roast pork more than a game bird. Dessert lacked excitement, being uniformly sweet. On the positive side, the service was impeccable, and the staff displayed utmost professionalism. The atmosphere was fantastic, complemented by a stunning view. Would I return? Probably not.

Initially having nestled in the heart of the restaurant, I found myself placed away from the scenic views outside. Despite this, the central location provided convenient accessibility to the impeccable service led by Giuseppe and his team. Their engaging demeanor and active participation in our conversation transformed the dining experience into a memorable and enjoyable affair, compensating for the absence of an external view. The attentiveness and warmth of the team truly made the overall atmosphere delightful, turning what could have been a minor setback into a positive aspect of the day.

Amazing experience! Every single dish was executed so flawlessly.. the intensity and the layering of the textures as well as the flavours. I took the vegetarian set while my partner took the regular set.. I cleaned out each dish to the last drop! Definitely will go back when the menu changes. Thank you for the wonderful meal!

The best Michelin restaurant in Singapore we have been to thus far!

Every dish was divine and designed to perfection. It was so flavorful and delicately presented.

And to top it off, we had the best service from our dedicated restaurant executive, Kim, who's so warm and welcoming while he explains every dish in detail with passion. Thank you so much, Kim, for making our dining experience extra special!

We will definitely be back again.

My first 2 Michelin stars dining experience in Singapore

Food: 3 stars
1) food lack varied texture
2) All your dessert has 1 flavour, sweet. Can do better with different flavours…
3) brioche is dry

Service: 4 stars -  was awesome thorough-out the sitting except during the start, I was asked, “What would you like to order?” 😂 I was slightly taken aback when our server said that.

Atmosphere: 4 stars - the aerial view is unbeatable. Just that it’s a city view.

Hopefully odette lives up to its stars better

adr_address: The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands, 2 Bayfront Ave, B1- 01B, Singapore 018972
formatted_address: The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands, 2 Bayfront Ave, B1- 01B, Singapore 018972
name: JUMBO Signatures

reviews.text:
We were served by Amy Mac, She was very friendly, informative and lovely. We were given welcome complimentary and a small refreshment when we finished with our foods.
We ordered coral red steam minced garlic fish, mud crab singapore chili and scallop fried rice. Everything was very delicious and unforgettable!
A highly recommend when you are in Marina Bay Sands.

Celebrated my friend's birthday here, and it was a great experience.

The restaurant is located in the MBS and the environment is very good. The service in the restaurant is also very good.

Tried a few signature dishes, and my favorite is scallop wrapped in yam ring. And the fried mini buns make the crab even more delicious🦀️

This is the second visit.
Thanks to Amy Mac, one of employees, my mom and I had a really great time.
She not only kindly served the whole meal and explained the features of each but also offered us sharing dishes, too.
Food and atmosphere is good, too.
I plan to visit this place next travel.

Everything that we ordered was goooooood. My faves: seafood quinoa fried rice and salted egg lobster. The individual serving of the deshelled prawn in cereal made sense as appetizer. The staff was super welcoming, we went for iftar, and despite the timing was in between their 2 seatings, they accommodated us. The private room had a minimum spend of 1.5K, we got that for free, well we did spend more though, and totally worth it. Jumbo's finest treat to date!

My visit to this fine dining restaurant was truly delightful. Despite having other branches, I didn’t regret choosing this one. The cozy and quiet atmosphere, coupled with attentive and well-mannered staff, set the perfect tone. I indulged in serveral starters, a soup, 4 mains with a dessert, and words can’t capture the exceptional flavors. The signature Huss-free chilli crab is a heavenly delight for those avoiding a messy experience, and the pork chop stands out with its remarkable juiciness and tenderness. A must-visit for an unforgettable dining experience.

vicinity: The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands, 2 Bayfront Avenue, B1- 01B

adr_address: 190 Orchard Blvd, Singapore 248646
name: Jiang-Nan Chun

reviews.text: Amazing and most delicious Chinese new year celebration meal. Everything I tried was amazing. And the service team were amazing too. Kudos to the staff that made it such an enjoyable experience.

Braised pork belly was my favourite, other dishes are delicious but not worth the price paid, specially went for the sweet and sour pork which some articles claim is the best in Singapore. I think for $42++ I expected something more special, overall the ambience was really good and exceptional services. The Peking Duck, was served with caviar (something special), however we topped an additional $20 to request the duck meat to be cooked as Gongbao Chilli Duck but somehow the meat was reduced by a lot hmmm… all in all it was a good experience just not so value for money.

One of the best Peking ducks ever! Please note that all other dishes, despite the high price, are portions for one pax only.

Very expensive but worth the Michelin star!

We originally came for peeking duck, but the waitress advised us that it would be too much food for the two of us, which I appreciated! We got one of the chefs menus instead. My favorite was the chili prawns and my least favorite was the fried rice, it just wasn't anything special compared to the other dishes.

Service was great and they even set up a kids place setting for our baby, which was sweet, even though he is much too young for solid foods.

The food was mediocre at best, but the service was good. We made a reservation for seven beforehand, yet the table we were assigned was extremely small, could not even fit the dishes we ordered.

Compared to other Chinese restaurants in this price bracket, such as those at the Ritz Carlton and Hilton, this dining experience left much to be desired.

BBQ Meat Combination 2/5
Steamed Star Groupa 2.5/5
Peking Duck 3/5
Sweet and Sour Pork 4/5
Stir fried Kai Lan 1/5

adr_address: 2 Bayfront Ave, # B1 - 67, Singapore 018972

editorial_summary.overview: Upscale Japanese restaurant & sushi bar serving gourmet food, cocktails & sake amid dramatic decor.

name: KOMA Singapore

reviews.text: I thoroughly enjoyed my dining experience at this restaurant. The tempura starter, particularly the sweet potato, was delightful. While my main dish leaned towards the salty side, it complemented well with rice. The bonsai dessert, perfect for chocolate enthusiasts, though slightly sweeter than I prefer, was still enjoyable. I look forward to returning to sample more dishes and perhaps indulge in their cocktails on my next visit.

Visited for dinner.

To be very frank, I was pretty disappointed with the meals considering KOMA being highly rated place and the price of each dish.

I would say this place is more of an experience type of place rather than here for the food type of place.

Staff are very friendly and helpful.
Ambience is nice with the iconic bridge and bell.

The food is nice but not what I’d expect.

As a solo traveler, sometimes it's hard to get a table for one. No such problem here! Not only did they seat me like a regular group, they were also very attentive and even stopped for conversation.
The food is phenomenal, with fresh fish and delicate flavors.  I savored every bite.
The Bonsai dessert quite easily tops the charts in the best dessert I have ever had.

Have walked past the restaurant many times and have always been wanting to take a picture at the “Tori gates”.

Finally managed to get a booking and woah, the place was absolutely mind-blowing! Service was good, food was great as well. I requested for counter seats, as I personally felt that the view of the chef and the bridge and restaurant was great!

I really like the desserts, the sushi, and everything served. Definitely not the cheapest but you are paying for great service, food and ambience. Wonderful date venue.

I will be back.

Beautiful restaurant and nice wait staff. I wanted a surprise dessert at the last minute to celebrate my daughter’s birthday and they managed this without any hassle. As it was during the Chinese New Year period we ordered the festive set menu which was very presented. Everything was fantastic and I highly recommend this place. Will come again for sure!

adr_address: 70, #02-02 Collyer Quay, Customs House, Singapore 049323

editorial_summary.overview: Dimly- it contemporary eatery offering cooked Japanese dishes & sushi alongside sake & cocktails.

name: Kinki Restaurant + Bar

reviews.text: Service by Prem was top notched. Professional, courteous who went above and beyond to ensure my wife and I had a great evening. He even gave a complimentary cake and shots for my wife’s birthday. Food and ambience were excellent and we were even given a nice view of MBS.

The food overall was really good, we had the foie gras chawanmushi, unagi claypot and the Cowabanga. All three items were really good and would definitely recommend. We also ordered cocktails, Calpis Colada and the Purple Light. But we were most impressed with the service given by Prem, he service was really good and we had a pleasant time here for a birthday dinner.

We were served by Vickie. He was very attentive and friendly. My girls and I enjoyed ourselves there. We had the Yusheng and it was splendid! The rest of the food was fine no complaints. My only gripe with this place is that there’s no shelter so we had to brave the rain to get to the restaurant.

Excellent food, exemplary service, great view!

My wife and I had the window seat as it was our wedding anniversary and the experience did not disappoint. Pricey but totally worth it...

Unagi claypot was not bad, just not enough burnt rice bits lol.
The ninja sushi and sashimi set had samples of the popular dishes, recommended to try.
The AC DC dynamite is also worth a try.

Will try the rooftop for better view next time.

amazing vibes!! awesome view, good for photos! very kind and accomodating customer service by Lovely :) great food and pretty good range of drinks available, cheaper esp at happy hour! went twice and would go again if we come back to Singapore ❤️

adr_address: Keong Saik Rd., 4, Singapore 089110
name: Kok Sen Restaurant

reviews.text: Visited just after they opened for dinner service on 28 March. The restaurant, having been awarded many Michelin Bib Gourmands between 2016 and 2023, does not disappoint on the food and quality of service. The restaurant was rather on the small side, with the seating area inside filling up around half an hour into dinner service. The staff were very professional and food is very good, would recommend trying the salted egg dish (if you like salted egg) or go with the noodles. Not much in terms of drinks though...

one of the best zichar meals i ever had!! each dish was executed perfectly and v tasty. the moonlight horfun was a definite highlight. prices are affordable and comparable to the neighbourhood zichar places. although crowded during weekend dinner time, we got a table quickly and service was fast too. will definitely recommend to eat here if you are in the area.

I really liked the newly renovated place compared to the old coffee shop. The service was good, though nothing much to talk about.

If you're there to surf the net, do connect to the WiFi provided. The network is bad in the restaurant.

I was not the most impressed by the food. The recommended dragon chicken dish looked like it was skinned alive with only the wings left with the real chicken meat. The rest of the body felt like some form of tofu or fish cake texture. If you like it but want a meat dish, do order another. The clay pot tofu was so-so and ok for the spicy prawn horfun. The consolation was the prawns as they were pretty good quality.

Worth visiting, I was there about 5:30pm. No queue but the place already packed. The service was great, friendly & helpful! Food was delicious & portions are quite big. No for dates, as the seating is a bit squeeze to accommodate more diners. Wide variety of food available.

Last year’s dinner for Winter Solstice. Food was just above average. Seems quite overrated considering they have a Bib Gourmand. The signature dish Golden Dragon chicken is a dish I order pretty frequently as I love it but the version here is pretty mediocre. The best tasting dish has to be the prawn Hor fun. We arrived pretty early for dinner and the place was pretty packed so they must be doing something right. *shrugs*

adr_address: 76-78 Serangoon Rd, Singapore 217981

editorial_summary.overview: No-frills eatery serving Indian vegetarian classics like dosa (crispy stuffed crepes) since 1947.

name: Komala Vilas Restaurant, Singapore

reviews.text: One of old & best South Indian restaurants at little India.In Singapore the best dosa İdil poori all are here. PM Modi & lots of other celebrities visited this restaurant. The prices are reasonable.The staff service are good

First time trying Southern Indian food - didn’t disappoint! Loved the sides of chickpea curry and tomato chutney, and the palak paneer and veg jalfrezi were so rich 😋 And the poori!! Was yum on its own, and great for sopping up the sauces.

Am a bit basic so I had to get their naan… and no complaints - was just the right amount of chewy and thick without being tough!

Got stuffed, and only paid $13.15 per pax. Will be back!!

This place truly never disappoints! It’s one of my favorite spots in Singapore, I especially love it for late breakfast/early lunch. No wonder there’s a line so often!! But don’t worry, the line moves super quickly and it’s so worth it. My favorite thing is the ghee masala dosa and chapati plate- the raita in that one is so different than any other I’ve tried but it’s so good! Their cauliflower side dish was also delicious. I would also highly recommend to get a lime juice with your meal and to try their coffee after. You can also feel that they don’t add too much oil as even though it’s filling, it’s still quite light. A must visit in Little India.

Famous South Indian vegetarian restaurant that serves up delicious dosai and rice meals at decent prices. They’ve been around since 1947. We enjoyed the mysore masala dosai and Rawa dosai, and three types of curries and chutney/sambar come with it. Side dishes were butter paneer and Manchurian Gobi, both absolutely yummy! For dessert, we tried rasmalai, a cheese pudding in sweet saffron infused milk. Plus Masala tea to wrap up dinner is a must, with its spice flavours, its good aid for digestion. We will be back!

Food here is good, not that very bad. Service got to improve. Environment can be cramped and noisy. Pricey but still okay, you pay what you asked for. I was served food first, even finished up eating the foods but drinks were served after 5-10 after finishing up my meals. Masala tea arrived 30-40 minutes late upon ordering. This is not acceptable at all. And never even apologized for serving the drinks late. I ordered one ice tea and one masala tea. Also, I personally feel the standard of the food have dropped a lot. Used to patronize here often but I think it's about time that the service and food taste is falling apart.
Overall food is 7.5/10.
Service is 3/10.
Environment is 4.5/10.
This review is based on my honest opinion.

adr_address: 10 Bayfront Ave, Tower 1, Level 57, Singapore 018956

editorial_summary.overview: Hearty Italian dishes served in a relaxed restaurant with warm decor, plus sunset & city views.

name: LAVO Italian Restaurant And Rooftop Bar

reviews.text: This is a must do if you are in Singapore. This bar is located on top of Marina Bay Sands hotel and provides breathtaking views of the city all around. They have good food selection and staff is extremely friendly and helpful. Make sure to book a reservation otherwise you may have to wait for upto 30 minutes on the day. Make sure to ask for a table outdoors to enjoy the views. 20 layers chocolate cake is great but make sure you have four people to finish it off as it's huge.

Such an amazing experience! This was one of my favorite nights in Singapore. The bar area is beautiful and all of the staff are so nice. We tried a few drinks and they were all great. We didn’t have any food, but the food we saw others order looked nice. There’s great views of the city on both sides. Make sure to make a reservation if you’re wanting to book a table that’s outside!

The best time to visit would be during the golden hours. You can sip your favorite cocktail and enjoy the stunning views of the Singapore skyline. It offers the best aerial view of the skyline, but the food can be a bit overpriced. It's probably best to go for cocktails instead.

The restaurant has is just amazing view. The whole city is visible from here. We had drinks and fries here. Fries are full bowl and it is enough for two people.
The staff is prompt and polite. She help us for taking photos also and suggested us some drinks was nice

Ambience and service are top-notch. Came here for lunch, and we ordered the set meals. They have a two course meal (appetizer and mains) and a three course  meal (appetizer, mains, and dessert). The food was just okay, I wasn’t blown away because there's no innovation going on. However, they used fresh ingredients, and it was flavourful.

Service was amazing. The staff was attentive, polite, and prompt. They even helped to take our pictures.

I'll probably come back but I won't order the set meals again. Maybe their other dishes are better.

adr_address: 333A Orchard Rd, #04 - 01 / 31, Singapore 238897

editorial_summary.overview: Outpost of a classic beef & seafood fine-dining chain with tableside carving in a formal setting.

name: Lawry's The Prime Rib Singapore

reviews.text: My husband and I had an amazing experience dining here. We celebrated our wedding anniversary. We were greeted warmly and great service from all the staff. We had lobster bisque and lobster tail for our starters and they were good. We enjoyed the prime rib as well. Two thumbs up! They also gave us a complimentary cake for our celebration. We were surprised that they also gave us a memorable photo of the two of us with our baby daughter. It was really special. We would definitely be back again.

Decided to visit Lawry’s after being recommended by friends and family.

Decoration and atmosphere gives the retro vibes, and that’s not a bad thing. Service staff were all friendly and attentive.

Ordered their famous prime rib, having a “Lawry’s cut” myself which is 285g of prime rib, along with a side of mashed potato, Yorkshire pudding and the famous spinning bowl salad. Topped up an additional serving of creamed spinach.

The prime rib is definitely worth it, meat was so tender, juicy and flavourful, which is one of the best prime rib I ever had.

Definitely worth visiting this place at least once.

Absolutely fantastic- every restaurant needs to take a leaf from Lawry’s. From the start to finish we were doted on like royalty- my father is a man of few words and high standards, but he was sure to say “the service is impeccable”. Fantastic place for birthdays. Exceedingly well taken care of by all of the staff but with a special thanks to Mr Shiva and his team.

Went for Valentines’ day dinner, but I’m very disappointed with the service.
A rose was given to every couple when we entered the restaurant, which was a very nice gesture on this special day, but mine was missed out.
Upon sitting down we were handed our menu and after that everything wasn’t very attentive. The tea light on my table was extinguish. Bread rolls and the comply drink wasn’t served until we asked for them.
We were almost served appitizers twice and palate cleanser was almost serve trice. The platting of the food was also not too appetising.
Service was slow and the food was only average. Was pretty disappointed with the service and food considering the price we paid.
This was our 4th visit and one of the worst.

Reliable international chain for prime rib (I had the 300g Lawry’s cut) and their famous spinning bowl salad (who doesn’t like a bit of drama and flair with their lunch service?). Meat is cut table-side from a silver trolley, and all (lovely and friendly) staff are dressed in slightly OTT anachronistic old-fashioned uniforms. You will leave feeling like a towkay (which depending on your perspective might be a good or bad thing).

adr_address: 5 Cox Terrace, Level 2 Fort Canning Arts Centre, Singapore 179620
formatted_address: 5 Cox Terrace, Level 2 Fort Canning Arts Centre, Singapore 179620
name: Le Jardin Restaurant

reviews.text: The online decor and ambiance of this restaurant looked so appealing that I decided to pay it a visit. However, the reality was far from what I expected. The actual environment was disappointing, and the food was even more so. The salted egg pasta lacked any discernible salted egg flavor, and the burger was just average. Considering the high prices, the quality of the food simply did not match up. It was so disappointing that I didn't even want to order any beverage. This experience has left me with no desire to return.

Super beautiful garden themed place, very vintage style as well, there were vintage dressers, and the table top was glass and underneath the glass was some sort garden/terrarium thingy.
Even the toilet was beautifully decorated with flowers LOL.

Menu was extremely limited though, I would come in again for a drink and tea maybe, but not for the mains. Thought it was supposed to be a french restaurant, but was hardly authentic. We got the chilli crab pasta (meh), rainbow trout (super small in portion), and moist chicken with glutinous rice (quite unique but highly divided).

Maybe a nice date place but would say avoid the mains.

I would rate this place 3.5 based on food quality vs cost. But otherwise, the location, decor and service staff are excellent. The venue is great for special occasions. Food and taste quality require a lot of improvement if price needs to be maintained.

Very pleasant spot in the middle of the Botanic Gardens. They lean in (heavily) on the floral theme, but that does help remind you of how special the location is. We had a very nice brunch, although I did get the impression that we were earlier than they were expecting (11am) and the wait staff, while perfectly pleasant, did seem to be frantically preparing for people who'd arrive later. That was ok though - the food was very nice and coffee/drinks were solid too.

Great ambience in the cafe with decor and quiet music not interfering with conversation. Went on a day pouring with rain and it can be difficult to get there because it is not connected to the main building via an internal corridor. Also have to walk a long way from the carpark or public transport which can be a great thing.

Very quiet that day but good for long chats then. Food was pretty good but a bit hit and miss with the chicken for the glutinous rice entrees being quite chewy. Truffle fries were good though.

vicinity: 5 Cox Terrace, Level 2 Fort Canning Arts Centre

adr_address: 1 Scotts Rd, #01 - 16 Shaw Centre, Singapore 228208

editorial_summary.overview: Refined, chandelier-lit destination featuring upscale French cuisine & a vast wine selection.

name: Les Amis

reviews.text:
Les Amis: A Michelin Star Dining Experience

Les Amis is a fine-dining French restaurant located in Singapore that has been awarded three Michelin stars. The restaurant is known for its use of fresh, seasonal ingredients, and its classic French dishes with a modern twist.

The interior of the restaurant is elegant and sophisticated, with white tablecloths, chandeliers, and plush seating. The service is impeccable, with the waitstaff being attentive and knowledgeable about the menu.

The menu at Les Amis changes seasonally, but always features a variety of seafood, meat, and vegetarian dishes. There is also a tasting menu available, which allows diners to sample a variety of the chef's creations.

Overall, Les Amis is a dining experience that is sure to impress. The food is excellent, the service is impeccable, and the atmosphere is elegant and sophisticated. If you are looking for a special dining experience in Singapore, Les Amis is definitely worth a try.

Good experience to celebrate our anniversary at a 3⭐️ Michelin restaurant. Great service with good food and wine.

With my limited exposure to French cuisine, I might not have fully appreciated the taste. But I really enjoyed the overall experience there.

A memorable night.

Celebrated my birthday at Les Amis with family, and it was phenomenal! The upscale ambiance and impeccable service set the stage for a memorable evening. Each dish was a masterpiece, showcasing culinary expertise. From appetizers to desserts, a gastronomic delight that made my special day truly exceptional. Highly recommend!

The food and wine pairing was excellent. A true gastronomic experience. Everything that we sampled was fantastic. Service was impeccable - special mention to Patrick for making it a better night for us.

Les Amis restaurant is a gastronomic wonderland that transported me to a world of culinary bliss! The ambiance felt like a page out of a Parisian romance novel, with soft lights and a melody of enchanting tunes. The menu, a poetic composition of flavors, offered a dance of taste that left me in awe. The waitstaff, dressed in elegant attire, choreographed a dining experience that was nothing short of a culinary ballet. Each dish, a masterpiece plated with precision, tasted like a symphony of harmonious ingredients. If you're yearning for a dining escapade that feels like a rendezvous with gourmet dreams, Les Amis is the destination to indulge your palate in a poetic feast!

adr_address: #25-01 One Raffles Quay, Singapore 048583
name: Liberty Insurance Pte Ltd (Singapore)

reviews.text:
My insurance claim was attended quickly and promptly than i expected to be. Also
i learnt they are service oriented rather than finding ways to
Exclude some aspects to reduce the claim amount.  They scrutinize the pros and
Cons of the claim and try to settle the claim quickly for their customers.

If Google review allowed 0 star, I would have given negative 1 star. Liberty pet insurance is fast to collect premium but very slow to process claims. Even though their process say 10 working days, they took almost 2 months to come back to me. After almost 2 months, they find all sorts of reasons to reject my claim by claiming skin condition. I strongly discourage anybody to purchase liberty insurance. Very bad and slow customer service from claims department. Wasted 2 years of premiums of being liberty insurance customers. Better avoid this insurer at all costs!!!

I had bought numerous travel insurance with different companies before but Liberty is the most ridiculous and worst!  Claims officer trying to make things difficult. Each time trying to come up with new excuse to deny claim. Discharge summary, GP referral letter, medicals bills, travel agency letter still not enough! Still need medical records or memo from doctors! These are additional costs. Claims processes difficult and suck! Extremely disappointed and angry with them! If there is a negative star rating I would definitely rate Liberty.

Upon purchase of the comprehensive car insurance, I was told that the age for young and inexperienced driver is 24 or less. However when I made the claim for my car accident I was told that I have to pay an extra $2500 excess for young and inexperienced driver as the age is apparently 27 now. There is no such clause stating the age under my policy fineprint.

Avoid at all cost.

The worst service ever! No response at all after knowing I'm entitled to an additional discount from BMW for my insurance renewal. Never keep promises after chasing for the answer. Worst if I continue insured with such scammer!

adr_address: 5 Straits View, #B2, #34 The Heart, Marina One, Singapore 018935
formatted_address: 5 Straits View, #B2, #34 The Heart, Marina One, Singapore 018935
name: Little Bowl Singapore

reviews.text: [Feb 2024] One of the few eateries that open past 8pm at Marina One. Service is friendly, mentaiko salmon was visually pleasing and cooked to perfection. Price is also slightly more affordable than many Japanese casual eateries. Highly recommended 👍

Ordered the Shio Pasta on their recommendation. The dish came with a mushroom soup-like sauce that was slightly salty and not very creamy. Didn’t really like that.

The spaghetti was tossed in some oil that I can’t quite figure out, but it’s plated well. This too, was salty. Quite mixed, but not a fan of it but can see how some could like it.

The chicken was the highlight, fried well, super crispy breading and a hint of spice. This let them eke out a 7/10 considering the price of the location.

It may not be my cup of tea but I think if you’re willing to try it, or like salty things, you could give it a shot.
Had a small gathering here today. Food was simple and great! Dont belittle the unseemingly portion, it is quite filling. Had our first yusheng of the year here as well.

One of the more affordable options in the area. Food is okay, but the service by aunty is good. We had the mentaiko salmon and smoked duck bowl and it was average. Good to pop by if you’re looking to settle your lunch quickly.
The pasta is delicious with tasty fried chicken. Portion is big too. The female staff is friendly. Pork Belly Don is well done.

vicinity: 5 Straits View, #B2, #34 The Heart, Marina One

adr_address: 22 Ann Siang Rd, Singapore 069702
name: Lolla

reviews.text:
Lolla offers an exquisite tasting menu that caters predominantly to seafood lovers. The option to choose between crab or uni as one of the main dishes is a delightful dilemma, highlighting the quality and variety on offer.

Each dish we tried was nothing short of delectable, demonstrating a high standard of culinary expertise and fresh ingredients. The flavors were well-balanced, showcasing a sophisticated approach to seafood that’s both innovative and deeply satisfying.

The service at Lolla was exceptional. The staff were not only friendly but also knowledgeable, making them great conversationalists and guides through the tasting menu. Their recommendations were spot-on, adding an extra layer of enjoyment to our dining experience.

The ambiance of Lolla adds significantly to its charm. It’s friendly and intimate, creating a perfect setting for a memorable meal, whether it’s a special occasion or a casual night out.

In summary, Lolla is a stellar choice for anyone looking to indulge in a seafood-centric tasting menu. With its delightful dishes, outstanding service, and cozy atmosphere, it’s a dining experience that truly deserves a five-star rating.

Wow. What a great find in Singapore! They offer tasting menus on Fridays and Saturdays. Everything we ate was well-balanced, inventive and flavorful. The presentation of some of the dishes was also delivered by the head chef. I am also astonished by the level of service. Everyone was pleasantly attentive and not overbearing. This was one of the best restaurants we visited in Singapore and around the world.

Absolutely loved the food here. The sea urchin is terrific - we had the 1/2 portion with the pudding and it's more than enough as it's quite rich. The quail is a must order, so tender & juicy. Service is top notch. Although I will say that the cheesecake was just so so. Will definitely return soon. Easy to make reservations online

We had four course lunch on Saturday
1) Avocado, smoked eel consommé, yuzu
2) sourdough bread, kombu butter
3) Uni fideaua (additional order)
4) crab ‘Relleno’, aligue sauce, kaffir lime
5) caviar, hay ice cream, sesame oil

Wine - 2022 Domaine Masse Givry 1er Cru ‘Servoisine’ Rouge.

Non-alcoholic drink - Limonata (Made in Italy lemonade)

One of us ordered additional squid ink pasta (Uni fideaua).  In fact with the help of sourdough, 4 course is just nice for lunch.

No complaint on any of the dish.  Like the savoury taste of the kombu when it was spread on the sourdough.  Have finished the last drop of the aligue sauce with the remaining sourdough.  The mixture of the caviar and sesame oil with the hay ice cream was a surprising combination.

Went here for Valentine's Day with my wife and I unfortunately did not have the best time.

I completely understand why Lolla doesn't have a Michelin star. They are almost good enough in every category but fall flat in all of them. The food is hit and miss, the service could use polishing, the ambiance could be slightly improved.

The Good:

- Food was prepared with skill and presented well.
- The restaurant felt lively and romantic.
- My partner liked the sea urchin pudding. They said it was unlike anything they ever tasted.
- Everything tasted ok. Nothing was too memorable.

The Not-So-Good:

The decor was ok, I was seated in the basement of the restaurant where they have one really long table shared by multiple parties. To give people privacy they put a large amount of items all over the table and on the ceiling to create partitions. I appreciate the effort but it ended up making the table extremely cluttered and it was a tad difficult for me to see my partner at times.

If you're going to have a communal table lean into the concept and make it truly communal. This felt like they wanted privacy and a communal table but ended up getting a mediocre version of both.

The Bad:
- The portion to price ration was extremely small. In one of my pictures you can see the iberico ham. Those 6-10 thin shavings were more than I've ever paid for iberico ham. Not to mention they were stuck to this rock and it was difficult to remove them. I'm sure someone thought it will look modern if they stick it on a rock but ultimately I want to eat my food not struggle to scrape it off.

- The communal table has a bathroom located behind the middle of the table. It's not great for obvious reasons.

- The most egregious offender was the service. The lady waiter was extremely rude and unprofessional. I was told I had 2 hours to sit, ok I get it it's Valentine's Day, but this lady would not leave me and my partner alone. She kept coming to us every minute asking if we wanted anything. It's like she read a book called "How to be a waiter at a nice restaurant" and saw a chapter called "Be attentive" and she just took it too far. I felt like I was at a bazaar getting harassed to buy something NOW when all I wanted to do was talk to my partner and bask in their glow and the romance of the day.

adr_address: 22 Gemmill Ln, Singapore 069257
name: Luke's Oyster Bar & Chop House

reviews.text: Amazing food, oysters were perfect and corn bread was some of the best we've had. Service was spot on and welcoming.

If you’re not a steak person (I fall in this category) and expected to be blown away with the thought that their steak is amazing (because of the reviews and high price) prepare to be disappointed. This review is purely subjective as I am not a steak person hence this only applies to people like me.

1) Appetizer of Tuna Tartare was mediocre. I expected more flavor from the tuna. The bread that came with it was amazing though. Highlight of my meal.

2) Oysters were good. Don’t expect them to be the freshest. They did come from the USA 😅

3) Steak was a steak. Flavors were bold and rich; probably not for me.

4) Service was attentive. Ambience was top notch.

Was it worth the $200 bill? No. However this is purely subjective :)

Overall good food and love the portion. I will definitely be back! Only hope the clam chowder isn’t that water down and too much salt. Definitely recommend this place and reservation is highly recommend.

Amazing meal with great food and service. The corn bread at the start of the meal was served warm and it tastes really good! The oysters were fresh and plump but slightly too salty for my liking. The beef was really good and the restaurant portioned it out for us as 2 of us was sharing it. The clam chowder was slightly too thick but it tastes nice. Scallops were very well cooked and the coleslaw was crunchy and refreshing. Crab cakes were good too and I could taste the real crab meat in them. For sides, we got lobster mac& cheese and I liked that it came topped with biscuits which gave it an added crunch.

Absolutely loved this place. It's a nice intimate setting, and loved the 1930/40s music playing. The wait staff were attentive and the food was excellent. Would highly recommend if you want somewhere special to go

formatted_address: 390 Orchard Road, 01-03 Palais Renaissance, 390 Orchard Rd, #01 - 03 / 04, Singapore 238871
name: MERCI MARCEL ORCHARD

reviews.text: Let me just say I love love the bartender at Merci Marcel (got her permission to post her photo here). She is so sweet, so attentive and overall a fantastic host to me and my friend. Great drink and THE BEST CREME BRULEE I have ever eaten in my entire life. The bottom part is so creamy that I wanted to take a bath in it, and let's not even get me started on that caramelized sugar topping. It is taken to the very edge of being a perfect caramel. Food, drinks, service - this place GOT IT ALL.

A pretty place in the middle of busy town. We had reserved a slot for noon but we were running late, staff was cooperative on moving our slot. But when we reached we felt reservations not really required as walk-ins were allowed. So that’s a good thing.
Food wise we thought it was bit on pricey side. Portion of the food did not feel worthy of the money we were paying. May be it would be good if they make up with the portion as food was decently good. They have different menus for each day of the week, brunch, lunch, breakfast and so on.
We ordered French Ratatouille served along with bread which was actually delicious. Smoked Salmon burger wasn’t that great, can say okay. I had Spring in Paris which was a mocktail and was good. Cappuccino came with dark chocolate and was great choice.
I would like to come back and try more options, so Cheers :)

Very good food but note that they have a very limited menu during 4-6pm.
Ravioli was the star of the show, extra cheesey and creamy, very well done. French toast was delightful and perfectly done. Pannacotta was a tad sweet but still good. Overall a pleasant experience. Nice ambience too.

My first visit to Merci Marcel and my friends and I had a good time bonding over the food and the servers were great, especially Marilyn who was patient in giving us and overview of food selects and sharing the specials of the day. Soft yellow lighting gave it a nice cosy family/friends evening gathering atmosphere vibes. Thumbs up!

It was my first visit with my wife to Merci Marcel, we were delighted by the overall vibes of the restaurant. We ordered the eggs Ben and French Toast Brioche, latte and flat white. The food and coffee were excellent, the portion of eggs Ben was a bit small though. A great place to chill!!

formatted_address: 5 Straits View, #04-01 Marina One East Tower, Singapore 018935
name: Majestic Restaurant

reviews.text:
Had lunch at Majestic Restaurant on CNY Day 4.

Food was served fairly quick, all the dishes we ordered were tasty.

Service wise, most of the staff are quite average and not like the usual warm and friendly service in Chinese restaurants.

Since the price is a bit higher, this place is more for special occasion. If your wallet is fatter than average people, you can frequent this place.

Majestic Restaurant - the culinary pride of Chef Yong Bin Ngen. Always a joy to relish and revel in the Cantonese chinois food here, set in a unique location for a Chinese restaurant.

The airy dining suite is appointed under a glass roof overlooking a green scape. Every morsels of food here is the distillation of modern techniques with time-honoured traditions and is exquisite in both taste and appearance.

Notable dishes personally - dim sum items like har gows were luscious and succulent, char siew paus were tasty and fluffy, five spice pork belly roast was aromatic and juicy. Standouts - the shark bone collagen soup is a must order - extremely tasty and rich in velvety texture. The baby abalone mee sua was sublime and comforting.

Desserts were memorable - especially the durian fried ice cream was superb. Mango sago was also very refreshing.

Service could have been a little friendlier or more polished - expected as the benchmark for setting apart the good and the exceptional standard of a Chinese restaurant. Having said that, service was generally earnest and brisk without much hiccups. Just wish for it to be friendlier or more personable to leave a deeper impression - often the reason for revisits.

Overall, a good place for tasty Chinese dishes and worth a visit. Perfect for business lunches or milestone celebrations.

Tried the $98 set menu and it was amazing!! Really enjoyed every single dish, except the dessert which we felt was a little lacking. However, appreciate that they allowed us to top up to other dessert. We topped up one of our dessert to the almond puree at $4 and it was amazing! Quality of the food was worth the splurge! Staff was also attentive and courteous. Will definitely come here again to try other set menus!

I was looking to get some good Chinese food and remembered Chef Yong and his Majestic Restaurant.
Seeing that they were now housed in Marina One, I was even more curious to check it out as I had never been there.
Just to get the feel of things we had the trip of dim sums, kurobuta pork (as recommended in previous reviews), braised tofu and ended with 2 types of desserts.
The menu is quite extensive and as we were just two, we are hoping to try more of the dishes with more people when we come again soon.

Don't get the chance to take more pics of food but overall, the quality is quite good, consistent, and fresh.

I dislike the desserts here, I think we probably ordered 12 desserts and they didn't impress us.

The service of staff was good, they served and waited patiently when we dined slightly over their closing time

vicinity: 5 Straits View, #04-01 Marina One East Tower, Singapore

formatted_address: 80 Middle Road Level 2 InterContinental Singapore, Singapore 188966
name: Man Fu Yuan Restaurant

reviews.text: This spot is great for a casual dinner night out. The food and the atmosphere is awesome and the service is excellent. I wish to compliment the service from Rene, Jie Eein and Sam. They are very friendly and helpful. Additionally, Chef Shawn also came to our table to greet us during our dinner. The food that was prepared was fantastic  and certainly a pleasant dining experience.

We had their weekend dim sum buffet. The service and food were incredible. Shirley, Maggie and Chin Chin were amazing hosts, recommending dishes and ensuring that we were well taken care of.

Great place for your family dinners. I will definitely come again soon! :)

Thank you Moon, Xiao and & Sam for their impeccable service! My wife and I went during dinner service. We chose our own dishes, so it was kind of a hit and miss.
Pity we didn’t manage to try their pork belly dish; it was already sold out at 7pm. The Irish Duck was the highlight of the dinner! Will definitely have that again the next time. Deep fried soft shell crab was a miss because I felt it was fried too long and I could taste the slightest note of burnt bitterness. Overall still a 5/5 experience:)

We were served by Moon, Chin Chin and Maggie during our visit to Man Fu Yuan. I must say their services were tip top and the food was fantastic, especially the herbal drunken prawns. I must credit Chef Cheong for the wonderful dishes. Great place with wonderful food and services and we are definitely coming back.

Just had lunch with family at Man Fu Yuan. I have to mention Ms Rene who is an excellent server. Though busy, she took time to ensure everyone is well taken care of. With a staff like this will definitely level up the status of this Michelin star restaurant. Food is excellent and my family enjoyed the lunch a lot. Recommended for both small and big groups but reservation is highly recommended as it is always fully booked. I enjoyed 20% off with the IHG membership. Discount is not applicable with the weekend dimsum buffet.

formatted_address: 21A Boon Tat Street Level 2 Located near, Telok Ayer St, Singapore 069620
name: Meadesmoore

reviews.text: Walked around the area on a Friday night with hoping to score good steak and this place had it! Managed to get seated by walking in as they had a cancellation, but otherwise I do recommend making a reservation here if you intend to visit! Can't go wrong with truffle fries; gnocchi was pillowy soft, and the steak was done just right! Really liked the tri-cut options as we could tell the difference and assess which cut we liked more! Service was impeccable and every staff was right on the ball. Will definitely revisit for a 'treat yourself' moment again!

I think we ordered a little too much but still struggle to finish it all😂 The crispy pork ears is a great way to start with wine. Ordered the flat iron steak, had the mac & cheese (can’t miss this) and then contemplated the truffle fries and ordered. Goshh .. luckily food is good enough. It’s a quiet restaurant and love the dark cool vibe.

The highlight of our meal was the Shaved Ox Tongue; delicately thin slices were perfectly seasoned and flavours were well-balanced. We also enjoyed The Meadesmoore Cut, which is a generous portion of unique steak cuts for two. We ended our amazing dinner with the Seasonal Eton Mess, which is a delightfully refreshing treat for our palates.

Had an amazing time at Meadesmoore. The set lunch was well-timed (so the mains arrived together) and the steak was definitely worth a try - medium rare and with a nice crust. The portions were also very generous! Food was so good I forgot to take a photo until I was halfway through the meal (oops). Service staff were also very attentive. Loved the decor with the marble tables and comfy cushioned seats, which made the place ideal for a nice steak date. Will be back to try their other cuts!

Had an amazing dinner at Meadesmoore! The ambience of the restaurant was inviting and cozy thanks to the dim lights and intimate space, and the staff were both warm and attentive.

We started with the beef and crab tartare that blew me away with its perfect combination of flavours and textures, and followed strongly with their flat iron steak. It came with Paris butter and peppercorn sauce, which I thought complemented the well seasoned and medium-rare steak perfectly. We paired the steak with a side of black tomatoes, which helped to cut through any heaviness from the meat and introduced another interesting flavour! We ended the night with their seasonal eton mess, which featured bananas and a rum ice cream. Again, this dish was delicious and did not disappoint, ending our evening flawlessly.

Highly recommended to stop by for special events, or for whenever you’re craving for excellent food!

reviews.text:
I spent my birthday at Mimi, but didn't receive any special greetings or attention. The signature crab meat and lychee balls we wanted are no longer available. We were very disappointed when a young waitress impatiently informed us that all the signature dishes we could see on social media were not available anymore. Besides, almost all vegetables are out of stock, and the only options are broccoli and spinach. So we ordered spinach, but it didn't come for a long time. Until we saw that the next table, which ordered after us, already had spinach. We asked the waitress and she told us that the kitchen had forgotten to make it…

Fortunately, the flame-chicken is still available, very good-looking but a little salty. The mustard shrimp balls were the best dish of the meal.

Hope the restaurant can update the menu soon to avoid disappointing customers.

At first when we entered the building, the unit seems to be very unkempt like there was renovation happening, and there was no one on the first level to attend to us. Found someone who came out from the kitchen & told us to go up to level 2.

Service was bad although there wasn’t much customer to begin with. The food don’t come in sequence as well (we ordered set B & the duck&pork came later than the veges). I had 2 Amex plat card which allows me to get 2 complimentary drinks but they said they were super understaffed so they could only provide 1 complimentary drink…

Food generally was good, the best ones are surprisingly the cod & lo hei. I had better duck and pork..

When paying, the waitstaff didn’t even try to look at us when a few of us waved our hands and even tried to voice out that I am looking to make payment. I ended up needing to move up to them and said that I want to make payment.

Food was good but not good enough for me to want to go back due to the bad service. There were several hiccups throughout as well which one of them is not to change the cloth after doing lohei. So we had to eat with dirty cloth throughout. I couldn’t even take nice pictures without seeing the food marks all over it.

There were tables with lazy Susan, and I’m not sure why mine wasn’t given as we have 7 people. It wasn’t very convenient to grab the food as well.

If I had the choice, I wouldn’t spend another thousand here. 🤣

I had a very pleasant dining experience at Mimi's restaurant when celebrating birthday dinner and we're very particular about Chinese cuisine. We agreed and highly praised the Treasure of the Sea and Chicken on Fire, which she mentioned that it's a very good rendition of Chinese cuisine flavour. The duck confit is crispy on the outside but the meat is quite dry and feels a little tough at certain part.
The current oriental restaurant vibe and deco is cozy and intimate, which I think is a good direction than the original deco with very bold colours. We are very pleased by the attentive service from the team as well that even went the extra mile on serving the longevity bun for us just right before closing.
Other than that, it was a pleasant dining experience and looking forward to revisit again.

This is my second visit to MiMi, prompted by my friend's desire for flavorful Chinese food before heading outstation for supervision. During the first visit, the food was exquisite, and the presentation was meticulous. However, on this second visit, the items seemed more casual. Perhaps the first experience set our expectations too high.

Apart from the food, the waitstaff appeared less approachable. When we requested a hard copy menu, the response was, 'We don't have one, just scan the QR code.' Despite my attempts to scan the code, it didn't appear on my phone until I insisted, and they eventually provided a printed copy.
(food order is taken manually instead of via order online, why so insisted on scan QR)

We tried the Deep-Fried White Bait Fish, Chicken on Fire, Char Siu & Roasted Pork Belly Cubes, Camphor Tea Smoked Duck, Beef Tenderloin Cubes with Black Pepper Sauce, Crispy King Prawn with Wasabi, Asparagus, and desserts like Chilled Mango Sago with Pearls and Osmanthus Jelly with mixed fruit cocktails.

The White Bait Fish and Beef Tenderloin Cubes stood out as worth trying, while the others met standard expectations. One positive aspect was the background music, a well-mixed blend of classic Chinese songs that complemented the restaurant's ambiance.

Chicken on Fire-Interesting, but the meat is dry, hope can be improved…
Wasabi Prawn-can be improved too..

I like the following, recommend:
Fried Noodle-surprised us, one of the best of all dishes
CharSiew & Roasted Pork-Must try!
Pork Rib-So flavourful, best go with white rice.

You can’t miss:
P.Fizzy Brew-Chinese Tea Brew 😄
Peanut Lychee Mochi-my favourite
Yampaste in Coco-my sis favourites

Service is good, a lady staff prepared 寿桃, longevity bun for the birthday boy.
She did explained to us  too, on the change of menu is mainly due to the change of Chef.

Overall, we enjoyed our time and food here. Atmosphere is great, few tables of customers, so we can enjoy here.

Hope the next visit we can get more special dishes.

name: Miss Fitz

reviews.text: Excellent cocktails and a sneakily good food menu to boot. Really enjoy the octopus, halloumi, and truffle fries, and the service there is always warm and hospitable. Highly recommend this spot for a nice gathering with friends or for a post-work bite and drink.

They have the best Bloody Mary in Singapore, even better than St.Regis in my opinion. They sous-vide their tomato juice and make their secret sauce from scratch. There’s a nice kick from the tabasco so if you’re a fan of savory and spicy flavors, you’re gonna want to try this. Service is top notch too, the staff Khai and Ben are always so cheerful and friendly!

Went there for company dinner on Friday evening. Very accessible from CBD area. Parking is easy nearby at the Sail as well. Food is decent but it was a pity they ran out of octopus. Staff are professional and attentive. A little pricy of course due to its location.

Came for lunch and quite liked the place miss fitz, is the sister restaurant to the one next door (SOS) so you can also get some items from their side like the SOS burger
I had the salmon which was pan fried quite nicely.
I heard there’s also a secret bar here but didn’t get to try today but will come back another day for the drinks as I heard is interesting too!

Smart, relaxed lounge-like bar in a breezy, open ambience making it easy to socialise.

Good Happy Hour deals between 5-7pm. Very good 2-for-1 deals on Tapas and 30% off bottles of wine on a Tuesday evening.

The G&Ts were generous in size and both tasted very good.

As an added bonus, Roxy has just opened up hidden away behind Miss Fitz, so pop through and try their Signature Cocktails!

I would come back for lunch and sample the food menu.

name: Miyu

reviews.text: My first omakase experience. Chef was very attentive, made sure to go out of the way so you are comfortable. He shared some lovely anecdotes of his travels and experience setting up his own restaurant. Needless to say the food was impeccable - fresh, packed full of flavor and extremely intricate. I thoroughly enjoyed the uni with rice. Thank you Miyu!

Tried the Omakase lunch 98++ menu and add uni (20+) today at Miyu. Overall I would say the sushi served are really fresh and tasty. However the other non sushi dishes are pretty average, hence rated 4 star as a whole based on price value perspective considering it’s an expensive lunch. (Note: I didn’t post all the pictures of the sushi I ate)

Environment is really nice and the service is great! It’s a nice place to host your guest and business partner.

Dining at Miyu was such an enjoyable experience. The food was impeccable and the seafood was extremely fresh. Every plate was handled delicately and it was great to have seen the chefs in action - the food and experience is definitely worth the price. Chef Wjng and Chef Kwan were also extremely friendly and service-oriented, making the experience all the more enjoyable. Would highly recommend this place to Omakase lovers for all occasions.

Second time I got to visit miyu. The Chefs, especially chef Kwan is very friendly and attentive. He even checked with us if the amount of wasabi was good. The servers also explained each dish patiently and well.

Ambience: Very cozy and warm interior which gives a feeling of exclusivity, with soothing music too! Great place for a good conversation and quality time with dining partner.

Food: All ingredients were fresh, I especially loved the medium fatty tuna which MELTED in my mouth. Chirashi don was such a pleasant combination of flavours and rice is cooked and seasoned to perfection. Tamago cake was so fluffy as well.

Overall this place hits the spot with reasonable prices and would definitely come back again.

Well curated and unique Omakase experience with special touch of Shia of lowers, mini octopus in chawanmushi, melt in your mouth sushi and sashimi.  We ordered the Yuki lunch Omakase.  Can’t really describe the ingredients as mostly explained in mandarin and I blanked out a bit.  Had an incredible medium bodied sake as accompaniment.

Chefs and crew were friendly and attentive with free flow of pickled ginger and tea.

Highly recommended.
