name: Restaurant Reve - Singapore

reviews.text: Had our wedding anniversary here last night and everything was perfect! Food was amazing and one of the best priced Michelin restaurants in overpriced Singapore. Service was fantastic and they even prepared a special wedding anniversary dessert for us.

I visited Reve earlier this year and enjoyed my experience. The food was of a high quality, although there were no real highlights that stood out. If you are looking for a fine dining experience that is executed well, Reve is a good place to visit. The presentation of the food is excellent.

The restaurant is well lit but the atmosphere was perhaps lacking. Service was excellent but the counter seats are flanked by 2 mini dining rooms, and conversations can be heard quite audibly.

Wine pairings were great, would recommend to try. Overall I think this is a good entry for folks looking to enjoy a fine dining meal.

PS - pictured here was one of my favourite dishes of the night.

Awful experience for a 2 time 1 star.

The Amuse-bouche had limp crust that was suppose to be crispy.

For starters, the flower crab was fishy, sauce for the oysters overwhelmed the oyster taste and my scallop was overcook.

Appetiser were the only dishes we enjoyed.

Add on signature A5 Wagyu beef was full on tendons. When the waiter took away my plate, he didnt even bother to ask why i did not touched it.

At this point, the whole dining area was filled with fumes, never had this experience with other open kitchen concept restaurant, the exhaust was simply not working till the point i almost left breathless.

Lamb tasted like duck with no slightest hint of gaminess left.

Petit four again had a limp Canelé. First time we had a hard and chewy one.

Throughout the whole dinner, no feedback was sought. Only when I've called for the bill, the executive chef ask how was the dinner. When i feedback on the beef, he only said ohh, no apology and move on doing other things.

Utterly disappointing. At this price point, I'll say go somewhere else.

Exquisite food at an attractive price point. Here to celebrate a birthday and we enjoyed ourselves. A minor flaw was the signature sea urchin pasta - felt that the pasta itself was not seasoned enough and bland, it was only relying on the caviar for savoriness. It was also too soft for our liking, would prefer it to be cooked al dente. Overall, an excellent meal and we will be back. Highly recommend the A5 Wagyu top up as well.

This restaurant is value for money,All the dish are excellent!Must try!Yesterday me and my husband come to Reve celebrating my birthday.Chef Roberto is very attentive and warm.He noticed that my hubby didn’t eat the start salmon and asked reason.Chef Roberto made a cooked Salom for him!That moment we feel very warm in heart and touching!We went other Michelin before,even waiter noted my hubby not eat raw meat,but nothing happened!
We want to say thank you! To Chef Roberto and his team.we will come back again!They also presented hand backed dessert for my birthday,This is perfect birthday lunch!I will Remember this meal and Chef Roberto! Thanks again!My favorite is the start salom and pasta,very special!!It’s amazing!

adr_address: 56 Tras St, Singapore 078995
name: Revolver

reviews.text:
Food: 5/5
Service: 4/5
Atmosphere: 4.5/5

This is my review on my visit early in December 2023.

Food - We chose the following sets: Discovery Set and the Vegetarian Set. I really enjoyed all the dishes. Many of the dishes, I can see its inspiration from other cuisines like French, Italian, and that kind of incorporation with the dishes presented really showcased the blend of many cuisines. I also appreciated the types of items and flavor points that the chef highlighted for each dish. It does get pretty filling due to the time it takes per item, but if you want more food or to discover the entire collection of what the chef offers, then probably the Omakase would be a good pick when visiting.

Service - When it comes to the service, this was one area I think could be more consistent/needs improvement. When we first started, the chef(s) were pretty attentive to us, and came over to chat about each dish in our course, went into more detail, and were there to answer questions. In the middle of our dining, it switched over the the waiters, and it was more or less just reading off the menu. I think when it comes to this, it might be better to have either the chef have their full attention throughout the dining experience, or just have the waiters come only (to make it more consistent) Still, the service was overall really great, and this was my only main comment on which I felt could be better.

Atmosphere - The atmosphere during dinner was really cool, I liked the overall aesthetics of the restaurant, and the low level lighting helped focus directly on the food and people you are with.

Overall, highly recommend trying out Revolver if you get the opportunity.

First time visit in July 2023. Not really a fan of modern Indian cuisine but this place proves me wrong! All the dishes are heavily packed with authentic Indian spices, even the use of uncommon ingredients like scallop and lobsters incorporates very well with their unique spice mix. It was so intense that I have to ask for a palette cleanser half-way through the course (in a good way). Every single course was well executed and was very impressed with their fire-based cooking technique. Will return again and hopefully they can maintain the consistency.

Indian fusion, gaucho grill and rock music! A great experience from a menu of indian tastes but inspired globally. I chose the discovery set as I was full from a late lunch but I would try the omakase on the next chance I get! 100% recommended for food and great service from the chefs/cooks! Favourite dish was the turbot!

Revolver has been on my list of restaurants to try in Singapore for a while, and I finally got a chance last week.

The restaurant offers a take on Indian staple dishes that are cooked on fire/grill with international ingredients.

What I liked about the menu is that over the courses of small dishes, each one had a different flavour that was a notch above the previous one. Also, each dish had one tangible element of taste from a typical Indian street dish.

Our group was a mix of non-vegetarians and vegetarians. We chose the Discovery and vegetarian courses.

The menu changes quite frequently. This visit was in February, and we had the following dishes :

1) Hamachi, Tamarid, Coriander Jus - Small sushi-style Hamachi that is then coated with a tamarind based coriander chutney. This is closely associated with the popular Indian street dish, pani puri.

2) Hokkaido Pumpkin, Smoked Espuma - Not a big fan of pumpkin, but this dish blew my mind. A charred chunk of pumpkin served on a savoury base that had nuts. The pumpkin was crunchy, smoky and didn't taste like regular pumpkin at all. Really good!

3) Fresh Paneer, Winter Spinach - This tasted not too different from Palak Paneer. I would say this was just ok.

4) Dry Aged Turbot, Spiced dust - A well cooked, smoky piece of turbot served on what tasted like a layer of butter chicken. This had very tender flavours and the fish melted in the mouth.

5) Venison, Ginger Nihari - My favourite dish of the night was two well done sliced deer meat slices served on a bed of nihari. Nihari is a Mughlai curry that's usually associated with lamb and requires hours of cooking to get the right taste and soft cuts of meat.

6) Mikan Orange, Saffron Cake, Creme Cru Ice Cream - Saffron cake, which was warm and soft. Served with a sweet slice of Japanese orange. I would have liked the saffron cake alone, since the ice cream and orange diluted the flavours a bit.

7) Manhattan - A cocktail to go with my meal. Maker's Mark bourbon with Bitters. Smooth and complimented the food well.

While this is definitely a pinch on the wallet, I'd still say this is an excellent dining experience. For a smaller group or a couple, I would say the seating next to the grill is ideal.

The staff is friendly and super attentive. The chef came over to personally speak to us.

I'd strongly recommend this place to anyone looking for a premium dining experience.

My favourite ‘atas’ (fancy) Indian restaurant in Singapore - it has a very NY vibe, mostly counter seating next to strangers, and the flame-kissed dishes prepared before you. Food is flavourful and heavy, so come hungry.

adr_address: 18 Tg Pagar Rd, Singapore 088441
name: Ristorante Luka - Tanjong Pagar

reviews.text:
What a lovely place and friendly people! Definitely going back! First of all, we got the best seats ever - directly facing the wood pizza oven and the chefs expertly producing amazing pizzas in a matter of minutes. Seeing your pizza in the making makes you appreciate it all the more. The crust is perfectly crisp and charred, with the right amount of chewiness giving it more body. The topics are high quality and the right amount. Every pizza that I saw come out of the fire was perfection.
Side note - I was pleasantly surprised by the free-flow sparkling water for $2.50.

We had Melanzane and Prosciutto+buffalo mozzarella. Worth it! Will be coming back for more  ❣️

One of the better pizzas I’ve had in Singapore. The crust is crispy and chewy, the sauce on the pizza is on point, and the toppings are the perfect balance. Really likes my meal here, definitely coming back!

The food was absolutely amazing! Ingredients are very fresh and premium, elevating the whole dish. We ordered the prosciutto pizza and mentaiko pasta, tiramisu for dessert. Was just nice for two people, we were extremely happy and satisfied. Can’t wait to come back and try more things on the menu!

Very crowded on a Friday night.

The pizza isvery nice! And the tuna appetiser is a must order.

Water is free flow for $2.50 per pax. I thought that is very expensive!

Luka serves good Japanese- Italian fusion dishes. And you know it’s good when it’s patronised by many Japanese.

The combination worked well for the dishes we ordered. The Samurai pizza infused juicy teriyaki chicken with the pizza crust. We also liked the A4 Wagyu beef which melted in the mouth, and it was accompanied by an assortment of delicious vegetables. We also ordered a special of the day - Hokkaido snow crab risotto which was also great.

Giving this restaurant 4 stars as while the overall food was good, it was on the pricier side, and somehow lacked the X factor in its dishes (and hence does not really warrant the high prices when there are more affordable restaurants which serve comparable or better food).

adr_address: 19 Cecil St, Singapore 049704
name: Rosemead Singapore

reviews.text: First time trying. Service was really good and the waiters did a great job sharing about the portion and their recommendations. However, for some of the mains, portions were quite small. The beef and cheese puff was fantastic. Pecan pie a must  try item. Overall, a great experience but prices on the high side. 👍👍👍

My family had a great reunion dinner at Rosemead. The yusheng was different from the usual but refreshing and tasted great. The tomohawk pork and rice were also great.  Our server Pam was very hospitable and ensured that we were comfortable and enjoyed our dinner. Excellent service.

A casual yet warm dining experience with great quality. Value for money!
The bread (Shiitake shokupan) is amazing with the cultured butter best for the night.
The wagyu beef is tender and juicy.
Happy hour beverage is amazingly priced!
The pork belly skewer is very generous in portion.
Had an amazing birthday dinner here. Nice cocktails. Killer Shokupan. Really awesome atmosphere and impeccable service. Dhipan hospitality was second to none! Definitely would come back again.

Rosemead never disappoints! Their sides and mains are all so perfect 👍 highlights are the warm shokupan bread, brussel sprouts and amazingly juicy pork chops! Dessert were great too and thank you to the staff who decided to give us an extra dessert on the house for a birthday we didnt mention ❤️

adr_address: 100 Tras St, #03-14, Singapore 079027
name: SABAR Singapore

reviews.text: Had grilled half saba fish, spinach salad and beef tongue. Fish and salad was great. Esp love the salad with the dried fish flakes. Beef tongue is too much sauce and not so fantastic. They also have some promos on sale going on. Bill was $60. Seems that the place gets busy on weekend nights. Worth a try.

Very busy during weekend dinner time.
I had called during the week to make a reservation but still had to queue. No one asked or cared about any reservation and when I asked about it, there was no acknowledgement regarding bookings.
So I waited for about 15 to 20 minutes before getting a table.. sat down and waited for another 15 min or so before someone came to take our order.
I saw only 2 staffs waiting the tables , including the lady who was also cashier , clearing tables and ushering people in. Naturally, waiting time was long.
Food was good though.. very value for money bang for your buck. For 38++ you get a set with 3 mains and two rice. Saba fish was nice and fatty and freshly cooked.
Overall, food was good and despite the service due to shortage of waiters.. I think I might go back again if I feel like having Saba and rice for a meal.
The fried chicken was also good and crispy.
If you are an impatient hangry person, I would not recommend this place.
Be prepared to wait a long time for everything - to be seated, to order, to have your tea refilled etc but I think you will enjoy the taste of the food.

Came to try their lunch sets, price to quality ratio was good plus portions were generous. Their draft beer price was one of the better priced ones around as well. Service was prompt and fast as I came slightly after peak hours. Will definitely recommend their saba and negitoro don, which were really enjoyable.

Lunched here on a Sunday and there was a short queue at 1.30pm. 2 of us ordered the March promo at $38 to share and it was superb value! We had the saba fish, grilled miso pork and sashimi which was quite fresh and the set came with 2 rice and miso soups. But the star here is really the saba fish. The skin was light and crisp, the flesh was tender and each fish was at least 550g. For someone like me who usually don't like saba fish, this was AMAZING and I kept thinking about it the past week! Service was rather slow as there were only 2 aunties running the place but they do try their best. The older auntie even apologised for their slow service when we went to pay for our meal and we had such a good experience that we are going back again on Sunday!

First time I ate such delicious Saba Fish. Their Saba fish is very different from the usual. High quality!! Smooth nice texture and grilled to perfection.
We also ordered other things and it’s delicious too. The fried oysters is huge and  indifferent.
Service was good, my fiancé he accidentally spilled the miso soup and the floor staff quickly came to the rescue and replace another new bowl for him. Mind you only 2 floor staffs but they are super efficient! The restaurant was full despite the 100am mall was kind of empty as they usually serve mostly working crowd in that area.

adr_address: 6 Marina Blvd, #01-18/19 The Sail at Marina Bay, Singapore 018985
formatted_address: 6 Marina Blvd, #01-18/19 The Sail at Marina Bay, Singapore 018985
name: SOS Bar Restaurant

reviews.text: Came here on a quiet night, but so nice and chill. Service was great, and so was the food. We got the beef and pulled pork burger, recommend the pulled pork. Was soooo nice ♥️ thank you! Pet friendly too, the service staff gave our dog water. Cleared our food. Beer was worth it.

Work nearby, came here alone because I had no lunch plan - I liked it. It's relatively quiet for a Wednesday lunch break. However, I enjoyed the me-time for myself just having a plate of pork chop and a pint of amber nectar.
There's no A/C but it's good enough with the ceiling fans. Service was great and the waiter was attentive. It might just be due to the low number of diners.
I would come here again whenever I'm dining alone close by. Food wise, I would order other food options in the lunch menu as the pork chop was barely average.

Overall, I would say that this is a good place for a quick pint during or after working hours in a smaller group of up to 5 pax.
Order the nachos, can’t go wrong. The chips and avo dip was so good! Staff was great, met the founder and he was super chill. Would rec the interesting bloody mary if that’s your thing.

Unpretentious,  casual but in no way a dive bar, the SOS has got the right vibes for a quiet midweek drink with your friends or sweetheart as well as a rowdy, steam-blowing-off beer with coworkers on a distressing Friday or whatever day of the week you find yourself in need of a haven of respite.
Easily located, poised as a clipped edge on the streetside corner of The Sail, SOS Bar is rather handy. Public parking is available on the 4th floor of The Sail, reached by going around a sort of driveway/street that is correctly shown on Google Maps.
If you take the MRT, you'll want the blue Downtown Line, alight at DT17, station aptly named the Downtown Station.  Exit A. Walk across the street using the crosswalk and you are there. It's that easy!
On our visit we had a cold beer and a gin-yuzu drink, both just fine and dandy. Also tried the sweet potato fries which were presented fresh out of the fryer in a wire basket. Easily done.
Other reviewers have said there isn't much to see here, but I would disagree. They have sports on wall-mounted tv sets. This is a corner location not far from banks, shops, a hotel or two, plus there are residences in The Sail, so plenty of diversity as far as people watching if you're not into tv. Small dramas of lovers meeting, tourists being lost, workers being exhausted, expats being bored or lonely, all kinds of little stories are being played out on that street intersection if you just watch. Having a friendly staff, good to great selection of spirits and interesting cocktails or mocktails is a bonus. Catch a glimpse of Singapore here, especially on a Sunday, when other areas of the city are mobbed, this SOS Bar can be your haven of peace.
Highly recommended.

Drinks are okay but very expensive. The staff is friendly but if there are many customers it can take a while till you get your order.
It can be very loud and conversations might be harder.

name: Saint Pierre

reviews.text:
My husband and I recently enjoyed a delightful wedding anniversary lunch there on 16 March '24, and it was an unforgettable experience. From the moment we stepped in, the ambience was warm and inviting - we sat facing the Marina Bay view. The staff was incredibly attentive and professional, making sure our every need was met, the wine sommelier was excellent and very knowledgeable about the wines.

But the true star of the show was the food. Every dish we tried was bursting with flavor and beautifully presented. We selected the Set Lunch Menu and Wine Pairings, I would definitely recommend! It's clear that Chef Emmanuel and his team takes great pride in their craft, using high-quality ingredients to create truly memorable meals. We were surprised with a special white asparagus dish after we told the chef my husband was originally from Netherlands! We left feeling happy, satisfied, and already planning our next visit. If you're looking for a restaurant that offers exceptional food, impeccable service, and a romantic atmosphere, St Pierre is the perfect place to celebrate any special occasion. (I'm still thinking of the cheese platter and Omi Beef, some pictures attached!)

Thank you Chef Emmanuel and your wonderful team at St Pierre!

This is a small restaurant with beautiful views.

The food is fantastic with the crab dish and blue lobster dish on its own are worth the trip (best lobster we have ever had).

Some mild negative points are that the wine pairing was average and second desserts were nothing special. Though they do give some financiers to take home which are amazing.

Overall though - 5 stars as the food is exceptional and service is is warm.

This restaurant definitely lived up to its two Michelin stars. I am willing to make a detour to savour its beautifully prepared dishes and curated wines.

The 4 course weekend set lunch was aesthetically pleasing and the taste wouldn’t throw you over the edge. Although only one dessert was listed in the menu, be prepared to be pampered with more after that. Even though I wasn’t a frequent wine drinker, the sommelier was able to recommend a very fine pairing based on my crude description. The tea that i separately order to go with my desserts was also skilfully brewed. It’s these little detail of perfection that made this place unique.

The service staffs were pleasant and professional. However, the person who greeted me at the entrance wasn’t enunciating properly. I almost tripped over a small step but she might have warned me about it. I also felt that the ingredients of the dishes can be explained more slowly. The entrance to the restaurant wasn’t obvious as it served two restaurants.

Every course was well thought out, ingredients fresh, tasty. Every dessert and petit 4 was also delicious.
The restaurant also allows for children to dine in, very family friendly.. Provided that they don't run around and disrupt other diners!

THE BEST WESTERN MICHELIN STAR RESTURANT IN SINGAPORE

I want to thank you and your staff for the excellent experience we had at my wife’s birthday.  The service, food, view were all excellent.  We appreciate the extra effort to ensure my wife got the full experience of the menu, which most other resturants would just take the easy way out.  We had been to many Michelin star resturants, including Odettte.  But hands down your place is the best, even beating out Odette in all aspects (service, food, view).  We looking forward to dining with you again.

adr_address: 5 Purvis St, #01-04, Singapore 188584
name: Saveur Bistro

reviews.text:
Pleasantly surprised by this restaurant, wonderful food. We went as a big party of 10 (including 2 kids) and tried several dishes, but a few stood out:
1) Fine de Claire oysters - they don’t get any fresher than this. Freshly-shucked, with plenty of natural brine and bright flavours.
2) Onion soup and lobster bisque were both great. I haven’t had lobster bisque with such deep flavours for the longest time.
3) Bouillabaisse - heavenly with the bread. The prawn was grilled prior to adding in, which was a nice touch.
They have a formidable wine list as well.
Service was attentive, and the place filled up quickly in the evening. Would recommend making a reservation!

It’s my find for 2023! Hard to believe they have been around since 2011 and my circle of foodies have not tried this joint until I did.

And I fully recommend it!

Food is super! Authentic French and impressive collection of wine! Go for the lunch and dinner sets which offer fantastic value!

Would have given service and atmosphere full 5 stars but the joint is clearly understaffed although the crew can be seen doing their best! Place is a wee bit too noisy for me too.

But I definitely will return!

Had the set lunch on new year's eve. Very happy with the bread and salted butter. (They nicely accommodated our request for a second serving of bread and butter) 👍🏻 The burrata tomato salad was delicious. Duck confit was crispy and loved the generous proportion of mashed potatoes and sauce. Creme brulee was also creamy and rich. Service and ambience was great too. We left the restaurant a bit late but they didn't hurry us.

Highly recommended by my colleague and I like the food as well. However, the onion soup can be improved (my colleagues said too much pepper). The duck confit was nice. The noodle was delicious. I think first time I tried goose liver (Foie gras), not bad. Given 4 stars for service because they forgotten one of our dishes.

I had set dinner with baked Escargot in butter and parsley as entrée (🐌 it has texture like calamari, and its good), Steak au Poivre (medium rare, really good) and Chocolate mousse.

The wine list is lengthy, with prices ranging from $76 to $654. The wine list is not very useful for people who are unfamiliar with French wine, and the team does not include a sommelier.

It's a good place for family and friends gathering.

adr_address: 80 Mohamed Sultan Rd, #01-13, Singapore 239013
name: Shabestan, Finest Persian Restaurant

reviews.text: The food was amazing!! Highly recommend the Cold Appetizers Platter as well as the grilled Shabestan Platter. Compliments to the chefs!! Service was also top-notch. We had difficulties ordering for a group of 8 as it was the first time for some of us and we couldn’t really decide, but the recommendations given to us were fantastic. Everyone only had praise for the food and the service!! Thank you!! We will definitely be back!!

The staff is really friendly and made sure we got everything we needed. The food was absolutely delicious and specifically the ice lemon tea drink was amazing. Ronny the waiter really funny and friendly to us and I greatly recommend this restaurant to everyone.

We ordered: Muhamara, Ghormeh Sabzi, Mixed Kubideh Kebab, Javaher Polo, Baklava for 2 pax.

Servers were pleasant.

Dip, rice, and stew were really good. Highly recommend the rice as it comes with nuts and fruits (Javaher Polo).

Would have liked the kebab to be more grilled for the charred taste but that is probably a personal preference.

The baklava was a bit disappointing (prefer the Turkish version).

The Lebanese wine was very tasty as well.

Book outside on a cool evening, very chilled as you sit right beside the water area. Environment is super nice as well.

Huge compliments to the chef and the man of the match; Mr Arun. He went out of his way to ensure that the food, service and ambience was over and above the rest. He was uber helpful, attentive, warm and efficient. We had such an ace time hugely because of him. He is definitely an asset to the company. Thank you once again for having, we will definitely be back for more!

Was tasked to source a place for small group gathering. The challenge was a mixed request for vegetarian, no pork, no beef, and cozy dining place.
After immeasurable search, eventually I gave Shabestan a try, and it absolutely did not fail us! Everyone was so happy and super satisfied with the dishes. Meats were perfect! Tasty, succulent, tender, flavourful, truly representing finest Persian cuisine.
Every single dish that we ordered was a knockout!
Falafel, Dolme, Ash & E-jow soups, Platter & Lamb Shank (both bestttt!!!).
Thanks for the service team also to refrain us from placing excessive orders, we appreciated & enjoyed the warm service and hospitality so much.
Kudos, Shabestan!! We’ll meet again soon 👍🏽

adr_address: 2 Cook Street at Maxwell Reserve, Autograph Collection, Singapore 078857
formatted_address: 2 Cook Street at Maxwell Reserve, Autograph Collection, Singapore 078857
name: Shikar

reviews.text:
Ok so where do I begin! I had high expectations of this place. However, no matter how good the ambience and food is, the service can really dampen your food experience. It was a team dinner for 5 (two of them my Australians bosses who love to try  Indian food when they are here), for Friday evening, paid reservation charge of 50/head, expecting the experience to be top-notch.

Clearly they were understaffed and with some new trainees. The waiter of our table was quite in a hurry, never let us finish a sentence of what we wanted, cut us off abruptly before we could order anything fully. We waited for 45 min after our starters were done and we had to quite repeatedly ask 3 staff to serve our main course. The staff were worse than the trainees, and looked very disinterested to serve overall. And nobody even bothered to top up our drinks and water in between all this. Can you imagine finishing a dinner over 3.5 hours? That's how long we had to wait to a point where we didn't want to order anything more fearing the wait time. And the staff wouldn't even come to the table even if we waved.

We understand that some days may be tricky to handle with less staff, but please be honest and politely apologize to your customers. The waiter who attended to our table, gave all sorts of excuses in a pretty rude way and didn't even wait for us to reply back. Patience is a virtue Shikar staff need to be trained in.

Food was ok, just fancy looking, nothing out of the world, way too pricey (900$ for 5 pax - just usual starters, mains and desserts). 23$ for kulfi that looks and tastes exactly like the one you get in local Indian stores for 2$, so skip the desserts, IMO or just skip this restaurant even. You are not missing much. For the steep price we pay, we expect the experience to atleast not disappoint.

10/10 wouldn't recommend for service which is plain abysmal.

Came over to Shikar for a relaxed weekday lunch date. The restaurant is located in Maxwell Reserve Singapore, Autograph Collection.

This was my first time at this hotel, and it has a very colonial vibe, with a lot of historical paraphernalia. The ambience is very nice! The restaurant was about 50% packed at lunch time.

Shikar is located at the end of a long hall from the main lobby. The cuisine is primarily North Indian. We opted for the weekday lunch thali. They have a vegetarian option and a non-vegetarian option.

For the vegetarian option, I opted for Tandoor Roasted Paneer, while for the non-vegetarian option, we went for Pot Roasted Lamb.

The thali comes with spinach mash (palak), Shikari Daal (or Daal Makhani), Stir-fried okra (bhindi), basmati rice and a choice of bread (we chose the maize millets roti).

I really liked how soft the lamb was - it was really well cooked. However, the star of the lunch was the creamy Shikari Daal (daal makhani). It was thick and rich - loved every bit of it.

The spinach mash (palak) started well, but if you let it to cool it loses it's flavours. The okra and the paneer were good, but not outstanding.

The dessert of the day was kheer and gulab jamun. The gulab jamun was served warm, and was really good. The kheer was cold, and I felt it didn't complement the gulab jamun as well as it should have.

The service was just ok in my opinion. Our server changed twice, and weren't the most attentive, even though the restaurant wasn't at full capacity.

😍😍😍 A super premium dining experience

💲Pricy but it's worth every penny

🤩🤩🤩 The food is superbly delicious, and the ambiance feels like a palace.

👎 Booking can be a bit tricky, as they require a credit card with a $50 hold per person. If someone can't make it, you'll lose the $50, so plan accordingly.

Despite the booking process, the dining experience is truly exceptional.

We stumbled on this restaurant while wandering around Tras Street last week. Decided to come back here for lunch. They have a very nice thali set lunch. Small portions that quickly added up. But the portions, while seemingly insubstantial, were packed with flavour. We were happily stuffed before we got to dessert.

Shikar was sooooooo yum!!!! And the service absolutely amazing! I would highly highly highly recommend this place. The decor was amazing too!

We ordered -
1. Makhana with this delish chutney.
2. Garlic naan
3. Saffron almond roti
4. Kali dal.
5. Paneer.
6. Aubergine ghee roast.
7. The seabass in lotus leaf.
8. The prawns in coconut curry. So yum. Esp with rice.
9. A small basmati rice
10. Rose pista Kulfi.

name: Shinji by Kanesaka

reviews.text: Wonderful experience here at Shinji with Head Chef Ishi! We enjoyed the 15 piece sushi for $200++ and enjoyed the whole experience, interacting with chef Ishi and enjoying his artful, beautiful, and most importantly delicious sushi creations. I love how simple it is. It really lets the food quality stand out. He asked about our food restrictions before as well. We left knowing about more sushi & enjoyed their seasonal offerings! Yum. We also enjoyed interacting with other customers at the bar counter. We were offered sake by another kind & generous customer and ended up leaving friends. Amazing food and amazing company. Already planning our next visit back.

Had a great lunch there. The food was exceptional, so fresh, very premium texture and the twists in unique flavours w the different accents and techniques used. The staff, both the chefs and service staff provided very attentive and warm interactions. Raving about it to friends, well deserved.

Still as good! Excellent rice consistency with the right pressure applied on every nigiri, firm but not dense. Fish was firm and nicely sliced in the right proportion to the rice. Will definitely continue to visit.

picked the Omakase menu but to be honest, only their sushi are worth the price!
Get the sushi set instead!?!?
Really good sushi here, well deserving of their Michelin star.
However, service was kinda bad. Kept ushering us out in a rudely manner( even when my friend was still finishing her fruits).
Understand that you have another seating coming up, but please do say it nicely and friendlier.

Waiting area can be enhanced for guests, instead of being placed in the dark area. Chefs are all superb, interactive, well trained in all aspects, considerate as per universal standards of the fine dine Japanese excellence. Cosy space for omakase, ingredients are fresh, right cut, delicate culinary expertise in food presentation. Will be ideal for each to have more space and comfortable seats.

reviews.text: I would give this place a 4.5. The chef is obviously very experienced and talented. Watching him assemble each shari and gently place the piece of fish on top, was like watching a dance performance.  There were some amazing pieces and some “good” pieces. I would go back to try it again :)

If budget is no objection , then this Michelin ⭐️⭐️ Japanese restaurant is the one to go to . The skill level of the head chef and the best ingredients that he uses and at the same time very generous make this Japanese restaurant to be one of my favorite . There are many Japanese that charges a lot but under delivered . However , Shoukouwa is different although I still prefer the liver sauce in the Awabi from Sushi Sakuta as well as the Nodoguro . Definitely will be back again 👍

One of best omakase that I have ever tried. The abalone dish was a highlight with it soft texture and you can taste the sweetness.

All the ingredients were top notch along with the attentive service. They provide you with a menu and card detailing the seafood used in each dish.

We were very lucky to have the head chef to serve us when we dined at Shoukouwa on 8 July 2020.

The ingredients are so fresh and so thoughtfully prepared that it brings out the flavor of the food - we felt like heaven with every bite.

The food is best paired with sake. We had 十四代。It was smooth and sweet and flavorful.

Service is exceptional and we enjoyed our dining experience there. It’s unquestionably worth the 2-Michelin Star. We will definitely visit again.

This was a divine experience. Wemt there to celebrate my wifes bday and it's actually my first omakase experience. Food was excellent, vibe was excellent, everything was just top notch. A bit on the expensive side but well worth it. Location is also awesome. After a nice meal you can go outside and walk by the river taking photos. Trull a magnificent place to go to for special events.

name: Sommer

reviews.text:
Sommer is a one Michelin star awarded in 2023. I came on a Friday night for their spring tasting menu as part of my birthday celebration.

Every dish was well thought out and brilliantly put together. Presentation was simple and elegant. Dishes seemed to be focus on using good ingredients without having too sophisticated or complex elements. My favorites were the brioche and kombu butter and Brittany cod.

The complimentary birthday cake was probably the best I ever had which is a pineapple flavored cake.

Lastly, special shoutout to Lelia who made the whole experience so enjoyable. Fine dining is something most Singaporeans don’t enjoy everyday so being able to have it without being too pretentious can largely be due to the way the service staff engages you. A genuine looking smile, constantly topping up our tap water, being situationally aware, recommending dishes without being pushy, and taking photos voluntarily is just a few of the many things that made the night very enjoyable. Hospitality at its best!

Ambience and atmosphere were great. Intimate feel but yet didn’t make you feel awkward.

Food were great. Flavour and taste were on point with each and every course having their distinct personalities and yet bring you to the next course with ease.

Wine paring were wonderful as well for those who like to drink.

Worth to check them out.
A memorable birthday lunch at one of my favourite restaurants. Chef Lewis Barker and his team always on top of their A game. Elegant, refined and deserving of their Michelin star. Bravo 👏

Wonderful Birthday dinner at Sommer.

My wife and I are regulars are Sommer and like to have celebrations here as it feels so special.

The service was superb from our arrival through to our departure - with the staff making sure my Wife’s 50th was memorable.

Our table was by the window with views across Marina Bay to the light show and MBS. Inside we looked across the dining room to the open kitchen where we could watch the Chef putting the finishing touches to each plate - on occasion he would visit our table to say hi and deliver / explain a dish.

The food was stunning to look at with first rate produce prepared and presented on immaculate plates. Luckily the flavours match the looks. From the lush green flavours in the canapés, the fresh tastes of the ocean in the mid course, to the rich earthy tones of the mains.

If you’re drinking they have an extensive wine list and are happy to chat with you to ensure you get just what you’re looking for.

With the price of eating out in Singapore ever on the rise Sommer is one of the view places that resists the urge to raise prices just because they feel they can and it’s one of the very few restaurants in it’s class where we feel you’re still getting value for money.

In summary. Go eat at Sommer. It’s fancy, yet relaxed, with excellent service and wonderful food. You won’t regret it.

Celebrated my birthday🎂at Sommer. The restaurant is in a great location, and you can take a walk after meal to see the view of Marina Bay.

We opted for the lunch set menu and extra scallop. However, I think the baking trumped the main course. The bread before meal and all the desserts were delicious, especially liked the chocolate one and the pistachio puffs. And thanks to the restaurant for the birthday cake.

The only drawback was that the food was served a little too long and the table that came later than us even got the same food before us.

reviews.text:
Interior is dated, food is good but not excellent. Definitely not up to the standards for the price paid. What’s ridiculous is that Dimsum and appetiser came after all the mains are served.

But it was during CNY period so it must be busy for them as well. Charge $30 for corkage.

For the price that I’m paying, this restaurant is a no go.

My girlfriend suggested Song Garden as we were craving for Dim Sum.
We visited on a weekday lunch without an appointment and was swiftly ushered to a table after the manager asked for my name. It is uncommon for restaurants to be asking for the diner's name (unless you have a prior reservation and they wanted to clarify). My doubts were lifted when the manager returned with the menu addressing me personally and this went on throughout the luncheon. And that to me, is customer service at its best.

Our orders were Stir-fried Carrot Cake with Signature Chilli sauce (8/10) the chilli sauce in my opinion was a tad 'meh', Abalone with Black Truffle (9/10), Steamed Vegetarian Crystal Dumpling (8/10), Double Boiled Sharks' Fin Dumpling (8.5/10), the soup was flavourful though the dumpling skin was a little too soft for my liking, Steamed Prawn Dumpling (7/10) and lastly Steamed Diced Seafood in Pancake (8/10), it was a bummer to see a crabstick but the pancake was soft and good!

Overall, I am beyond impressed with the impeccable service from the manager and the wait staff were great as well. The food were served piping hot and our tea constantly replenished without the need to remind (even when they were full). The oriental theme decor is pretty too.

Perhaps the day we visited was packed, we literally had to raise our voices to compete with the other diners. I will definitely return.

Service staff are  great, very thoughtful and nice to chat with. Very attentive with tea service (one of the better ones who looked out for tea pot refills from the customers without needing the customers to request)

Food is nice enough for the guests to want to come back. Very generous and ncie serving of har gaw. Liu sha bao is very well made too (no dried up ones). Eggy prawn hor fun has a very nice wok hei and one of the stand out dishes. Recommend to order veg cooked in their broth (broth is v tasty). Otah siew mai can give it a miss.

Will come back

The food quality is overall average. Lobster soup is rich in taste but the serving of the lobster is under expectation. In fact most of the dishes portion is relatively small for that price range.

Service experience is also under expectation. We sat at a place with a blind spot and the service staff are not attentive to our request. I have to walk to the counter for help. Suggest to provide some electronic buzzing system if the restaurant has under staff to serve the customer.

Came across this place via Google search.
Suppose to come here for DimSum. But only available in the afternoon.
But we still decided to stay for dinner.

Food is not bad, very well presented. Taste is pretty ok especially the chicken and the laksa prawn.

But when comes to the service by the restaurant staff, I gotta give them a lower rating. It certainly under expectations.

Firstly, they are not welcoming at all when we were at the counter waiting to be seated.

Secondly, the waiter is not attentive. They have no smile at all (which is important in service line).
When we request for tea or request him to add hot water, he just came and grab the teapot and go off with super monotonous attitude. When we say thank you, the staff don't even response at all (basically like a robot).

Therefore, I don't think we will come back again. The food is ok but definitely not the best compare to the same level restaurant elsewhere. Also the service staff and their attitude didn't impress us despite the restaurant is not busy at all (only 3 tables including our table).

reviews.text: We came in for a late lunch after choosing from a list of Michelin-recommended Peranakan restaurants. Our server was very knowledgeable about the food and made several recommendations. Overall, the food was very good and we got to try different things we never had before. However, our server hovered over us throughout our meal and it became very uncomfortable. Our friend even told her that we needed space so we could enjoy our meal but she ignored that request. We also were not aware that the shrimp chips she automatically placed on our table when we sat down were $3 each little basket (the size of a fist). Our kids grabbed them and devoured them quickly. We only found out when we got our bill that they weren’t complimentary. They also charged us for water, which it did say on their menu to be $1.50 per person. Nowhere else in Singapore did they charge us for water or automatically put snacks on our table that we were supposed to refuse if we didn’t want to get charged. We have experienced this in Italy, but we weren’t in Italy. When we brought it up to our server, she said patronizingly that “nothing in Singapore is free”, which was not our experience at any other restaurant there. We find it to be a shady business practice and would not wish to go back again if we visit Singapore in the future.

Haven visit here for 2 years and the quality still good! Brought overseas colleagues to have a taste of Peranakan food culture that is uniquely  Southeast Asia. #preservetheculture

Love the Assam Curry Fish Head, fish is not overcooked and it doest taste fishy. The curry is rich and flavorful, unlike those curry powered water. #youknowwhatimean

The beef rendang are tender and the sauce is packed with spice flavor. #addriceplease!

Staffs are friendly and attentive. I was trying to explain to my overseas colleagues what is buah keluak and the effort required to turn it into a dish that is unique to Southeast Asia and how the blue colored rice are pure organic and not through food dye which then they were laughing in surprise. And I guessed my conversation overheard by the staff, she brought out the raw buah keluak and blue peas flower to show and further explained to my colleagues. She even brought out kueh kueh for them to try knowing they have not tried before. #brilliantservice #feelslikehome

Personally I love spicy food, though the food is not spicy to my level (just like most food places to cater for general crowd), but i can never discount the flavors that my palete had very much enjoyed today. #foodispersonal #hatersgonnabehaters #iloveitandyoucanchoosenotto

#shoutout to Linda and Nancy, thank you for giving my colleagues a wonderful experience

Eric Lye

Thank you Nancy for serving 15 of us so well, advising us on what signature dishes and how much to order, and attending to our various requests (vegan diner, refill water, extra plates etc.) so quickly. Food was served fast and everyone enjoyed every single dish!

This place is specially catered for tour groups. The decoration is quite attentive. But food so so only.  Sayur Lodeh quite ok, taste like lontong. Udang Sambal is not what we expected, is not red in color, not spicy at all. Most important, the prawn is not fresh. Cause we thought all are spicy, we order ikan Manis. This is sweet and sour fish slides, normal. Ordered their signature, but only gave us chicken breast, even the taste still ok, but too dry. The cendol flavor not good, the taste of coconut milk not good, gula melaka taste also not enough.

Quick lunch with colleagues over at this nice quaint restaurant. Had the curry assam fish head (recommend), kailan (so so) and the assam goreng sotong (so so)

Food is generally okay. Service as well. Was a little disappointed that they only had Tiger Beer even though the menu listed more beer options.

reviews.text: Highlight of the meal is definitely the Peking duck. Asked to cook the meat with noodles and deep fried. Each style has a cost. Dim sum was good but the yam was the stand out for sure. Not the cheapest for sure but great service. Note that this place is not under Marriott Bonvoy.

Our anniversary at Summer Pavilion was enchanting. The refined setting, flawless service, and delectable Chinese cuisine created an unforgettable experience. Every dish was a burst of flavors, complemented by the breathtaking views. A truly ideal spot for celebrating special moments with your loved one.

My experience here was top-notch from beginning to end! The receptionist was quick to respond and very accommodating. The staffs (Karen and another helpful staff) were exceptional in their customer service and knowledge of the menu. The food, especially the poached rice with lobster, was outstanding, and the complimentary birthday dessert was simply delicious.

Very impressive service. All staffs are professional at the top notch. Specially thanks to Mr. Kelvin / Keion, very approachable & attentive. Suggestions are practical, humble & cheerful.

Food is awesome. The fish collagen soup is a must! Love the tea duck & poach rice so much. Dessert the mochi sesame ball is authentic & soft chewy. Can't forget the Oolong lychee (hot), never had such an aromatic tea since. Try it to believe 😍🥰

Overpriced and underwhelming. Not a standalone restaurant, still depending under the shadow of The Ritz-Carlton.

On early arrival, the receptionists (yes, more than one) were unable to think of an alternative option to keep guests preoccupied whilst waiting for opening time. None of them knew anything about the display at the reception area which could keep guests entertained since they weren't doing anything anyway until opening time or suggest a bar option within the hotel. They were completely oblivious to the situation.

I did like their wagyu starters especially that mouthful truffle oil explosion. However, their so-called amuse-bouche dubbed by staff as "the one not on the menu" was totally unnecessary and an added effort to my jaw. No sommelier to actually go through with the pairing and the rest of the dishes weren't exceptional. Bird's nest soup with chicken wasn't extraordinary. It came off as just a filling liquid with a gimmicky coconut shell bowl. Chicken meat was just boiled separately, taken out and dumped into the "double-boiled" bird's nest soup. Abalone was leathery. Finally, I was pleased with the smoked duck and was really looking forward to the lobster. What a shame. Watered down with unremarkable lobster meat and just the idea of rice cake swimming in thin soup is ridiculous. Might as well make a rice porridge. I was hoping the desserts would really kill it. Nope. Epic fail. Bland. Bland. Bland. What a waste. And no little petit fours to end since they so blatantly introduced an amuse-bouche to start.

Now here comes what I was hoping they would live up to; their tagline, "It's always summer at the pavilion" with their beautifully and elegantly displayed china, and the variety of colour from the brochure and what did I get? Boring black and white. With just the occasional coloured plates.

But I'm not finished yet. Dinner ended at 21:00H and was hoping for a kitchen tour or maybe a little hello with the chef like most Michelin restaurants do, only to be declined saying it's the busiest time of their service. But there were hardly anyone. Empty tables remained empty that time with guests already finishing and exiting. What a snob replacement chef in the absence of the actual chef.

And don't even get me talking about the ambience. It doesn't command elegance. No soothing background music. Loud, boisterous, dressed in joggers clientele. Spacious seating arrangement, yes, but nothing stunning to be admired in the room.

Sometimes, I lose faith in the credibility of the Michelin. Time to knock off that one lonely star? Their "signature" tasting menu didn't come off special to me. I could most probably have just gone with the a la carte or the less expensive "peony" tasting menu (if I remember it correctly.) Perhaps the redeemable option was the (real) chef's recommendations.

reviews.text:
First of all, the view and ambience here is amazing! It’s perfect for a relaxing and memorable date night or gathering with friends and family.

The service here was also exceptional. The staff were extremely meticulous, almost as if they could read our minds.

Lastly, the food was on-point as well. We got the 8 course set, where they served us everything from tacos to steak and churros. It was even better with the lime margarita (the best I’ve had thus far)

Strongly recommend this place to anyone looking to have great food, an enjoyable time and a memorable experience!

Super Loco Customs House in Singapore has really good Mexican food. The quesadillas were awesome and the salad was fresh and tasty. The people working there were super nice too. Great place to eat if you like Mexican food!

Had a satisfyingly delicious date night here. Ordered 2 starters, 4 tacos (2x fish, 2x shrimp), a main and churros and (barely) walked away very full. We were pleasantly surprised at the amount of fish in the fish tacos.
For drinks we had margaritas and micheladas. Highly recommend micheladas!

got us a table straight away on a busy night without a reservation.
view is amazing.
service was perfect - super helpful without being over the top. catered to allergies and server was extremely knowledgeable.
food was amazing (spicy but amazing).

highly recommend.

Had dinner on a weekend night. Do book ahead as they mostly are fully booked on weekends. Fusion Mexican food and most of the food were well executed. The fried fish and the octopus wrap are my standouts from the meal. The hot and spicy drumlets are also nice if not similar to Korean chicken in terms of taste.
Portions do run small so I think 2-4 items per person is expected. The frozen magheritas are nice so do give them a try if you’re into slushy cocktails.

name: The Coconut Club

reviews.text: Great food, everything was tasty. The nasi lemak is fragrant and not too heavy. Highly recommend making a reservation for the upstairs dining room which is spacious and comfortable for larger groups.

Very nice atmosphere and superb friendly and very well trained hospitable staff. The coconut rice was very fragrant, dishes are like an "atas" or fine-dining version of Malay/Indo food. Overall a good tasting experience despite a more "tamed" version of Nasi Lemak vibes, however the chilli was fantastic. Their desserts were underwhelming such as the durian chendol.
We tried the coconut drinks. It is super refreshing and it tastes really good. The ambience is excellent. The staff were friendly and helpful. Highly recommended!

Came here on recommendation of a friend who lives in Singapore. The place is very stylish, not air conditioned too much, the upstairs area is very peaceful and good for a relaxed lunch. Of course we had to get a coconut shake and a coconut plus a coconut rice. The food was superb and beautifully presented. Waiters were knowledgeable and able to accommodate special wishes.

I had wanted to try out Coconut Club months ago, but the chance didn't happen till today..

Brought wifey to have lunch at the most "Atas (elegant) Nasi Lemak" in SG... Ordered - 2 x Signature Ayam Goreng
Berempah Nasi Lemak, 1 x
Gado Gado. Drinks - 1 Coconut Shake & 1 Coconut Club Mai Tai (Cocktail).

The Rice is amazingly good, smooth coconut flavoured. The Sambal Chilli is scaled-down drastically as opposed to our local flavour. (Probably to appease the tourist tastebud). Both the anchovy and roasted ground nuts are mildly salted. (Just nice).

Nice setting, nice ambience with retro music to compliment. Service by staff was good and fast with friendly disposition.
Overall it is a good experience. Will revisit again. (But in the evening for a cooler environment)

reviews.text: Tried the Feast for Two menu with my bf. We ordered cocktail & red wine, crab brioche, steak, wagyu cut of the month & spinach! Everything was really delicious but we felt that the portion was really small for the prices. Otherwise, service was great too. :)

Extremely good tasting food here. The steak was wonderfully cooked and seasoned. Furthermore, they had the option of unlimited fries which made it even more worth it! Ambience was perfect, a good balance of class and minimalist design to create a nice meal with my friends.

Utensils were cute, but presentation of the steak could have been done a little better! Also the steak looks normal compared to its taste, so maybe slightly better lighting and plating could do it additional justice!

The interior is really trendy and pretty, despite being small. Would not recommend the steaks here as it could be quite a let down if you came here specially for that.
But one of my fav places to come for 1-for-1 cocktails, which are pretty decent and of a good selection. There is something for everyone, from light to heavy, tall to short cocktails.
Not to mention the tiramisu here is quite tasty too. They also give free savoury popcorn made with beef fat and herbs which could be a little stale sometimes too. 😅

Wanted to give 4 stars due to the soup being too salty but decided to give 5 stars as their service is extremely good and they are very attentive. Nice food, esp the fries and creamed spinach. Steak is a bit tough even at medium rare probably due to the cut. Ambience is great.

Food was excellent and very reasonably priced. The steak was delicious and I will definitely be going back. The cocktails were just so so, but the excellent service compensate it. Would highly recommend sharing sites with friends and family and enjoying the steaks. 🥩

formatted_address: 13 Stamford Rd, #01-84B Arcade @ The Capitol Kempinski, Singapore 178905
name: The Masses Singapore

reviews.text: Restaurant was pretty empty on PH morning. Food was nice with a good twist. Kueh pie tee casing was soft, will be better if it crispy. Waffles & roe, waffles wasn’t warm. I felt it will be better if it warm and crispy. Duck confit > 5Cs pasta.

Went for the communal set and most of the dishes were great! Crabmeat Pie Tee was a bit fishy, Escargot and bone marrow was superb, C&C&C pasta was alright, but we really enjoyed the purple cabbage in prawn head butter! Nothing to complain about the two mains - Duck confit and Asparagus risotto.

Service was generally good, except that the older short hair lady could really put a smile on while serving the tables.

Would def come back to try their next version of menu when it happens!

Super yummy Wild Caught Lemon Sole Meunière - the brown butter sauce with capers is so addictive!
Their truffle fries is delicious too.

Came here for dinner and I’ll have to say the food was a hit!

Had the cold pasta, purple cabbage, wok hey duck confit and the Canadian tomahawk pork.

The cold pasta went well with the lobster bisque, crab and caviar, it also had hae bee to top that added extra flavour to it.

The purple cabbage was really interesting! It was creamy and the ikura popping in your mouth was like the cherry on top.

The duck confit was normal, nothing spectacular but the wok hey rice noodles underneath was an interesting touch to the dish.

The pork was really tender and the crusted parts had black pepper which gave it a slight kick.

Wanted to try the desserts but they were not available which was a bummer.

Overall a really pleasant dining experience
Amazing food, thoughtful service. My wife and i were in awe throughout. Great place for celebrations or to catch-up with friends. Would definitely come back again.

vicinity: 13 Stamford Road, #01-84B Arcade @ The Capitol Kempinski

adr_address: 48 Peck Seah St, Singapore 079317

editorial_summary.overview: Sharp, sophisticated venue serving clever cocktails & regionally sourced Middle Eastern cuisine.

name: The Prince (formerly Fat Prince) | Modern Arabic & Middle Eastern Restaurant

reviews.text: Absolutely impressed by the dining experience at The Prince, undoubtedly a contender for a future Michelin star. Offering a fusion of Modern Middle Eastern cuisine with Mediterranean influences, each dish is a masterpiece of flavor and presentation. From clean, delectable plates to innovative cocktails, every aspect of the meal delights the senses. The ambiance is refined yet inviting, with attentive staff ensuring a seamless dining experience. An unforgettable culinary journey from start to finish. Thank you!

Came to The Prince formerly known as Fat Prince for a weekday work lunch. The place is packed and it did take a while for the food to be served but the service staff was very attentive, refill water and take down order very quickly.

We all went for the lunch set which is $32++ for 4 courses. A variety from beef to mutton to chicken to fish and vegetarian.

My colleagues were raving about the jackfruit keema while I enjoyed my chicken and battered fish.

Pita bread and ingredients hold well and everything were fresh, while one of us could not take carbs and they also serve it with just the salad greens and the protein.

What stood out was the cashew hummus for me, I can taste the lovely aroma of it and it goes perfectly well with the soft pita bread.
The fried cauliflower was a hit, so is the fingerling potatoes too.

Would love to come back for dinner or ala carte to see how is the food like.

Went with family. Amazing experience seeing it was our first time there. The waiter was very patient to explain the choices to us. Service was impeccable. One of the best in SG IMO😉 Food was beautifully presented & the taste of every dish was “WOW”
Came for a weekday lunch for the set menu. The ambience is very nice and it’s not too crowded. I enjoyed the starters and thought they were flavorful, but thought the kebabs were a bit dry.

I decided to dine at Fat Prince for a special occasion after reading several positive reviews here. However, I must say that apart from the great ambience and service, food was extremely disappointing. Amongst all the dishes we ordered, we only enjoyed the cashew hummus and the battered cod as they were outstanding.

The falafels had a crisp outer layer but had undercooked, raw, pasty texture inside. We were told that is it supposed to be like that. So I let it be.

Grilled octopus portion was extremely small for $32++ and was so-so. It wasn’t as juicy maybe because it was such a small portion which made it easier to be overcooked.

Lamb racks were cooked well but we definitely have better tasting lamb racks at other restaurants in this country. The mint sauce that accompanied it was unnecessary since was flavourless and really basic. We were also told that they do not cook the meat according to the number of diners present. We have to order the racks in groups of 4 which was a tad bit odd.

Coming to dessert, we ordered the kunafe. It was good and not great. I was not impressed because as a patron, I expect a certain quality for the price that I’m being charged for.

It’s good to dine here once to get an experience. Will not go back again.

name: The Spot - Singapore

reviews.text:
Came here for a birthday celebration and had an amazing time with my friends! Kudos to the kitchen team for serving us amazing food (we all really enjoyed it) and the whole team for taking care of us with care

Definitely recommend this place to chill with your friends. A very nice place to hang out with your friends 💯

Recommend the fried squid, veal and the chocolate tart!

Had a great dinner experience with my bunch of friends to celebrate their birthday. Hola! The decision turns out to be the best choice of the night as we indulged in the wide spread of the palate.

We tried a myriad of appetisers and in particular i love the scallops the most as it was moist and juicy.

Next on, we had a few main dishes and the highlight for me will be the Iberico pork ribeye with mango salsa. The sauce complements well with the tenderness of the meat and the mango salsa is of a great tone to the dish as well.

Last but not least, the warm valrhona chocolate tart is the highlight to end off the dinner with the banana emas cream that goes well with the chocolate tart.

Kudos to the kitchen crew led by chef Chee Sen and VK. The hospitality of the service crew is terrific as they even extended their service to take great photos of us with the great food.

Overall, a fantastic night out at spot

Great food served from the 1855 group of dining concepts. This venue looks classy and resembles more like a cocktail bar with a large bar smack in the centre of the dining area.
Attached to a 1855 retail shop, you can order your wines and drink them without corkage while you enjoy your food.
Tried some appetisers and mains from their lunch menu. The must tries are the baby squid and beef tartare. The cheese bread they served was nice too. Try the green curry snapper and lobster capellini as well. Would give the pork loin a miss. All in, it’s a good place for a business lunch or short drinks after work.

The sides ordered were underwhelming.
Sad to say was very looking forward to the potato, but it was not crispy. The beef skewer’s meat was lacking of flavour.

45 minutes before closing, all the tables were asked to either finish up or be given plastic cup. Not an enjoyable visit.

Will not be visiting again.

- attitude staff that rolled eyes at us
- food was below average, wagyu beef was tough and overcooked.
- dessert feels like meiji matcha icecream well plated and price tag at crazy price lol
- on a saturday lunch, we were the ONLY customer there, could totally tell why now
- not sure why theres so many google review when the food is so terible with bad customer service
- paid $177 for 2 person, extremely terrible experience….

vicinity: 5 Straits View, #01-26/27 Marina One East Tower, Singapore

name: The Tavern Restaurant

reviews.text: Having a meal in this restaurant is like being transported back to the 80s. The food menu was limited in choices and the dishes were too pricey for the (lower than expected) quality. Wines were also expensive. There were only two service and one kitchen staff so orders took awhile to arrive. However, the ambience and service more than make up the shortcomings. Overall, a very pleasant dining experience and I’ll definitely return, probably for the set lunch.

the food is alright, the price is totally not alright. It should be stated as 2 or 3 dollar sign on Google maps. we were in for a shock when it cost almost 300 for 4 person meal. go to old habits cafe, the food and price there much better.

the owner is a cool old man that introduced us PUB Gin. other than that, would not go back. or wait till i am richer
Very friendly staff and good food..Wagyu beef and black cod fish.
Fantastic ambience on Valentine’s Day with great atmosphere and music. Food was great especially the Japanese wagyu steak and black cod filet. 100% recommended and would love to come back again!

Had an enjoyable fabulous yummy steak set lunch meal with great companion in this nostagia Swiss restaurant on a quiet afternoon. Will definitely return again for more:) Thumbs up for the excellent service Mr Raju really admired your passion in thisF&B industry. Keep up the good work and many more good years ahead👍👍👍😄😄😄

adr_address: B2-02/03/04, Canal Level, The Shoppes 2 BayFront Ave, Marina Bay Sands, Singapore 018972
formatted_address: B2-02/03/04, Canal Level, The Shoppes 2 BayFront Ave, Marina Bay Sands, Singapore 018972

html_attributions: Tim Ho Wan Marina Bay Sands Branch

reviews.text:
The beef noodles is worth trying, safe bet. I like their prawn roll, just nice with vinegar dipping sauce. XO carrot cake is a bit of let down, I don’t like the fact that relatively thick layer of batter on the carrot cake, though overall taste okay.
Peach gum dessert in coconut milk is refreshing and worth trying too.

This was our first visit to Tim Ho Wan, and we were excited to try out their cuisine. The restaurant’s ambiance was pleasant, with a cozy and welcoming atmosphere. The staff was courteous and greeted us warmly upon arrival. We were seated promptly, and the menu was presented to us. The dishes we ordered were all delicious, and we were impressed by the quality of the food. However, we did find the portions to be relatively small for the price. The service was satisfactory, but the staff appeared to be preoccupied with larger parties, and our smaller party was somewhat neglected. We were taken aback by the fact that even napkins were subject to a charge, which may be a cultural norm in Singapore.

Food is decent. However the dining experience is quite lacking. Main gripe about the place is that there were flies disturbing us throughout the meal. When we gave feedback to the waitress, her response was that we already have pest control and this can’t be helped.

Secondly, as mention in one of the previous reviews, they do not provide serviettes.

Overall I feel you can probably give this place a miss and fine at other venues in MBS.

Food was overall decent. Highlight is definitely the pork buns. Been dreaming about those buns ever since I tried them in Tokyo last year. Safe to say, they didn't disappoint.

I ordered the MBS special lobster chow mein and it was just a disappointment. No flavour and sauce was super thin. Stick to the basics if you decide to go. The turnip cake was also barely hot when it came out.

There will be a queue depending when you go, but it goes quick.

You scan the QR code on the  table and order .
The food was quite good  but I am giving 3 star due to their service . We had to ask for chili sauce and you hardly saw any servers around .

Special mention to the prawn roll in crispy beancurd skin , filled with fresh prawns and complemented by the sauce .

The xo carrot cake is one of the nicest I have had in SG, coated in batter and fried , subsequently fried with egg and bean sprouts .

The wanton mee was cooked al dente, loved the springy texture . Wanton was plump and juicy .

We spent $25 pax per person.

editorial_summary.overview: Casual, swanky spot with global buffet & à la carte menus, craft beers & outdoor waterfront seating.

name: Town Restaurant

reviews.text:
Great free flow of champagne for the Sunday Brunch. We selected alcohol Brunch. Free flow of Singapore Sling too. Super fresh seafood. Great Japanese section. And lots of pastries and cakes to enjoy.
A cute slice of chocolate birthday cake too.

Went for weekday buffet lunch with my hubby yesterday at Town Restaurant. The ambience and atmosphere was superb.The staffs are great and so is the service.Has variety of options,Indian food too.The desserts and the live pasta station were good.Also has ice cream counter.

Cons: Not vegetarian friendly.I am a vegetarian, and didn't have much option for food. The manager was kind and she asked the kitchen to prepare vegetarian soup specially for me. Thanks for that :)

The best buffet in Singapore!! All the dishes are top-notch, of the best quality, and use only the freshest ingredients. Thumbs up, and I highly recommend it to those who are visiting Singapore in the future.

Amazed at the variety of food selection! I have been to many hotels breakfast buffet locally and globally but never had the amount of selection fullerton town restaurant has even for those 4 or 5 stars hotels also doesn't have this much range.
I don't usually eat rice or noodles during breakfast buffets as im more of a western food fan however i gave an exception to try out this time as the chicken at the chicken rice session looks juicy. Never regretted! Its super tender and juicy and nice. You can choose the chicken parts yourself and the rice is also very fragrant.
The chicken noodle section also allows you to choose the ingredients you want which has a good 10-12 ingredients to choose from. The broth is clear and tasty!
Nasi lemak also taste great, not to mention the usual western selection of hotdogs, bacon etc...
They do also have a cheese station with the plain biscuits and smoke salmons which goes well as a combination.
For salad eaters, you will never regret their salad station. Its quite a big station which definitely the condiments or sauces you can think of to make a good salad bowl. Many ingredients to choose from too and they do even serve chicken breast for protein eaters.
Highly recommend their buffet breakfast here, outdoor seats are also windy as its sheltered and many fans around.

Place serves a delightful lunch buffet spread of local Asian fare such as laksa to other international items. Staff service is excellent and attentive. Very good range of interesting pastries, cakes and desserts as well. Food has been fairly consistent over the years - good value on the buffet lunch.

formatted_address: 60 Collyer Quay, Level 10 OUE Tower, Singapore 049322
name: Tóng Lè Private Dining

reviews.text:
Dish:
1: really great mix of texture and flavour. The watermelon seems to be marinated. It created a mind blowing moment when eaten together.
2: love the thickness of the soup, slightly giving msg aftertaste and slight fishiness from the fish maw.
3. The lobster takes the cake. Moist, retaining all the flavour, fresh. Eat it while it’s hot.
4. Also another mind blowing encounter with braised pork. The biscuit, I’m not sure what kind of texture it’s trying to achieve. It’s dense with no crisp crunch.
5. It’s abalone, nicely seasoned. The glutinous rice was a bit dry on the edges. Not much punch or stickiness. It falls off the fork like normal rice.
6. Nice end to the meal. Subtle tangerine taste elevating the birds nest and sweetness of the snow pear.

Visited Tong Le earlier for an intimate family celebration and was really glad we made this choice!

Wanting more flexibility, we chose to go ala carte instead of the set menu. The food was excellent, its taste, texture, visual were all on point! My favourite dish was really the Double Boiled Organic Chicken Soup, it felt so rich in collagen that we all looked younger immediately after that. 😂

Not forgetting the service we received the whole evening from Sarah and Joseph. They were meticulous, attentive and went the extra mile to make sure our special occasion was made even more special and perfect! ❤️

Thank you Tong Le for taking such good care of us! ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️

Every dish is on point. We curated our own menu and we emailed them in advance. We used the klook vouchers so that saved us $60. We love the ambience that the rotating restaurant has to offer. I must say the view of Marina Bay Sands is stunning. A great place for celebrations. We went there for birthday celebration and they gave us a free birthday cake. The staff were so attentive and took so many nice candid pictures for us. We really enjoyed ourselves dining at Tong Le Private Dining. Thank you!!!!

Food was really good for its price. We had the Colorful Cloud Dinner Set Menu. I will say it started out amazing and plateaued off around the main course. But for its price I am won't be too picky. Service was good, staffs were friendly and professional. The revolving platform gave a 360 view of the city which was a huge plus for me. Atmosphere was quiet when we came early on, but started to get a bit rowdy due to a huge party to our sides despite the closed-off rooms. But overall a pretty decent visit. Will recommend!

The environment is really good, it is a turning restaurant in the CBD area, you will enjoy different view during your dining experience. I tried Chinese fine dining menu here with 7 course. Love the Iberico pork, very juicy inside and crunchy outside. Definitely will recommend to bring client here.

editorial_summary.overview: Special-occasion spot with a classy rooftop bar, plus seasonal international meals & a tasting menu.

formatted_address: OUE Bayfront, 50 Collyer Quay Rooftop Level 19, Singapore 049321
name: VUE

reviews.text: We had their set menu here for my birthday. All the food was very good. Taste was on point. Serving portion slightly on the smaller side but usual. Food freshness and quality good. A lot of design has gone into their food presentation. Ambience of the place is great and the view of the bay is unparalleled. Only downside - price could have been cheaper. 😉

Was treated to lunch here at the OUE Bayfront by a good friend and what a superb experience it was. There’s a dedicated reception at the lobby where you’re ushered towards a private lift. The lift opens to a beautiful reception with an imposing hallway lined with wines and art.

The main restaurant is cavernous and well-lit with great views. Service is prompt. We were served bread with olive oil & vinegar, as well as pots of truffle butter to start. My friend ordered the heirloom tomato & salmon whilst I ordered the artichoke veloute & lion’s mane mushroom steak.

I loved my veloute which was so good that the organic egg felt superfluous. Similarly, the lion’s mane mushroom steak with the spicy sauce was so flavourful that the generous shavings of truffle seemed unnecessary. Although I had planned to return to try the other dishes, I might just enjoy these same ones again. Dessert was an incredibly sweet musk melon with berries (blueberries, blackberries & raspberries) and sorbet. I thought this was really well-balanced with the mixture of sweet & tart flavors. A lovely birthday surprise had also been arranged.

Many thanks for a wonderful afternoon.

View of Vue is breath taking. Perfect for a romantic date. Celebrate the hub bday here. We order a A5 Black wagyu that melt in your mouth but was serve a little too cold for my liking, we top with a foie gras which taste great on the sweet side. Cheese platter was great. Tuna tartar was ok. We also ordered a the Darjeeling Poached Pear dessert. Unlimited servings of Fat Beef bread with the dip was very tasty. The restaurant also surprise us with complimentary birthday dessert as well. The bill came up to be $600++. Outstanding Customer service by one of the male staff with spect, he is not only attentive, also very observant. Did I mention he is a superb photographer as well 😍. The Caucasian lady waitress gives off a tired of working vibe. Unfriendly, when we express need for help, she answered in a way as if we have no money to dine there. When we were leaving I say thank u smiling to her she even return a half eye forced smile, not really bothered by it but really 🙄. I would recommend Vue for the atmosphere, not too intimidating.

Good location, good food, good service. Celebrate my wife birthday. Went for lunch today, they are very kind to provide birthday dessert and also birthday card.

The restaurant is facing MBS. You have a very good view.

Will be back again. Thank you very much for making the birthday lunch special.

This place has a wow factor. The 19th floor view of Marina Bay Sands and its surroundings are astounding. Service was impeccable.

The angel hair pasta was one of the best I ever tasted. The halibut was perfectly done. I don't like fish that is overcooked. The duck breast did not have any gamely taste. The "melt in the mouth" beef cheek was tender and tasty. Definitely worth a second visit.

vicinity: OUE Bayfront, 50 Collyer Quay Rooftop Level 19
