formatted_address: 5 Straits View, Marina One West Tower, #04-02, The Heart, Singapore 018935
name: WAKANUI GRILL DINING SINGAPORE

reviews.text: We had a lovely dinner experience here. The reservation process was easy, and the follow-up from the reservation lady was friendly. The service staff was phenomenal! Attentive, friendly, and a special shout-out to lovely lady (I believe she is the duty manager?!) for ensuring a seamless dining experience and great recommendation. The food was exquisite, bursting with flavors. The beef ribeye was tender, although my request was medium well to well-done. The lamb rack (must try) surpassed expectations with its lack of a strong lamb smell. The creamy burrata cheese with fresh tomato (however, I do more prefer with cherry tomato instead of regular tomato (less old-fashioned flavor) and a glass of pinot-noir 🫰. For pricing, you may check on their website. Will be back again!! 🫢

Had the fireside brunch which was the festive menu. It was really delicious and enjoyable! The lamb chops were done to perfection! The steak and salmon were very nicely cooked. Service was stellar too.

Food, service, ambience were perfect. The service staffs were so hospitable. lamb chop was so juicy and tender, iberico pork chop was delicious. the scallop served with white asparagus and lemon sauce went so surprisingly well together. can’t wait to be back again

Classy restaurant located at the heart of prime estate. Parking can be confusing for first timer who drives there as there are two towers and the land area is big. The restaurant is reachable from the carpark lift directly from the West Tower lift.

The quality of the meat is top notch and the chef takes great care to bring out the best taste from the ingredients used. A good selection of wine is available for those who would like to pair them with the dishes.

We had a delicious family lunch here. Ordered from the Prix Fixe Lunch menu. Starter was beetroot cured salmon and soup of the day was parsnip but some of us upgraded to lobster bisque (superb). For mains, we had lamb rack, steak fillet, catch of the day. Desserts were hokey pokey ice cream (yums) or dessert of the day, yoghurt panna cotta. Also added some sides ala carte: sourdough, Hokkaido scallops, grilled octopus, and meatball pasta (kids menu). Everything was delicious and well-balanced. Even the purees in the sides/mains were super flavourful. Loved the mocktails as well.

Service was attentive and friendly, and they took special note of my kid and ensured his food came first. The place is lovely, has a good view from within the restaurant and outside of it.

Highly recommend for dates, special occasions, business lunches or a more atas family lunch.

vicinity: 5 Straits View, Marina One West Tower, #04-02, The Heart

formatted_address: 22 Orange Grove Rd, Level One, Garden Wing, Singapore 258350
name: Waterfall Ristorante Italiano

reviews.text: Professional service was provided by the thoughtful and attentive staff. An entire birthday cake, not merely a slice, was given to us. Most dishes were great. The highlight of the meal was the seafood stew. All the breads were also exceptionally delicious. However, the sea bass tasted very ordinary and the sky high price tag went to the showy ‘performance’ by the chef. Restaurant was too dim and had a funky smell.

Although the restaurant was fully booked for the evening, we managed to get a last-minute table thanks to the hotel’s reservations team. Overall, the ambience was cozy and we saw a number of tables celebrating special occasions.

Food was above average but nothing to rave about if we were to be honest. It was good that the restaurant had a kids menu so our daughter could try smaller portions of food that she liked.

We would have given the restaurant a 5* if service had been more up to the mark. We had to request for water refill, and for some reason the staff didn’t think it polite to switch the ceiling fan on after turning it off to light a birthday candle for the adjacent table (neither were we told before it was turned off). We would consider the restaurant for our next stay at Shangri-La, but would stay away for celebrations to avoid having to serve oneself 😅

I just had dinner tonight with my family at Waterfall and what a great night we had.

Firstly, it was a very last minute dinner and although the restaurant was full , the lady at the entrance made effort to accommodate my party of 5.

The ambience of the restaurant was polished yet cosy , like a posh Italian villa.

Tobias who was our main server and he was very attentive; service was fast and thoughtful at the same time. He explained the menu well and gave us time to decide while giving helpful suggestions. I could also see that the service staff worked well as a team, taking care of different aspect of the restaurant experience .  We had our appetizers, mains, desserts and drinks

Food was impeccable: fresh, tasty, good quality ingredients which shone through and just the right amount of flavor.

Even though not everyone on the table ordered the set dinner (which was good value), our food was served at just the right timing and synchronized to arrive perfectly so the tempo of evening was just right.

Everything is simply perfect about this place. Highly suggested. One of the best dine in experiences I have had for a while!

Thank you to Tobias, his colleagues and the chefs for a great dinner!

Food was pretty good in general but there was nothing outstanding. The beef was probably my favourite dish; it was tender, flavourful and not dry. Service was excellent and the restaurant had a relaxing atmosphere for a night out with family and friends.

I must add that our expectations did affect our experience.

Here for a 4 hands collab dinner, i will compliment the local chef, felt his land dishes were better than his partnered 1 star Michelin chef who likely did all the sea dishes.

Service and presentation is expectedly good.

Overall a decent experience for quality italian.
All dishes did have a slight flair/twist but didnt wow me.
The tenderloin dish and desserts were the highlights that changed my mind on not worth returning to possible return.

For Wine cockage 45++
I expected a more bit on glassware.

vicinity: 22 Orange Grove Road, Level One, Garden Wing

editorial_summary.overview: Stylish eatery offering elevated & modern French fare with Japanese techniques plus cocktails.

name: Whitegrass Restaurant

reviews.text:
Second time visit, as nice as first time 😊
Loved the fish and duck the most in the Valentine/sprint menu. Really unique and cooked to perfection. Bread was so yummy too.
Friendly and attentive staff adds to the experience ❤️

An elegant delectable sensory experience.  Nestled in the courtyard away from the flow of traffic.  Greeted with a welcome smile and made to feel welcome. Food options cover all taste desires visually, smell and taste. Portion size aligned to high quality. Worth a lunch while in the city.

Our first time here. The service was hospitable and genuine, no pretense despite being a Michelin-starred restaurant. Alex and Kim were friendly and was impeccable in their service. Food was amazing with unique combinations of fresh ingredients. Chef also came over to each table to interact which we felt was an awesome touch. Strongly recommended!

Well deserved Michelin Restaurants.
The bread is so crispy on the outside and so so so soft on the inside. Pairing with the bordier butter, it is really exceptional.
Every dish of the food is amazing.

The service is so good. When the table is full of crumbs, the waiter will clean it up to sweep away the crumbs. The waiter are also friendly and knowledgeable about the dishes.
When we found a bone in the fish and the chef came out to apologize. Felt the service was so good.

The atmosphere in the round room felt great too.

One of the best fine dining places I’ve ever been to! I can’t keep track of what was being served because there was just so many different courses, but each course was really tasty 🥰 I don’t think I’m a small eater but I was so full by the last few courses, I don’t think I ate any at all. Remember to pace yourself. I’m most impressed by their bakes; their toasty black sesame bread was literally the best bread I’ve ever had in my life.

adr_address: 1 St Andrew's Rd, #05-02 National Gallery, Singapore 178957
formatted_address: 1 St Andrew's Rd, #05-02 National Gallery, Singapore 178957
name: Yan Restaurant at National Gallery Singapore 宴中餐馆

html_attributions: Yan Restaurant at National Gallery Singapore 宴中餐馆
Yan Restaurant at National Gallery Singapore 宴中餐馆
Yan Restaurant at National Gallery Singapore 宴中餐馆

reviews.text: Nestled within the National Gallery Singapore, Yan surprised me with its delightful take on Cantonese cuisine. While the entire meal was enjoyable, the star of the show was undoubtedly the lobster vermicelli. The succulent lobster, cooked to perfection, paired beautifully with the springy, flavorful noodles, creating a textural and taste sensation I won't soon forget. Beyond the standout dish, the other dishes showcased classic Cantonese techniques with fresh, high-quality ingredients, resulting in a symphony of satisfying flavors. If you're looking for an elegant and delicious Cantonese dining experience in Singapore, Yan is definitely worth a visit.
I tried Both delivery and dine-in. Would say delivery was also recommended, but the dimsum may not tasted like dine-in. Highly recommended for business lunch dinner, or family gatherings.

I am surprised that it is a Cantonese restaurant , cos I feel that the food is generally blend, not sure if it’s for health reason. We ordered the $150++ per person, and the food is generally good. I like the lobster, while is slightly blend, but the lobster taste fresh and the texture of the meat is good. The cod fish is also slightly blend for me. The duck is good thought. The dessert is special, but mix the coconut ice cream well before eating, as it will enhance the overall taste. Finally, the Yu Sheng, it is so-so only, nothing special to me.

Thank you Yan Restaurant for making my grandmother so happy. definitely a pleasant dining experience. The food was good and up to expectations!!! :) hope there is more options of minimum 2 persons set menu for choices in the near future! Was pretty impressed that they really took the remarks and comments about the context of dining in their restaurant seriously. 🥲 will definitely be back again!

Did a wedding anniversary celebration here, found the whole dining experience to be great. It is pricey but 100% worth it as I was surprised at the portions provided. Really try the beef cubes with asparagus coupled with white pepper sauce. Staff were professional, friendly and prompt. Will come again for sure, hughly recommended.

vicinity: 1 Saint Andrew's Road, #05-02 National Gallery, Singapore

editorial_summary.overview: Hefty, farm-to-fork dishes offered in a comfy, American-style eatery with a waterfront terrace.

name: Yardbird Southern Table and Bar

reviews.text: Southern American restaurant inside Marina Bay Sands Shoppes that is rather popular with their well known signature dish, Chicken & Waffles.  The chicken was crispy outside & juicy inside, elevating the quality of each bite. The Mac & Cheese was excellent, melding together in a symphony of creamy, savoury, cheesy, making each mouthful indulgent yet not too heavy. The key lime pie was an exquisite blend of sweet, creamy, tart taste but not too sharp to steer the profile in one direction. We tried their old fashion cocktail, Yard which was unique with a piece of fried bacon as garnish. The let down dish was the crab cake which was mushy & fishy. Service was excellent as the waiters were all very friendly. They have complementary car park coupon worth $17 per entry during dinner time.

the staff named jewel is terrible. Got attitude issue and bad service. The food overall is good,  just the service wasn’t great, two of us spent 600 or so on the meal with tiny table , too much food, with no space on the table already but they just keep serving new food, I’ve been to this place few times before but this was the worst experience Wouldn’t bother to come back ,very disappointed

Opting for the lunch break set, I selected the protein power bowl and sweet corn hush puppies. The portions were impressively generous. The protein power bowl, featuring all my favorite ingredients atop a bed of rocket leaves, stood out despite being a tad salty.

The restaurant's atmosphere exuded romance, heightened by charming decorations—particularly noteworthy were the vases of lavender adorning each table. Dining solo, I expressed my interest in keeping the lavender to one waiter, but unfortunately, another waitress inadvertently removed it without my notice.

Despite this small glitch, it's a restaurant I'd gladly revisit. Next time, I'm inclined to explore their signature chicken dishes, curious to see if they match the excellence of my initial visit.

All in all, could be better. Ordered 3 mains and an appetizer to share. One main was served first. The rest of the food only came 20minutes later. We had to cajole our friend to eat first otherwise, food will get cold. And only when his plate is almost done, the appetizer got served. Then my chicken sandwich, followed by the burger.

Could have been planned better as this didnt give us a good eating experience with one friend finished eating first and watching us 2 eat.

Waitresses are okay - just doing their job. They asked "how is your food" but doesnt know how to respond and only smiled when we say "not so good".

Zero atmosphere, it's just like any other typical shopping mall restaurant. Will not come back unless someone can influence me to change my mind.

One of the better meals I’ve had in 2023, of course at a price. It is a nice place for special occasions. Portions wise for 2, we were well fed.

For 2, we ordered
Chicken with waffles
Lobster Mac and cheese (I think you can order the normal Mac and cheese, the chicken is filling)

reviews.text: Made a table reservation for at 1:30pm via WhatsApp, 4 days ago.. received a reply with confirmation. When I arrive today, the restaurant staff told me there isn’t a reservation under my name, and had to wait for them to get back to me, fortunately I was given a table, pretty small one after waiting. Luckily I arrived early before my guests arrive. Next is the menu set, during my reservation, I mention that one of the guest does not consume crab meat and if I could change the dish, the reply from the reservation team was a YES, but when I was mentioning to the staff today, she initially said no changes allowed, followed by a additional cost apply, so I had to pay additional $15 to remove my crab meat fried rice and replace with normal fried rice. I can’t imagine the nightmare of corporate clients when hosting lunch for guests, only to find out that their reservation was not recorded, and everything that you discussed with the reservation team is not valid. Next, the fried rice, crab rice is blend and tasteless.. while the pork ribs is very salty, and dry.. the dessert looked like something you can get off the supermarket shelves, without effort. The soup was rather salty as well, I guess the kitchen bought too much salt that they have to clear it fast. The only decent dish was the Lou hei. I highly don’t recommend this restaurant as it’s very unreliable, especially if you’re hosting important people. Funny thing is the staff forget to take our payment, and we almost walked out of the restaurant without payment, honestly I could, but I still decided to turn back and make the payment, despite the disappointing food and service. Probably the one and only restaurant that I would keep in mind, and recommend to my friends to NOT visit.

Cosy place for dinner with your loved ones with comfort food and also a yellow pot specially drink. We felt that the food was nice, reasonable portion but a tad pricey. But its ambience and staff service was really tip top. Staff was attentive, know their food well, able to communicate effectively and friendly. Kudos to the service team. We visited on our anniversary and the thoughful male staff served us a small cake for our special occassion. Love it!

Quiet restaurant with a modern Chinese decor. The service was great and we like how they engage with the diners. We appreciate that they have dishes for meat eaters and vegetarians but unfortunately the food was mediocre for the prices.

The dishes our table liked - fried prawns with sesame mayo, poached baby spinach, ee fu noodles, crispy pancake.

What we didn’t like - lion mane mushroom, fermented red wine Chilean seabass, Japanese matsutake mushroom.
They had some creative flavors which are an acquired taste.

Yellow Pot has a cosy ambience and attentive service. We enjoyed all the dishes we ordered. I highly recommend their 1) Roasted duck; the skin was crispy, tender meat and large portion, and 2) Black sesame prawn; the prawn was huge, succulent, crispy and flavorful. The servers were friendly and attentive. We had an enjoyable evening.

Was here on a business trip. Decor is very nice with great ambiance. The signature duck was delicious. Wine selection was great. Some dishes were a bit too ordinary for the value. Overall very nice place for group gatherings!

reviews.text: The BEST dining experience I have ever had. Service is top notch h. Food was magical. Would definitely recommend. ♥️

Had the lunch with 7 courses. First time experience in 3 star Michelin.

Service was excellent and the people working their really know their trait. However, two of the dishes didn’t deliver. One of them was the BBQ Quail, it was not salted enough. I didn’t find the dish overall to fufill expectations. Second dish that failed to deliver was toasted buckwheat pudding, just tasted soggy in my opinion and didn’t like the pairing with grapes. The seabuckthorn sorbet was however excellent and so was the onion soup. The grijesi fish with the emulsion was OK.

The staff and the concept of walking up the stairs was really nice however.

We went to Zén for a lunch for my wife's birthday, it was our first 3* so our expectations were high.

Overall feedback is great: the food quality is high class and some dishes really stand out. The service is young and somewhat casual but serious and refined at the same time. It is an experience. It comes with a hefty price of course but at this level it is the price of hard work and product excellence.

The place is cosy and comfortable, definitely lovely to spend a few hours to savour the menu, and suitable for a special occasion. The choice of rock/pop music on the loud side in the dining room worked well for us but it is unusual.

What we liked less was the non alcoholic pairing which was oriented towards fermented and acidic drinks (kombucha type). Lot of work goes into it I'm sure but it's an acquired taste that didn't work for us.
Also there is almost no carb in the menu and the restaurant doesn't offer any bread so we felt something was missing.

Overall I still give it 5* and applaud the work going into creating an experience like this. We feedbacked some of our minor disappointments to the restaurant and they responded very nicely.

Detailed menu review (spoiler alert)

Starter: excellent amuse-bouches, especially the choux. It is so good and so small you wish you could eat more. 10/10

Saba fish: good fresh fish dish with an interesting strawberry dressing. 7/10

Chawanmushi with caviar: excellent. Very tasty fatty pork broth, and good caviar that compliment each other well. 9/10

Lobster: perfect cooking and sauce, beautiful product and great dish 10/10

Onion soup with almond and licorice: perfect combination, exact temperature for service. Though the licorice maybe doesn't really come up enough. But possibly one of the best dishes I've ever had. 10/10

Kinki fish: crispy skin is excellent and fish cooked to perfection, generous serving of cream is a pleasure. The mussel on the side was less interesting 8/10

Quail: cooked to perfection with good foie gras though the wasabi on the foie gras was not necessary 9/10

French toast with aged beef: not our favorite dish, because of the Wasabi being too strong 6/10

Yuzu marshmallow : good pallet cleanser, very fresh, very much on the Yuzu 8/10

Chewy beet: fantastic berry ice cream, very interesting beet gummy, good and generous cream. 10/10

Japanese fruit: great and fresh, especially the persimmon 10/10

Macaron: excellent, should give more 10/10

Birthday cake: nice touch, thank you! Finally some sugar and carb after all.. very good cake. 10/10

Thank you Zén

Zen Restaurant in Singapore, nestled within a Michelin-starred hotel, is a culinary sanctuary where artistry meets gastronomy. The dining experience transcends mere sustenance, immersing patrons in a symphony of flavors meticulously crafted by master chefs.

From the moment one enters, the ambiance is a harmonious blend of tranquility and sophistication. The minimalist decor, adorned with subtle Asian influences, sets the stage for a dining journey that transcends the ordinary.

The menu is a testament to the chef's dedication to perfection. Each dish is a canvas, showcasing the finest ingredients and innovative techniques. The sushi, a delicate dance of textures and tastes, highlights the restaurant's commitment to authenticity. The sashimi, served with precision, melts in the mouth, a testament to the freshness of the seafood.

The culinary artistry extends to the hot kitchen, where traditional Asian flavors are reimagined with a contemporary flair. Signature dishes, such as the miso-glazed black cod, exemplify the chef's mastery in balancing flavors, leaving a lasting impression on discerning palates.

Service at Zen is an impeccable ballet, with attentive staff anticipating every need without intruding on the dining experience. The wine list is curated to complement the diverse flavors, elevating the meal to a sensory journey.

In conclusion, Zen Restaurant in Singapore not only lives up to its Michelin-starred status but transcends expectations. It is a haven for connoisseurs seeking a symphony of flavors orchestrated with precision and passion, making it a jewel in the culinary crown of the Lion City.
My partner and associates were impressed with the impeccable dishes and service provided, the staffs are very accommodating and food was very wonderful. Will be coming back soon with my family.

reviews.text:
I was there with my family last evening to celebrate my daughter's birthday. We were pleasantly surprised to be ushered to a private room which has a warm and homely vibe.

Janson recommended a few of their signatures from their menu. Very impressed by his personal and attentive service that made our dining experience a most memorable one. He even surprised us with a birthday cake dessert!

The food was alright but below our expectations. Overall, we were satisfied with the service and ambience.

Delightful Italian cuisine. Excellent service and a distinctive ambience combined for a great lunch

Delicious frito misto accompanied by roasted broccolini. And a beef tartare pizza. And two glasses of specially imported Lebanese Cabernet rounded of an excellent lunch

Special thanks to JANSON YONG for making our church wedding luncheon extra special.
Great recommendations, excellent service, and fabulous food.
Highly recommended.

Definitely have a great team but you have an exceptional example in service excellent in JANSON!
The food is excellent. Both chicken and the salmon taste real good! Tiramisu is also fantastic!

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Il Cielo at Voci, and I must say, it was a delightful experience. This Italian restaurant truly captures the essence of simple yet authentic Italian cuisine.

I was impressed by the staff attentive and prompt service.

We were celebrating my son's birthday with a family lunch at Il Cielo and they accommodated our request for a special celebration by presenting my son with a delicious dessert treat. It was a heartwarming touch that made the occasion even more special and memorable for us. Memories for the birthday boy.

Their freshly baked pizza was our favourite. Il Cielo's menu does offers a variety of options, and I was tempted to try more dishes, but the pizza left such a lasting impression that I couldn't resist ordering it again on my next visit.

This place is a true gem for those who appreciate the beauty of simplicity and authenticity in Italian cuisine in a warm and inviting quiet atmosphere.

Grazie mille, Il Cielo, for a wonderful dining experience!
